column6: 9 Pcs Manicure Set Pedicure Tools - Nail Care, Art Kit - For Girls Teens Women Men - Includes Nail Files Emery Boards, Nail Clipper, Cuticle Sticks, Manicure Gloves, Travel Pouch by Perfect Life Ideas
column14:
Functional starter kit is the concept here - the nail file is rather nice (and always did prefer the steel over the glass ones), and the emery boards are individually wrapped (and thick!).

Cuticle sticks are splinter-free and solid tipped.

The gloves are decent without any seam flaws although I could tell there that there is excess cloth in the fingertips left over from the thread finishing. The sizing certainly seems suited for young girls.

The nail clipper is as standard as you can imagine, and doesn't give clean, crisp clips with the off-hand. Yet it is really solid construction. It's the kind you will still find decades later in a drawer and still work.

The travel "pouch" isn't a pouch at all, but just a plastic rectangle with loops to slide the bits in, albeit pretty sturdy double seamed plastic rectangle. But it's not the most secure methods of carrying (the smaller emery boards like to slide right out as soon as I pick up the whole thing).

- Complimentary product provided for evaluation, yet my thinking here reflects all my personal purchasing decision processes, and hopefully may help clarify if this best meets your own needs and expectations.

column6: Philips Norelco BeardTrimmer 7100, vacuum trimmer (Model # QT4050)
column13: Perfect for the price, but not perfect.
column14:
I purchased this about 9 months ago. As of about 6 months ago the part of the door that held it shut for the vacuum storage broke. I simply hold it shut while using it, and it still works. It is true that this product will not catch 100% of long hairs if you have a full beard. When I trim my beard it will catch any where from 70-80% of the hair... which is better than nothing. Currently I have a little over an inch long beard hairs, just so you know where I am coming from.
If you don't use the attachment and are just clean shaving than this does a really good job of catching 99% of the hair, so long as you don't over fill the little storage area. For the price of this product this is exactly on point with what should be expected. If this product cost anywhere near all the others out there, that don't have vacuums built in, then I would be giving it less stars. As it stands 4 stars is what this gets as it hasn't failed me, and has reduced the mess that I have to clean countless times. Is it perfect? No, of course not, but its only 39 bucks.

My husband stole my purse-sized container of this lotion, and asked if I could order more. Here's the review:

First off, I love that it's available in a pump size. All lotion in the world should come with a pump. It just makes sense.

Gold Bond itself is an incredible product. I love their powder, and the lotion does not disappoint. This has a great, silky feel and leaves skin smooth. The pleasant scent is not too strong or overpowering. Perfect for man or woman or anything in between. Gentle enough to use on face (yes, my husband does this) or kids. Not oily or greasy.

I'm giving this an A+. My husband's skin feels great, but you'll have to take my word for it. It's a great product, a great size, and a totally worth it great price.

column14:
I grow my own loofah but it take a few months to dry after the growing season so I am all out right now. It pains me to have to purchase it but this brand took me by surprise. I really like that each loofah comes with a nice thick rope to hang it while not in use (you get 2 in the pack). They also come with a suction cup to stick to your shower (or shower door) to hang them on. It did smell different than the ones I grow. It had a grassy scent to it. It's not over powering but noticeable when I put it up to my nose.

I only use loofahs for my feet. I rub the end of the loofah on my bar of soap and go to town. They work great at removing dead skin that builds up to create callouses and tough heels. They were firm but not stiff as a board like some loofas are. They get a little bet softer when you get them wet. Ive had some in the past that were hard as a rock! All in all I love these!

*I received this product as a promotion in exchange for my honest review. I was neither paid nor sponsored for my opinions and all thoughts reflected in this review are solely my own.

column6: Imako Cosmetic Upper Teeth (Small Natural)
column14: I am very satisfied with this product.  My upper teeth are in terrible shape, and needed something to cover them until I have some extensive dental work done in about 2 months.  Well, they've turned out to be exactly what I needed.  They fit perfectly over my upper teeth and I can smile again and not feel so self-conscious.  Now, don't expect to get a perfect fit the first time.  I had to rework the adhesive several times before  I got it right, but it was worth the effort.  I went to the Imako Youtube presentation and followed the instructions exactly.  Again, it wasn't fitting properly the first several times I tried to fit the teeth.  But I continued to rework the adhesive, and after about the 6th or 7th time, I got a very secure and presentable fit. Now, I had to use a different fitting technique than the one that was in the Youtube presentation but, again, my efforts paid off, and I just love the result.  I wish Imako would include more of the adhesive as you lose a small portion of it as you rework it time after time.  But in the end, I had enough to gain a secure fitting.  Again, if you don't get a good fit right away, keep trying.  The key is to be persistent.

column6: Color Charm Permanent Liquid Hair Color
column13: I've tried just about every toner out there to find the best, and this is by far my favorite
column14:
Regarding T-18 White Lady

My hair is naturally straight black (I'm half Japanese), but I've had my hair pure snow white multiple times now. I've tried just about every toner out there to find the best, and this is by far my favorite. While I wish the less damaging toners would work, the use of developer and chemical process of this one is what makes the toner really WORK. Personally, I prefer leaving the toner on until my hair is lavender and within a wash or two my hair is white. It seems that going to lavender first and letting it fade out gets your hair to a better white, while going straight to the color you want will simply cause it to fade a bit more yellow when it settles.

column6: InstaNatural Retinol Serum - Anti Wrinkle Anti Aging Facial Serum - Helps Reduce Appearance of Wrinkles, Crows Feet & Fine Lines - With Vitamin C and Hyaluronic Acid 1OZ
column13: This product is amazing. I have been using it now for several ...
column14:
This product is amazing. I have been using it now for several months. I use it just after I wash my face (Purpose liquid soap). I use a moisturizer with sunscreen during the day and just the serum at night.

I notice the serum has helped my skin regain some of its suppleness and also helped soften the skin both visibly and to the touch. Wrinkles around the eyes appear diminished and finer. The same goes for the frown lines on my forehead as well. I am not familiar with whatever the general alleged benefits of retinol serums are and am only speaking of this particular product. I have been told my skin looks more youthful and vibrant in appearance. And at 47, I've often been mistaken for 37 - without makeup. It doesn't turn back the clock, but it definitely diminishes the texture by smoothening the surface and gives skin a healthy glow. Its not oily or heavy and when it dries there is no product sheen left behind.

To apply I fill the dropper and tilt my head and squeeze a bit on my cheeks one at a time and spread it around to my nose area, forehead, and over my eyes (with them closed). I have never experienced any burning or tingling but should say that I had been using a glycolic acid cream at night for many years before I switched to this product. First time users may want to use it once a day just to see how their skin feels afterwards.

The serum is somewhat milky/tawny in color and very watery. It may seem as if you applying nothing to your skin but if you give it time, you will most certainly notice the tone and texture of your skin improving.

column6: Garnier Olia Oil Powered Permanent Hair Color, 7.0 Dark Blonde (Packaging May Vary)
column13: It seems some love Olia and some hate it
column14:
It seems some love Olia and some hate it. For me, with dry, wavy, naturally red auburn hair going grey, it is the absolute best hair color and I have tried them all. Some tips and answers to complaints/issues: for even long lasting coverage I have found that leaving it on for a LONG time has been no problem for me. I leave it on my roots for at least an hour after application, sometimes 1.5 then pull through and leave on for another 45. Not only has this not hurt my hair, my hair seems to be in better condition and the best part it that the color is even from root to tip.

Regarding the bottle, I think its larger so there is more room to really shake the mixture around well. I have found that smaller color mix bottles don't provide enough room for the stuff to really move around and shake up - so it doesn't mix up well enough. Color that is not mixed well is not going to be uniformly chemically active. In addition to shaking hard, I stick the end of a comb or something else plastic into the bottle and mix well. It is key.

In short, mixed well and left on long enough this stuff colors beautifully, lasts long and conditions!

column6: Jerome Russell Punky Colour Cream Lagoon Blue
column14:
I wanted to leave a review after I have tested it for a month, so this is the result..
I bought this product to use on the tips of my hair for a sort of ombre look, which this works rather well for. I've tried other hair dyes before and they just don't work as well. My hair is medium-dark brown, but the tips are a little lighter. The first time I applied it I allowed it to set in my hair for 30-45 minutes before rinsing. It worked really well! Although not as bright as I wanted it, I thought it was great considering I hadn't bleached my hair. After it dries it looks nice and almost a teal blue. I washed my hair the next day (don't freak out when a stream of blue comes out because it's not removing all of the color!), and the color faded only some. After the second wash it does kind of dull the color, almost making it turn a greenish blue, which is no big deal to me.
When it comes to lasting, the color fades tremendously about 1-2 weeks later, or around 8 washes. I re-dyed the tips of my hair every week (letting it sit in my hair for one hour instead of half an hour) to make it bold, and that worked well for the first three weeks, but for some reason the color wouldn't take as well the past two weeks I've done it. I have used this product in the past with my hair bleached and boy does the color last! If you want it to be bright and last well over a month or two, I suggest bleaching.
Overall, if you're looking for a funky color to test out, this is the stuff to try.

Pros:
Great, vibrant color.
Works on dark hair.
Easy to apply.

Cons:
Fades within a week or two.
Doesn't work as well after so many applies.

column6: Philips Sonicare for Kids Connected Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column13: Brushing Goes Better With A Well Dressed Sparkly
column14:
If you are already familiar with Sonicare, you know these brushes give an awesome cleaning to your teeth, reduce gum disease, and are easy to use. You probably have already heard that kids tend to brush longer with power toothbrushes and also enjoy using them more. These facts combined tend to make the Sonicare for Kids a pretty easy purchase decision, assuming you don't mind the price. There are plenty of cheaper power brushes for kids, but none hit the high speed of the Sonicare, and that speed is a key part of the plaque removal and cleaning effect. The simpler slower power heads on $10 and $20 brushes will not get that same effect, and also many kids brushes are not rechargeable and do not include replaceable heads. Sonicare is certainly worth more for those added features.

However, what really makes this brush is the Bluetooth feature set. The free app, available for Android and Apple devices, is a clever design that encourages kids to brush by giving them a pet "Sparkly" which can be customized with gifts and prizes that the kids get for brushing regularly and for the appropriate duration. My 6 year old loves that type of thing, and though I am still doing the brushing for her, the animations that play during the brushing help her see what is going on, and the countdown timer helps her to see when the brushing will be over with. Finally, the one or several gifts at the end of the brushing are anticipated by her, so she can use them to feed the Sparkly, dress it up, change colors etc. The app also tracks compliance and will send reminders of missed brushings or short timed instances when the kids are old enough to brush independently.

The brush also comes with many stickers and can be customized to the preference of the user. The stickers seem to be holding up even with frequent wettings and the usual sort of rough treatment that a 6 year old can offer to any regularly used device. I would not assume the brush would hold up to frequent droppings, so if your kid is Mr./Ms Butterfingers or likes to slam things really hard against hard surfaces, you may want to hold off a bit on this purchase.

The Sonicare for kids also has lower speed / sensitive modes that can be used for kids, and you can gradually ease them into higher speed operation if the speed and power of the brush scares or discomforts them. My daughter was OK with fill power from first use, but its nice to know there is a gentler option available if needed.

There are few complaints. The brush head does not have a 90 day wear indicator as the adult Sonicare heads do, so you do not see when you ought to change heads. In my experience, I usually got a lot of extra use out of the brush heads even when the wear indicator was showing, so I am not sure how much use this feature would be for the kids set, as most parents would probably not run right out and get a new $20 brush head the moment the wear indicator showed anyway. Also, the app tracks usage time and is supposed to remind you to get a new brush head as appropriate. I have not seen this feature yet (having used the set for less than 90 days) but I have no doubt that it will function as indicated.

The app is a tad persistent and prolific in its reminders of missed brushings and other events, but this is part of the supervisory aspect of the kids set, and you can modify type of notifications to some extent.

As mentioned, the Sonicare for Kids is not cheap, and the replacement heads are also expensive. I believe the brush by itself is worth the elevated price, and the useful and well done BT feature and app add value. Even if your child is not yet brushing on their own, this combination of kid friendly features and the interesting and engaging app will get them on the right dental path and make brushing more productive and less of a chore for both them and you.uent droppings, so if your kid is Mr./Ms Butterfingers or likes to slam things really hard against hard surfaces, you may want to hold off a bit on this purchase.

As mentioned, the Sonicare for Kids is not cheap, and the replacement heads are also expensive. column6: Natural Republic Aloe Vera Gel, 300ml, 10.56 Fluid Ounce
column13: It's best to buy it in person and I'm pretty sure ...
column14:
I bought this tub from a Nature Republic store near my area. It's actually cheaper to buy this in person instead of online because I got mine for $6. I've read online about a fake Nature Republic Aloe Vera Gel, and they've warned their costumers about this problem as well. It's best to buy it in person and I'm pretty sure there are other Nature Republic stores in the states.

Anyway, this lovely green tub of goodness is HUGE. They say that this is a multipurpose gel that can be used for your hair and nails, a make up base, moisturizer, and much more which is probably why the tub is big. Seriously, $6 for this? Not a bad deal!

I mainly use this as a summer moisturizer and to set my skin care products. My skin is oily and because summer is still here, it's a huge problem for my face. This gel has the perfect, watery consistency that not only absorbs quickly, but it also feels cool and refreshing. It does have a sticky residue after applying, but it doesn't last forever because it's quickly absorbed. It also doesn't leave my face feeling oily or greasy like cream/lotion base moisturizers. I probably wouldn't recommend using this gel as a solo winter moisturizer because it's very watery... But who knows, maybe it might work (I'll update this review when cold season is here). The gel smells like a fresh, clean scent so for those who aren't fond of scented skin products this might not make you happy. Because all of the product is in a tub, I suggest using a little spatula to scoop it out. Or find a pump bottle that is clean and scoop the gel in there for easier dispense. I've been using this for only 2 days and it helps soothe those pesky red pimple bumps. My face doesn't produce a lot of oil ever since I've used this product, so it's a plus as well. As for acne, I haven't seen any improvements yet... But I'll continue using and see if there are any results for it.

column6: Dove Men+Care Body Wash, Aqua Impact 18 oz
column14:
For some reason this Dove Men + Care Body Wash, Extra Fresh, it seems to be somewhat stronger in scent than the same product in soap form.

I tried using some on my hands to test it out, which several hours later I can still smell the scent, tho of course it's not as strong as when I first washed my hands. For that reason, I don't find this product suitable for me to wash my entire body. I think it would cause some problems with my asthma, which strong scents sometimes set it off.

I also didn't feel the cooling properties that this body wash is supposed to have. It did make my hands feel clean and not dry, so this body wash is moisturizing and not drying. How much moisture this adds to your skin I cannot say.

So, I think I will just keep this body wash on my bathroom sink and use it to wash my hands. I like the pump, which would make it easier to use in the shower. I think all large bottles should be required to have a pump like this product does. No one needs to be holding a heavy bottle in your shower where it can be slippery.

If you love a stronger scent you may love this product!

column6: InFresh All-Natural Bad Breath Cure - Chewable tablets for instant inside-out freshness. Our patented herbal, formula contains parsley, mint, & deodorizing herbs. 30-day supply, 90 tablets mint flavor
column14:
This product works! Many people know me as breath obsessed. I hate raw onions and garlic primarily due to the effect it has on my breath. I used to avoid eating even salad dressing at work because I couldn't stand the lingering taste in my mouth. InFresh does the trick. I swallow 3 tabs after eating an offending food and not only does my breath seem to freshen but the taste in my mouth seems to go away. It kind of neutralizes everything from the inside out. Can it do battle against garlic? Mostly, although if you do what I did and eat half a head of roasted garlic, don't expect it to work a miracle. It does work on morning breath caused by sour stomach.

It's expensive and I seem to go through 1 bottle very quickly but it's the only product i have found that works this well.

One warning. The instructions say you can chew the pill. I tried it once and it tasted pretty unappetizing. So of course I had to offer one to a friend who immediately developed a repulsed look on her face and proceeded to get green bits of InFresh lodged in her teeth. Quite a funny incident but other than for laughs, I recommend swallowing the pills one at a time.

column6: No Lift Fung-Off Liquid Nail Conditioner
column14:
While I normally prefer natural, alternative treatments (in this case, tea tree oil, oil of oregano, etc.) I have to admit that this time, they weren't helping. The nail would grow but the location of the problem just above the half-moon at the base of my big toe wouldn't change. Even after a diligent 6 months! I then tried a couple off-the-shelf fungus treatments from the drugstore. It was clear they also did nothing. So... I did some research and this seemed the best bet (it had the best reviews elsewhere). I couldn't find it anywhere, until finding it available on Amazon!

Lo and behold, it started working right away. I continued applications per instructions, but from then on, it was just a matter of waiting until the toenail grew out. (And yes, that takes time. But it was "fun" seeing the "bad" section of the toenail growing out, thus I knew things were progressing well, until the problem was all gone.) The stuff is not going to "uncolor" a discolored toenail, but that's not its job. The point is that it kept the healthy, normal colored nail from becoming infected while the bad/discolored section grew out. Success! For that, when nothing else worked, and for doing what it said it would, it gets five stars from me.

column6: L'Oreal Paris Youth Code Skin Illuminator SPF 20, Tinted All-in-1 Facial Mo
column14:
I'm always looking for an instant miracle in a tube or a bottle. That's why I am almost always disappointed and often broke because a promised miracle is always pricier than one basic promise.
This product is visually white with small specs of tint. It is a moisturizer, sunscreen, and sort of foundation. I'm not a foundation user mostly because I don't like laying on a product that often runs in hot weather when I sweat. However, I do like light non-greasy moisturizers and I always use a sunscreen.
The moisturizer component is o.k., but frankly the cream I have been using as a moisturizer is lighter and far better. As for sunscreen, normally all need to be reapplied every two hours. As for the tint/foundation, this is plain strange. There are little micro particles of tint that need to be blended in the creamy white base. If you are adept at blending color this may work until you have to reapply every two hours. However, there is also an issue with the tint. It is light. I am a blonde with fair skin so this will work for me unless I have managed to get a slight tan.
As it stands this does three things, yet it doesn't do anything particularly well. The moisturizer isn't the best, the sunscreen is just o.k., and the tint is easily forgettable because it isn't easy to work with and won't work with a lot of skin tones.

column6: Lipogaine for Men, Premium Minoxidil Hair Loss/ Hair Regrowth Stimulting Solution, 3 Month Supply
column14:
I've used a couple different minoxidil products since I started losing my hair several years ago, and none have really amounted to anything promising. Although, in my earlier attempts, I don't think I used the products consistently enough. Since I decided to just stick it out with Lipogaine about 6 months ago, my usage has been more consistent (almost always twice a day). There was a period of time after four months of usage that I was losing a lesser amount of hair. At first, I would usually have about 10 or more hairs on my finger after I applied the product. After about four months though, I'd only see maybe five or less. However, now I seem to be having more like 10 again. I haven't gone through the shedding phase that's supposed to precede the regrowth phase, where the hair stops falling out and new ones supposedly grow in stronger.

As far as side effects are concerned, the itchy scalp is very minor for me. In fact, I only really noticed it very early on and then it pretty much went away. The only other side effect for me is flakes. I guess it's from when the product dries up on the scalp. I can really notice by just putting a comb through my hair; almost always a couple flakes turn up. Yet even those are fewer now than they used to be.

Ultimately, I'm not optimistic that Lipogaine is going to work for me. As of now, I'd say it's a product that hasn't done for me what it's claimed to do for others, but I'll play the waiting game in hopes that it just takes more time given that the side effects are very tolerable.

As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!
* Fragrance: Witch hazel
* Feel during application: Cushioned, slippery, but wet. It's a water-clear thin gel.
* Feel after absorption: Moist; on my non-oily arm there is some resistance when you move your hand across it but not so much that I would call it a film. On my oily face, it's somewhat sticky.
* Is it best for a certain skin type?: Dry and normal skin. No objections on the part of my oily, sensitive skin although I prefer something a little less shiny and sticky. I have sensitive skin and this actually soothed it in the wake of a product I tested that was somewhat irritating.
* Is it tested on animals?: No.
* Packaging: 1oz plastic bottle with pump top.
* Immediate cosmetic effects: Skin is shinier and there is a slight tightening effect.
* Potential long-term effectiveness:* With an avalanche of peptides and amino acids, hyaluronic acid, vitamin E, and extracts of horsetail, geranium, and dandelion, this serum has an excellent lineup of active ingredients to effectively increase collagen production, moisten, and increase skin elasticity.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

As a product tester I received this free or virtually so for evaluation and review. This does NOT mean this is a fake review. I was not paid for my review, or given any incentive or reward for a positive review. If you don't believe me, click my profile and scroll down to see the poor reviews I've given bad products. My job is to give an honest opinion, not help the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.l down to see the poor reviews I've given bad products. column14: I bought this from Amazon due to all the very positive reviews. column6: Majestic Pure Retinol Cream, Multipurpose Anti Aging Retinol Face Cream & Eye Cream Reduces the Appearances of Wrinkles, Stretch Marks & Redness - 1.7 fl. oz.
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

* Fragrance: Lotiony, slightly herbal.
* Feel during application: This is a very thick white cream. It feels smooth and rich going on.
* Feel after absorption: Moisturized and soft. You can feel something there, but it's more pleasing than annoying because it feels like it's moisturizing.
* Is it best for a certain skin type?: Dry to normal skin, because this is a rich moisturizer. A tad too oily for my oily facial skin.
* Is it tested on animals?: No indication.
* Packaging: .5oz plastic container with pump top. Pump is easy to control.
* Immediate cosmetic effects: Skin looks brighter, and moist.
* Potential long-term effectiveness:* With retinol, vitamins E and B5, shea butter, and propolis, this is a good moisturizer with the positive effects of retinol. You can get formulas with far more active ingredients in one product, but if you need moisture and want to add retinol to your regimen without any other complications, this is a good choice.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

The item itself is ok. I would rate it 3.5 to 4 out of 5 I will be using these as a head scratchers after my friends help me make my new dreadlocks this weekend. The ends are fairly blunt [not rounded] which provides a good scratch but Ive noticed you cant do this all willy-nilly. Once you get it started, you can scratch with a little more ease but you have to pay attention to your stroke otherwise your might catch a few hairs off-guard. Trust me, it will lose and you dont want a big bald spot. I dont think the painted tips really do any good considering the tips shape [Maybe the little drip of paint on the bottom was supposed to help create a "rounded effect"] There is but a sparse layer of paint (I think this is mostly for looks). This is my first metal pick of this sort so I dont have much of a comparison otherwise.

Otherwise,its a nice narrow pick [good eradicating any itch] without being to wide to get caught on everything else and its mom. Order the 4 pack for the value. Its a few bucks more and shipping is about the same. Get one for the car, bathroom, work....

column6: PRI Dermarestore - The #1 Clinically Proven Stretch Mark and Scar Treatment - 4oz Cream
column13: Get rid of those annoying marks
column14:
After having more than one child, I have plenty of stretch marks left behind on my belly and a few other places like my sides where it stretched on my basket ball belly with each child. After a while, most of the stretch marks have at least faded to a white color, they are certainly still visible. I decided to give this treatment a go, but I was a little worried I could not find a list of ingredients before I purchased. While I normally like to go all natural, this has quite the list of ingredients. There are a lot of natural things like aloe, but overall I could not pronounce most of the items and had to look them up. Since it's not a long term treatment, I still decided to give it a go. It seems fine so far, my skin isn't bothered and it seems to be helping. My skin looks better in general and the stretch marks seem to be fading. My daughter had stitches a while back and I will be trying this on her scar as well.

column13: An Up and Coming Skin Care Brand that's Effective!
column14:
This is my first time using a Retseliney skin care product, and I must say I am very impressed. I am currently using their Peptide Complex Serum along with their Anti-Blemish line moisturizer, and have seen results in a short time.

All the ingredients in this peptide complex serum are organic and completely natural and contain no synthetics, parabens, alcohol, GMO‚Äôs, or sulfates. Instead, it contains helpful ingredients such as Jojoba Oil, Aloe Vera, Vitamin E, Hyaluronic Acid, and various other natural ingredients that improve the condition of your skin and pores. I have sensitive combination skin that is plagued by eczema in some places but was still able to use this serum with zero issues or problems.

After the second use, I‚Äôve already noticed that my skin felt more tightened. Several days later, I noticed some of my blemishes have faded, and my pores seem to be less visible. I am highly pleased by these results in the duration that I‚Äôve used this serum, and I look forward to trying more of their products.

The formula is light weight and not sticky. Application is easy and the serum absorbs into my skin relatively quickly. There is no unpleasant odor it and does not have any problems with the makeup I put over it after the moisturizer.

Great product. This is a brand I will continue to follow closely. A sample of this peptide complex serum was provided for testing and review.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I was lucky enough to receive a free sample of Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing & Whitening System through Bzz Agent to try. I've tried many whitening products before and with the exception of whitening tooth pastes, most whitening products make my teeth unbearably sensitive. I was excited to try this product since it seemed like it would be a stronger and more effective paste treatment and I was hopeful I could tolerate it.

The good news is I don't have any sensitivity after using this product daily for over three weeks. At the same time I haven't noticed my teeth looking much whiter, so I'm not sure just how effective this system has been for me. So far I'm seeing about the same results I get from a regular whitening toothpaste. It's for that reason I'm unsure if I would recommend this product. If the results are about the same as just brushing with a normal whitening tooth past then there's no reason to use a two step system. I'm also not overly fond of the texture of the toothpaste.

column13: For me I really loved this product
column14: For me I really loved this product.  My beautician recommended Obagi Nu Derm because she noticed my adult cystic acne problems.  I told her that I had tried all sorts of things over the counter and prescription with no real results.  I was tired of taking the Minocycline pills because they really upset my stomach but they did work.  I tried the acne system first when I was researching on Amazon back in April.  The acne system worked great!!!  It definitely dried my skin out around my lip area and made my forehead a little shiny.  The difference was night and day.  Afterwards, I went to the Nu Derm as originally suggested by my beautician...I didn't really like it but it worked wonders for her.  That may have been because my acne was more cystic.  It was just ok I needed the stronger acne version.  The lotion was gritty and my acne started reappearing a little.  Now, five months later, I have switched back to the new formula therapeutic Acne system and I am back on track.  The new formula doesn't dry my skin as much.  I can literally count on one hand how many pimples/cystic acne areas I have had in the last 5 months.  It definitely smells like medicine....but for me that was minor and it was totally worth it!!!!  So definitely give it a try!!! My skin is clear and 500% more even.  I have a little ways to go to get my skin back even 1 million percent but everyone notices how clear and bright my skin is looking.  It makes me look younger too.  Cystic Acne is normally hormonal or stress related.  With that being said, its a long shot but this Acne system was phenomenal for me!!!! I will continue using it and recommending it!!!!

column6: L'oreal Paris Voluminous Miss Manga Mascara
column14:
I am giving this mascara a 3 star rating for the following reasons. 1) I prefer a dryer mascara. This one is a bit wet and with my short lashes a wetter formula has trouble sticking a building to them. 2) it has too many chemicals. My dream is to find a natural mascara that works. The closest I have come is Tarte Gifted Mascara. 3) The bendy wand is just a gimmick and is see no real benefit to it. 4) It's clumpy with more than one coat. I tried to put on several coats to build up my short lashes and I just got clumpy spiky lashes.
Now for the things I liked about the mascara. 1) I liked the brush. I like an old school fat bristly brush. Not these new rubber things with tiny spikes on the end. Those kind don't work for my lashes and I won't purchase a mascara with a rubber brush end again. This mascara had a bristle type brush with a narrower end that I liked. 2) it's a great black color. Some black mascara I put on and they never seem to tint the lashes dark and I have to keep trying to coat my lashes to get the dark color to show up and make a difference on my lashes. You do notice the dark color from one coat of mascara with this formula. 3) The price is really reasonable. I am willing to take a chance on a new mascara if it's reasonably priced. I have spent much more ( hello, Perversion mascara) and had poorer results than with this mascara. I am never happy to spend a lot of money and get a really wet sloppy mascara that seems to coat everything but my lashes.
Overall, if you have naturally longer thicker lashes I think you will be pleased with this formula. For somebody with thin, short, straight ones, it won't work as well.

column13: Need to follow your \WEN\" directions- not the ones listed on the bottle!!"
column14: I was a dedicated wen girl for the longest time- I have a lot of hair, but it's very fine and pretty long. This product is just as good as Wen- and living in the desert, that little mint tingle is pretty nice. NOTE TO THOSE OF YOU GIVING THE BAD REVIEWS FOR THIS PRODUCT:: do NOT follow the instructions on the bottle- remember your WEN instructions!! Clean the roots on the crown and the back underneath and the sides of your head- rub it in there- then add some more water and rub in more- the product feels like it 'doubles' in volume!! Then rinse some of that though the rest of your hair- add just a pump more for the length- comb it through - leave it in while you shower- rinse it out & put a little bit on your ends & don't wash out. - hopefully you'll change your mind- as for that 6-8 pump thing- use your judgement. I never have used that much and my hair stays clean for 3-4 days.  I can't say enough about this product - I'm so happy to have stumbled across it here for THAT price!!

column13: Not yet seeing the results I hoped for.
column14:
I was approached by two different brands to receive their eyelash growth products at a discount in exchange for my honest review, so I thought it was the perfect opportunity to compare the products and see if either truly did what they claim to do!

The product comes in a little silver tube, with a paintbrush-type applicator. The serum is a yellowish clear liquid that applies quite easily. It was interesting that you actually apply the serum to your lash line rather to the lashes, themselves. I quickly found out that a little goes a long way! Using too much serum makes it drip down into your eye, which left it with an unpleasant and gunky feeling.

I applied this product every day for one week to compare pictures, which I've attached. In my photos, the top eye is my "Before", and the bottom eye is my "After 1 Week". I have to say, I really don't see any difference in my "Afters". Compared to other products of the same type, this Eyelash Growth Serum is more expensive and I have yet to see any growth, even though they claim results after only 1 week. I will continue using this serum and hope for some results - but as of right now, I cannot recommend this product. :(

column6: Redken Shades EQ 9V Platinum Ice 2 oz
column14: This shade has a violet base with no background color, which means it's pure violet with no strange off tones.  It neutralizes golden tones and depending on how long you leave it on, it can result in a subtle change or a more dramatic ashy tone.  If left on too long, it can turn hair purple so be careful with the timing.  I only leave it on for two minutes, any more than that and I lose all the lovely golden tones.  I only want to tone down the gold not lose it completely, plus my hair absorbs ash really fast and any longer than that and I would lose all the brightness in my blond.  The timing with Shades EQ is quite tricky so a strand test is highly recommended.  It does leave hair soft and glossy with no damage whatsoever.  It lasts anywhere from 15-20 shampoos depending on how long you leave it on but it will last much longer if you use a sulfate free shampoo.  It will cover up to 25% gray and there are myriad shades that can enhance your natural color or add warm or cool tones.  You can get a color chart on Pinterest if you want to see the full shade range.  I've been using Shades EQ for 6 months and really like it.  I get compliments on my color all the time.  It delivers salon worthy results because it's a salon product.  The color is translucent and super shiny never matte and flat like drugstore color or the junk Sally's sells.  Shades EQ is a deposit only formula so it cannot lighten but it's super sheer and conditioning and leaves hair looking and feeling healthy.  It's an amazing product.  I highly recommend it.possible, both of which keep my color fresh and bright longer.  If you want to tone down excessive gold but don't want an ashy result, then use this formula.  My now beautifully neutral blond hair absolutely loves this stuff!  I highly recommend Shades EQ and this formula in particular.

column6: LiceLogic Natural Enzyme Based Lice Repel Conditioning Shampoo, 8 oz
column13: Nice smell and decent shampoo. Good for lice prevention!
column14:
I have two kids headed into school next month and I wanted to be prepared in case there was a lice outbreak, which in public school there always seems to be. I have been lucky so far and though I've worked in places where the kids had lice, never manged to get them myself. My two older daughter who are school age both have long hair and I would hate to have to cut it.

This shampoo just made since so start using so that the prevention is there. Better to be prepared ahead of time, than to wish I had and them end up getting lice! The shampoo itself is very thin. It is super clear in color so it's hard to determine how much you are pouring out at a time. After a few uses you get used to it and it is a lot easier to only pour small amounts at a time. It does seem to lather well in their hair though, and I've found that a little bit goes a long way!

I got the lavender one, and the smell is very nice. After it is washed out it does leave an odd wet hair smell, but once the hair dries it seems to go away. Considering this is a lice prevention shampoo, it really didn't surprise me about the smell.

Overall I am impressed with this lice repeling shampoo. I can't say for sure if it works to keep lice away yet, but I'd rather be use it and never know than wish I had and them end up with lice!

I would recommend this LiceLogic Repel Shampoo to anyone with kids looking for a safe solution to hopefully keeping the lice away!

Sodium hydroxide is just a fancy word for lye which we all know is the old fashioned way to make soap by running rainwater through wood ash. So this really is an all natural soap. The presentation of the soap is nice and it would be perfect for a gift basket for the health conscious person in your life. The color is all natural because there is no dyes. Now as for use. column6: BRIOTECH Topical Skin Spray - A Perfect, All Natural Cosmetic Solution
column14:
After turning 40, my skin decided to make me pay for having flawless skin as a teenager and I was diagnosed with adult onset acne. I've tried everything from proven "as seen on TV" and OTC topical products as well as prescription regiments suggested by my dermatologist. My acne would leave dark spots as they healed. Nothing I used helped alleviate the hyperpigmentation.

Earlier this summer, I had a reaction to the moisturizer with SPF that I have been using for the past two years. My whole face was red, splotchy and highly irritated. Washing it with my gentle cleanser made it sting. Everything I put on my face irritated the skin, including the topical antibiotic prescribed by my dermatologist. Through a friend, I was introduced to literature on Briotech. I will admit I was skeptical because the instructions are, well, too simple: "Spray...daily on affected area"---but it IS that simple. Since Day 1 of its arrival, I've used it 2-3 times a day: once after washing my face in the morning before makeup, midday as a pick-me-up, and once before going to bed. It doesn't feel like anything other than misting your face with water. Within two days my irritated skin recovered---no more itchiness and redness. I've used it for almost a month and I haven't had any breakouts and the hyperpigmentation from my scars is noticeably reduced.

In addition to my acne, I developed a hypersensitivity to sunlight exposure. Even after applying sunscreen, after exposure, I will have raised areas of itchy, irritated and erythemic skin. I would have to take antihistamines and/or antibiotics to help heal my skin, which would take up to two weeks. I went to the beach a couple of weeks ago and broke out in a few patches. I decided to try Briotech on them. Although I was still itchy, the redness and irritation dissipated considerably by the next morning. Also worked great on the kids' sunburns because it doesn't sting when applied.

I carry it with me everywhere. I just recently started spritzing down my yoga mats with it after class. It's not a harsh chemical so it won't break down the material like the antibacterial sprays and wipes at the gym. I'm quite impressed with this product and will definitely keep purchasing it. Thank you!

column6: Vitamin C Serum by Defy Naturals - 20% Clinical Strength Potency - Organic Vitamin C / Hyaluronic Acid / Amino Complex - ANTI AGING Formula Lets You Defy Your Age Everyday! Eliminate Lines, Wrinkles, Aging Skin and Crows Feet. No Fillers or Additives. 100% Satisfaction Guarantee! (Original Organic, 1 Oz)
column14:
So, I was sent this product to review and I did not like it. Partly, because I did not see any results. I don't have any wrinkles to fight, but I do have spots and would have liked to see some brightening. I gave this serum a go for 2 weeks and I might have stuck with it longer to give it a chance, except I hated using it. The label says it'll take 3-5 minutes to dry, but after 5 minutes, it still felt not absorbed. I even tried just using one drop of it and still had the same issue. It just left my face feeling sticky and did not dry down to a smooth texture, even though I applied it to damp skin, as instructed. There's no fragrance added, but I didn't like the scent. I can't really describe it, but I would have preferred if it was more refreshing.

For a brand that has "naturals" in its name, the ingredients aren't super natural. There's propylene glycol and phenoxyethanol, which I would prefer to avoid. It's my fault for not noticing beforehand, but I do feel a little betrayed by its use of the words "natural" and "organic" in its marketing.

The redeeming factors would be that this serum is vegan, the packaging is nice and easy to use, and the product is relatively affordable for a serum. Maybe it would suit someone with more dry or mature skin than me, but it did not work out with me.

*Item sent free for review*

column14: I so wanted to love this product. This was the closest I had ever gotten to finding a perfect match for my super pale skin tone. I used a silicone primer, a non-silicone primer, and no primer. I moisturized a lot or a little, and used setting powder or no setting powder. I find that this Dove Men+Care styling paste is awfully similar to the Suave Professionals Men's styling paste that I have been using in terms of both the texture and performance. Both work just as great for me but I'll have to give it to Suave for the much cheaper price. Another thing is that the Dove product has caffeine added to it, which is reportedly a possible hair growth stimulant. With my usual shampoo on day 2 my hair is getting limp and a bit oily as the day wears on, day 3 is completely greasy hair and I wash again. With this shampoo I did not make it to the end of day 1 (the day I washed my hair) without being too greasy. I avoided washing on day 2 for the purposes of testing the shampoo by using copious amounts of dry shampoo (I love Klorane). I then used this shampoo again exactly as instructed thinking that I would give it another try. Same results... oily and gross by the end of the same day I washed it. I have not used it again.

column6: Burt's Bees Beeswax Bounty Holiday Gift Set, 4 Lip Balms in Gift Box, Assorted Flavors
column14:
We live in a dry climate and use a lot of lip balm.

This goes on smoothly and holds together, even in warm environments.

However, I have two problems with it: it's not incredibly moisturizing, and it has a number of questionable ingredients.

If you live in a less dry climate, the level of moisture might not be as much of an issue. I find that unless I reapply constantly, my lips feel just as dry as before I used it.

But the larger issue is that it contains a number of seed oils, including soybean oil, and we prefer something that's made of better ingredients, like coconut oil and beeswax (this includes these ingredients, but also a number of less healthy oils - even canola oil?!?!).

If you are less picky about ingredients and don't live in a very arid climate, you may have better luck.

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column13: It's here! It's clear! It's not that special!
column14:
I received a free sample of this product from Secret in order to test it out, so for a few weeks I used my normal deodorant on one armpit, and the Outlast Clear Gel on the other to get a good comparison. Final conclusion: It's just ok. Not bad, but not the greatest thing ever to happen to my armpits.

I generally don't like gel deodorants...something about putting a gooey liquid in my armpit is less than appealing. As gels go though, this does dry relatively quickly and is only a little sticky. The product is clear and leaves no white marks, but I've never had any problems with white marks myself, and definitely not any issues with clumping (eew!). If white marks are a concern for you, this may be a product worth trying out.

The odor protection continues to be inconsistent, but so does my current deodorant. The most significant thing for me was the scent of the product. The other versions of Secret Clear Gel have a very clear label indicating the scent. The fact that the Completely Clean version doesn't mention scent at all is somewhat misleading, and I assumed that it would be relatively unscented. If you don't want a noticeable smell coming from your armpits throughout the day, be sure to get the version that says "unscented", not Completely Clean. All in all, Secret Outlast doesn't seem to be any better than my usual brand, but it's not any worse either. It may be worth a shot if you have issues with white marks!

column6: Ultra Beard Conditioner 8oz and Wild Berry Shampoo 8oz by Beardsley
column13: Save some dough, and just use regular shampoo/conditioner
column14:
I have a thick, ginger beard and have been looking for something to get it under control. I've been using my wife's shampoo and conditioner, and just thought I'd try picking up something intended specifically for beards. I wash my beard every morning. Can't stand not too.

Do these products work? Yeah. I guess so. But, do they work better than regular shampoo and conditioner, and are they worth the money? I don't think so. The shampoo gets my beard pretty clean, although I don't think it's as effective as my wife's shampoo. The conditioner is pretty good, too, but again, not as good as my wife's Aussie 3 Minute miracle.

I've used up both bottles now, and won't be spending the money again. Overall, if you're using soap, this is a step up. But there is way cheaper stuff that does a better job cleaning and conditioning my beard.

As for the taste, does any guy really care? I get that it's supposed to taste like wild berries, but come on. I'm half asleep in the shower, anyway, and don't typically drink the shampoo.

Ultimately, I'll use this stuff up, but will probably just go back to using whatever my wife buys for herself.

Does it taste good? Really, who cares?

column6: Splat Rebellious Colors Hair Coloring Kit Jet Black
column14: I dye my naturally blonde hair black. The first time I did it, I used a permanent box dye that I had used before, so I knew it would work well. However, I wanted to try a slightly less damaging dye that would also last a decent amount of time without fading, so I tried this stuff. The first thing I noticed was the smell. Because this is semi-permanent, it doesn't have that tell-tale peroxide or ammonia smell that many permanent dyes have. Rather, this smelled like a slightly stronger, more artificial aloe vera scent. Not unpleasant, though. I was quite pleased with the result after using it on my head. It did very well to cover my dark blonde roots, but also refreshed the previous black color (which had faded to a very dark brown in some areas), bringing it back to a pure jet black. My hair felt pretty good afterward, too, still nice and soft. I'll most likely be using this from now on for my roots, provided that the color lasts long enough without lots of fading.

column6: Natural Sunscreen SPF 30 by Mercola - 8 ounces
column14: Bought this product because of the ingredients listed above: "Inactive Ingredients: Deionized Water, Sunflower Oil, Lecithin, Coconut Oil, Glycerine, Xanthan Gum, Green Tea Extract, Jojoba Oil, Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E), Retinyl Palmitate (Vitamin A), Shea Butter, Eucalyptus Oil. Active Ingredients: Titanium Dioxide, Zinc Oxide." When I received it, I noticed completely different ingredients listed on the back of the bottle (in the tinest print I've ever seen... almost as if they didn't want you to see what's really in it) There was no green tea extract, no titanium dioxide, however there is a great deal of other stuff I'd prefer not to have in my sunscreen! It also has a chemical smell to it and gave me a headache. Definitely not something I want to slather on my skin every day. Returned! Here are the actual ingredients: Zinc Oxide 20%, Aqua, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice, Helanthus Annuus(Sunflower) Seed Oil, Lecithin, Cetearyl Alcohol, Cetearyl Glucoside, Cetearyl Olivate, Sorbitan Olivate, Glycerin, Simmonds Chinensia(Jojoba) Seed Oil, Butyrospermum Parkii(Shea) Butter, Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract, Cocos Nucifera(Coconut) Oil, Glucurolactone, Potassium Sorbate, Xanthan Gum, Punica Granalum Fruit Extract, Tocopherol, Rubus Idaeus(Raspberry) Seed Oil, Astaxanthain Eucalyptus Globulus Leaf Oil. I specifically didn't like seeing that there is Lecithin or Potassium Sorbate in this sunscreen. In my opinion, the fewer ingredients the better. Since then I have discovered ThinkBaby/ThinkSport sunscreen and am very happy so far.

column6: BMC 10pc Hard Rubber Tipped Plastic Handle Nail Art Tool Cuticle Pusher Cleaner
column14:
UPDATE: I have quite a lot of nail products including plenty of cuticle pushers and other similar products and these ones are STILL my favourite. They've lasted quite a while and I've only had the white tips fall off when I'm pressing pretty hard with slippery cuticle oils. I have been using them daily for over a year and I don't plan to switch brands if I don't have to.

These are fantastic little cuticle pushers! I was firm on orange sticks only until I got my hands on a soft rubber Jamberry pusher that changed everything. When it eventually wore out, I found these BMC pushers - a great price for a pack of 10 - and I now use these daily when pushing back my cuticles and applying cuticle oil. At 3 & 3/4 inches long, they're somewhat short but a pretty reasonable and comfortable length. The rubber isn't all that "hard" like the title says - they're not quite as squishy as my old Jamberry pusher but nearly so, which makes them gentle and easy to use. The white tips come off of the sticks when they start to wear out (and when worn out and slippery from oils), but some rubber cement (or tape?) might extend the life of them... but they're already a fantastic bang for your buck.

column6: Natural Eczema & Psoriasis Treatment - Organic Hemp Seed Healing Balm Offers Relief From Dry & Cracked Skin, Eczema, Psoriasis, Dermatitis, Rosacea & All Common Skin Conditions, Best Natural Moisturizer & Hand Cream - 100% Natural, Vegan, Chemical & Fragrance Free - 30 Day Guarantee
column13: Soothes the Itch and Scaliness of Psoriasis Immediately
column14: SO has a terrible case of psoriasis on his hands.  He‚Äôs tried all manner of lotions, those with lactic acid and salycilc acid and coconut oil, but he says they don‚Äôt do much... except burn, in most cases.  So when I found this super emollient balm with a new potential secret ingredient (hemp seed oil), I had to get it for him.    Upon the first application, the balm soothed the itch and smoothed out the scaliness on SO's hands.  And no burning!  After three days of two applications a day, the redness also diminished some.  He still has a few scabs... but that means they're healing; those scabs are no longer raw-looking, open sores.  Hooray!  If we had a complaint, it would be the size of the container.  SO tends to gob it on.  I'll be surprised if 4 ounces lasts him more than a couple weeks.  That said... it's helping, and he may use less when his skin is no longer so angry and it's just for maintenance.  Plus, it's the first product he's tried that works so well he puts it on without me having to remind him.  And the first product he's said he would re-buy.  We definitely will.  He's been wearing fingerless gloves for the past few years to hide the psoriasis.  With this, he might actually, finally, take them off.  Also, be aware that the formula contains rosemary and almond old.  Rosemary is a known skin irritant that can cause contact dermatitis for some people.  It doesn't seem to be hurting SO, however, and I don‚Äôt smell any rosemary in the product; in fact, I can‚Äôt smell the product at all unless I stick my nose in the can.  It has a pleasant nutty smell.  That said, and provided you‚Äôre not allergic to almonds or any of the other natural ingredients, this is otherwise a very good ingredients list, lots of emollients and soothers.  And the "best by" date is 4 months from when I received it, which is pretty good for organics and for the size of the balm package (4 ozs).  UPDATE:  SO's been using this product for a while now, in conjunction withanother psoriasis/eczema herbal ointment by Beauteous Earth.  He says this hemp balm is the best product he's found so far at relieving the itchiness, and doing so immediately.  But it's not the best product for relieving the redness.  When the itchiness is under control, he prefer the Beauteous Earth product for relieving the redness and making the skin look more normal.  Also, the product seems to have consistency issues.  We've since reordered and the new can has little white balls in it.  They melt on the skin, so I suspect the product is still fine, and SO says it still relieves the itch.  But he doesn't like the feel of the balls, and he reaches for the can less often because of it.  I see that other reviewers have mentioned this quality control issue, too, so... hopefully the company will straighten it out, because the product, when in top form, is otherwise excellent.    *The manufacturer gave me a discounted sample for evaluation so that I could give you this honest review.

column13: Plant Therapy is the among the best
column14:
I bought this because I was looking for an addiontioal essential oil carrier and after research found that this is the best one for what I needed. I have family members that have eczema and i have made them a balm type lotion with essential oils that helps reduce the flair ups and the severity and was looking for an oil that would be more nourishing to the skin and so I bought this as it is all of the thing I was looking for.

Evening primrose oil is the oil from the seed of the evening primrose plant. Evening primrose oil is used for skin disorders such as eczema, psoriasis, and acne. It is also used for rheumatoid arthritis, weak bones (osteoporosis), Raynaud‚Äôs syndrome, multiple sclerosis (MS), Sjogren‚Äôs syndrome, cancer, high cholesterol, heart disease, a movement disorder in children called dyspraxia and leg pain due to blocked blood vessels (intermittent claudication) and many more and thats just the oil alone and by its self.

The scent is not to strong but it can take some getting used to. It is also VERY oily when applied to the skin which also makes it a great massage oil because it doesnt soak right into the skin. I have used many brands for essential oils but I truly do like Plant Therapy and I trust the product I am getting!! The quality is by far the best. I did receive this at a discount for my unbiased review.

column6: Mehron Professional Makeup & Face Painting Student Practice Head
column14:
I was reluctant to purchase with mix of negative reviews regarding staining. With additional reading and tips garnered from different reviewers I made the leap. Here's the tips I used successfully: Sprayed the mannequin I'll call 'Mo' twice with hairspray, allowing to dry between applications. Proceeded with water-based high quality face paint. Admired my work long enough to let it set well enough. Sprayed Mo down with 91% rubbing alcohol that I've placed in a small spray bottle from a Walmart. Wiped the paint off easily with the Mr. Clean Magic Eraser. Rinsed the Eraser and wiped any smears left by moving the paint around the Mo's face. Took no longer than washing a child's face after the a painting, maybe less time because he was so compliant!

column13: Excellent value, recommended by our Teen!
column14:
We got this for review as a part of the vine program. The review is accurate and honest.

Our daughter is almost 14 years old and has curly----very curly hair. She tends to spend a lot of time swimming in the summer months and that leads her hair down a path which makes it hard for her to manage. For regular usage she likes the ability to adjust speeds and heat settings...in other words, less heat regularly and more when styling. The diffuser helps her dry quickly...especially because she has thick curly hair. There is a conditioning ring that is included but time will tell how much that helps....she does use it 2-3 times a week and is only seeing moderate improvement...but it is early to tell.

So far we are pleased with the product and recommend it highly as an excellent value.

column14:
This mask is a great moisturizing treatment if you are struggling with dry, frizzy hair. Twice a week, I have used this instead of my daily conditioner and left it in for a few hours. It was easier to blow dry my hair straight than it usually is. My ends look much smoother. I used this product for a month before posting my review because I wanted to see cumulative results...And I did. This hair mask also smells great...Almost like candy.

As an advocate for animal welfare, I appreciate that this product is cruelty free. If every consumer would buy cruelty free only, it would force companies to use some compassion. As someone who is licensed, I have used the best of the best in beauty/hair products and my standards are pretty high. I can recommend this mask just as much as I could a professional product that would cost 3x's as much.

Thanks for creating such affordable, effective products with compassion in mind.

Talking about materials, these brushes are Eco friendly and are made from synthetic fiber, which I like more than natural hair for many reasons. Brushes are really dense and soft.

You can really feel the quality, because after my daily usage and multiple washes, they didn't start shading and didn't fall apart. I know that this is also the result of my proper care.
If you don't know how to properly take care after your makeup brushes, Mozzetos follow-up emails will give you some tips how to do that, besides, Mozzeto gives a lifetime guaranty for beautybrush makeup brushes, which is really uncommon and also very great!

To sum up, I would like to say that for the price you pay, you get really high quality makeup brushes that will serve you right and you will really feel like a highly valued customer!

I definitely recommend this makeup brush set and for sure this seller!

column6: Sport Sunscreen Lotion - Best For Active Lifestyles - Broad Spectrum (UVA & UVB Ray) SPF 30+ Protection - Water And Sweat Resistant - Contains Vitamin E & B5 - Perfect For Sensitive Skin
column14: I was given the opportunity to try this Sport Sunscreen Lotion through Amazon.  Before I discuss my opinion of this product, I want to tell you a little bit about myself.  I am a red head with a very fair complexion who happens to live in Florida.  I have been careful using various sunscreens throughout my life because I am extremely prone to sunburn.  Even so, a couple of years ago, I was diagnosed with a small in situ melanoma.  Fortunately, the melanoma was removed with little fuss, and it was self-contained.  As a result, I have become even more careful using sunscreen when I go out for any reason.  Since I live near the beach and I love to garden, this occurs quite often.  Over the years I have used many types of sunscreen.  I have struggled with sunscreens coming off when I get in the water and being sticky. I have never been completely happy with any of the sunscreens I have tried in the past.  This all changed when I tried Andre Lorent Ultra Sport Sunscreen SPF 30+.  The packaging proclaims this sunscreen was developed for the ‚Äúextreme sporting lifestyle‚Äù and is water resistant for 80 minutes.  Since I have to be careful when exposing myself to the sun, I appreciated the warning on the box with regards to Sun Protection Measures.  The box suggests individuals should limit time in the sun between 10 AM ‚Äì 2 PM.  This is good advice when living in Florida.  The formula of this sunscreen states it is friendly to individuals with sensitive skin, and it is non-greasy.   I tried this sunscreen this weekend when I went to the beach and again today when I went outside and gardened for a little over an hour.  The product is definitely not sticky, and I was not in any way uncomfortable wearing it.  Furthermore, it did not wash off when I was in the ocean.  I am certain of this because I did not get burned even though I was at the beach for about two hours.  My skin is so fair, I would normally be sunburned within 30 minutes.  I would highly recommend this product.  Not only was the sunscreen excellent, but the service from the company was also outstanding.  The product arrived when scheduled, and the company followed up with an email requesting feedback.  I have used many sunscreens during my life, and this one is the best product I have ever used.

column6: Gillette Fusion ProGlide Manual Men's Razor Blade Refills Mens Razors / Blades
column14:
I always compare new blades to the old standard.

First off - the Proglide blades WILL fit on the old Fusion handle.

But, as one other reviewer pointed out, the new Fusion Proglide handle is better balanced. I feel more comfortable with it when I'm shaving in the shower. It was worth the extra cost to me.

When the original Fusion came out I compared to the Mach3, but couldn't tell much difference. With a 2-day growth, I used a fresh Mach3 blade and a fresh Fusion blade, and they both pulled a little. The only big improvement I could see was the top blade for under-nose trimming.

Now, the Proglide is a different story. I skipped a day shaving and did the same test. The Mach3 pulled like pliers on my chin hair, but the Pro glided right through. I think the thinner blades schtick is more than a marketing line. At least for me it is.

I'd give it 5 stars, but it hasn't done anything magical like make me irresistible to the opposite sex :)

column6: Sea Whip Cucumber Soothing & Hydrating Gel | Detox Gel Mask Enhanced with Hyaluronic Acid, Green Tea, Argan Oil, Botanical Extracts | Cools, Calms, and Heals | Professional Skincare Treatment
column14:
I am sooo pleased with this product! I have somewhat odd skin..it's acne prone, oily, but also gets dry easily, so it's hard for me to find facial products that really work for me. I received my Sea Whip Cucumber Detox Soothing Gel Mask very promptly, and was pleasantly surprised at the amount of product! It also comes in a nice jar that I can totally see myself putting to use once I use up all the gel. (:
I was so excited to receive it that I ran to the bathroom, washed my face and put the mask on right away! I dipped my finger in the jar and once I started applying it, quickly realized I got way to much..oops! A little bit goes a LONG way with this, which is great, that means even more use's! The mask smells great! It almost has a light 'cucumber melon' smell it to it (obviously the cucumber..but also a little fruity) which is one of my favorite scents. It's a clear mask, so you can put this on and leave it on and still answer the door without freaking people out which is an added bonus for me. (;
I waited ten minutes before washing it off (you can leave it on longer, even all night, I just didn't have time!) and it almost felt slimy, which wasn't a bad thing, I just wasn't expecting that texture! The slimy texture was actually a good thing because it was easy to tell when I had washed it all of, I was worried about not knowing when it was off because it's clear.
Once the mask was off, my skin looked and felt amazing! The mask was so refreshing, and my skin felt so soft without being oily. I had a little dry skin that was also gone after the treatment. Plus, almost a week later and NO ACNE!! I'm super excited that I found a facial mask that takes care of all of my skin problems in one!
I'm really looking forward to using the Sea Whip Cucumber Detox Soothing Gel Mask more! I will definitely be doing overnight treatments, as well as using for sunburns and other skin issues! I highly recommend the Sea Whip Cucumber Detox Soothing Gel Mask to all skin types!
I received this product for free to test and review, all opinions are my own! (:skin types!

column13: Not a miracle cure, but as close as you are likely to find.
column14: I've suffered with joint pain for over a decade.  My doctors have given me pain medication that I keep in my cabinet, but I don't want to be drugged all the time.  I've tried a variety of over the counter remedies, from Icy Hot to absorbine Jr.  They tend to only make me stinky, and never go deeper than the skin as far as pain goes.  This Deep Blue rub is a completely different beast.  The cold-heat penetrates deep into the core of your joints, and the pain is eased away without the stench of other over the counter remedies.  It smells, but it smells of mint more than menthol...  Yes, it's pricey.  That's because it contains genuine essential oils in a cream base.  It's a more natural way of healing than drenching your body in chemicals, and instead of covering the pain, it addresses the injury.  My knees haven't felt this good in a decade.  This is no miracle cure, it will take time and care, but this is as close as you are actually going to find.

column6: Dr. Bronner's Pure-Castile Liquid Soap - Peppermint 32oz.
column13: I cannot use any other soap
column14:
Ever since using this soap my skin has been absolutely glorious, no acne, no oil, no unpleasant body odor, less sweating.
The first few weeks actually was terrible. My skin was always dry, my hair alternated between dry and oily. I consider this period to be an adjusting period since your body has to overproduce oil thanks to most soap stripping away significant oil and body flora.
It's important to realize that the microbiome that exists on your skin is part of your healthy body, some bacteria are beneficial to your skin by competing with harmful bacteria and fungus. Dr. Bronner's soap is so good, if I ever use some generic brand of soap, I notice changes on my skin, be it smell, fungus, or excessive body secretions.
You can also use it for like everything in your household. I tried brushing my teeth with the soap once but it tasted like soap (no surprise here), but I can see how it could be useful if you were on the go or camping and wanted to pack light.
Lasts forever if you use sparingly and diluted if needed. I typically purchase a new bottle per academic year and it lasts me through school and early summer.

column6: Maybelline New York Volum' Express The Falsies Push Up Drama Waterproof Mascara
column13: Volume and length, more irritating than other Maybelline mascaras
column14:
Big thumbs up for this mascara's ability to add volume and length without clumping. The brush is new, and it seems to handle both tasks without making a mess of your eyelashes.

I wear a lot of Maybelline's mascaras--usually [[ASIN:B00AQ9S93A Maybelline New York Volume' Express The Rocket Washable Mascara, Blackest Black, 0.3 Fluid Ounce]]. It goes on sale at big box stores and you can find it for around five a tube, meaning replacing it every two to three months isn't like replacing a twenty-five buck tube of department store mascara from the luxe brands. And it works just as well.

This mascara goes on very well, but in five minutes, my eyes were watering. Sad to say, this formula doesn't work for my sensitive eyes, while most of the other mascaras do work for me. It's a shame because the mascara does a very good job of lengthening, adding thickness and holding a curl. It's really great--just, not for uber-sensitive people like me.

I tried the mascara again the next morning. My eyes are less sensitive at the beginning of the day, before I've stared at a screen for 8 hours or worn eye makeup all day. I applied it again on well-washed face and the mascara was not irritating this time. This gives me the impression that for highly sensitive eyes, it could be an issue, but for moderately sensitive, it may be ok.

This mascara does a great job of both lengthing and volumizing. The brush is slim and not hard to use. I would buy this instead of the \\\Rocket\\\\\" version anytime. It's in a pretty tube, as well--reddish and plum metallic with black--very dramatic. Cool shape. It's fun to look at and works quite well. One star off for \\\\\"somewhat irritating\\\\\" and \\\\\"not as volumizing as L'Oreal Voluminous\\\\\" which is the volume standard I use to judge all mascaras."

column13: Chronic Profuse Sweating No Match for Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel
column14:
As a member of BzzAgent, I was given a sample of Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel. I had never felt confident with even the most expensive deodorants or anitperspirants. Chronic sweating has plagued me since adolescence, and even prescription strength deodorants stopped the profuse sweating. With that constant sweating, embarrassment arose because of the pit stains or wet spots in my underarms.

However, since trying Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel, I no longer experience the wet armpits or the constant sweating. Even after doing a nerve-wrecking presentation that would have normally sent me into a sweating frenzy before, I had dry armpits and stayed cool and fresh. The clear gel is great for any shirt, as it leaves no embarrassing residue.

Secret Outlast Completely Clean Clear Gel is a godsend for people with over-active sweat glands. The fresh scent adds to my confidence.

column6: Aussie Spray Hair Gel
column14:
Aussie Aussome Volume Styling Gel -- 7 OUNCES

I wear my hair short and spiky and my problem? My hair is straight as a board and has zero volume. I mean absolutely NO volume and NO lift. My hair is also baby fine which adds to my hair dilemma. I love short hair as I don't have the talent and/or patience to work with my hair and make it look nice. On many people, straight short hair looks great, but not on me.

After I wash my hair I apply AUSSIE AUSSOME VOLUME STYLING GEL. I then apply my make-up and after a bit my hair is ready to be dried. Let me tell you -- this stuff adds ALL DAY volume and style to my hair. After spiking and styling, I am good to go. I love how this product does not weigh down my hair, does not make it stiff. It has an almost non-odor and lasts all day long. I am a school cafeteria manager and must wear a hair net from 6AM till approximately 11AM. When it's hot and you are wearing one of those light-weight white mushroom type foo-foo hair nets? My hair is 'restyled' due to heat. After I remove my hair net, I simply fluff up my hair and I am good to go. Love this stuff.

I stumbled across this product at a local store and bought the only tube left. When shopping at other places, I could not find this. I went back to the store where I purchased my first tube, but no luck. All the stores stock and carry other Aussie products, but not this one. So, I found this on AMAZON in a four pack and at a MUCH lower price!

If you need some shape and style to your otherwise straight hair, this is the product for you. I have never been happier with a styling gel. Thanks AUSSIE for helping to make this old broad look presentable !!

US	44109016	R2MEQ1DZYNUJJR	B00I8F3XPI	207374911	9 KLEANCOLOR FEMME LIPSTICK LS1276 - COLORFUL SET LIP STICK + FREE EARRING by Kleancolor	Beauty	5	3	3	N	Y	Fantastic collection of lipsticks and a great deal!	The only con was a few of the lippies were separated from the bottom and touching the top of the lid. Just turn it right side up and thump it against a table or something and it goes back into place. Seriously, do people not understand that they are ordering a batch of lipstick? Stuff is going to happen. Nothing to complain about though unless you just like to give bad reviews, which soooo many people like to do even if it's just their opinion. A review should be based on fact, not opinion,<br />I don't know what people were talking about saying that the lighter colors don't show up. Treat it more like a balm since they do have a lot of moisturizing additives and put on a few layers, or shizzle, use a primer in your skintone and you'll be good! I have light skin with dark rose colored lips and every color showed up. Though sometimes the shade would be interesting lol I love them though and were exactly what I had in mind and wanted, and honestly, who the &*^% can complain when it's a dollar a tube? Best deal ever. I bought 32 shades because my style varies so much, and I can give the extras and colors I don't wear away to a friend.<br /><br />Also looks great layered or with a gloss over it. I prefer a clear hyper-shimmer gloss, it makes the colors and your lips POP. Great texture with one stroke or three, stays put if you know tricks to keeping your lipstick on without a stain. Use a cream flesh toned or pearl eye primer on your lips and let it dry, then apply lipstick. One neat trick is to buy the Italia Lip/Eyeliners (I have the black and silver sets, 7 & 12 Pc, about a dollar or less per pencil but great quality) when buying any of the Kleancolor lippies and using the matching colors to the lipstick. I'm an Aesthetician, but unless you have no knowledge about makeup or have been living in a cave, you should know this one from normal colors. You carefully line your lips with...let's say the lightest aqua/turquoise liner, or you can use silver (for the pastel aqua-blue lippie) and then shade in your lips with the teal or turquoise AND the white or silver to lighten the base, and blend it with your pinky starting from the outside liner pulling in. I prefer to use white and silver with the teal because it turns out to be a streaky blended look, and once the liner dries and you put the lipstick on, it's a pale aqua with depth and highlights and some glow. Plenty of ways to use this!	2015-08-11
