column13: Love the product....STAY AWAY from Gunthy Renker!!!!!
column14:
I have been using Wen for over a year now. I have very fine, straight hair just past my shoulders. I use a blow dryer and hot rollers regularly. Wen has cut down on the hair loss and breakage, and left my hair in much better condition. I also love changing the scents to go with the seasons.

column6: Double Edge Safety Razor
column13: Great Razor, can't wait to try it on my head.
column14:
I am not a shaving connoisseur in any way, I don't have 14 razors, unicorn haired brushes, etc....I am just an average guy.

Yesterday I received my Edwin Jagger DE safety razor from Amazon. I will say I was a bit disappointed on how small the actual handle is. I know it says 3 inches on the web page but wow the handle is small. Regardless, instead if sending it back I thought I would try it out. I must say I was kind of nervous about using it since I have only ever used the disposable 3/4 blade kind.

Shaving:
The razor has a nice weight to it but once again I find the handle to be too small for my liking. I open the razor and insert a razor blade to begin shaving. As other reviewers have mentioned the blade does stick out the sides of the razor. I am not sure why it is designed this way but I see it as a flaw and potential issue when I get around to shaving my head.

I watched a couple youtube videos on how to shave with a safety razor so I was prepared. I shaved like I normally would but didn't apply the same amount of pressure I would with a disposable. I did not shave 3 or 4 times in different directions like some of the youtube videos suggest. Just quick short strokes (hehehe) like i normally do.

The shave was very close and very smooth. On par or possible better than what I normally get with a disposable. I shave my head 3 times a week so I will give that a shot next. Since there isnt any flex like a disposable I am a bit concerned but we will see. I will try and update this review after shaving my head.

column6: Lipogaine for Men, Premium Minoxidil Hair Loss/ Hair Regrowth Stimulting Solution, 3 Month Supply
column13: Lipogaine truly works - and is better than competitors
column14:
In 2012, I started using various products containing minoxidil to deal with thinning hair. It was most noticeable in the crown area, but also thinning elsewhere. I've used Rogaine Foam, Spectral DNC and Lipogaine. Lipogaine comes out the clear winner of the three. All 3 helped re-grow hair, but only Lipogaine did this without unwanted side-effects: Lipogaine does not smell bad (like Spectral DNC) nor change the texture of your hair in ways that makes styling difficult (like Rogaine Foam).

Anyone that's starting to use a product containing minoxidil needs to first realize that the process of re-growing hair is long-term. I did not start seeing noticeable results for about 3 months. Again, I emphasize START SEEING RESULTS. You are not going to grow a full head of hair in 3 months - but if you keep at it, the product will work.

One aspect of my thinning hair I don't like is my hairline at the forehead. Although I've read that minoxidil products are not best at working in this area, I have spent several months carefully applying Lipogaine to this area and have seen definite regrowth. Hopefully I will work as well as it has with the rest of my head.

I'm definitely pleased with the results. My head of hair is fuller and the hair is strong. I also like the fact Lipogaine (unlike other minoxidil products) does not have a bad smell and does not create problems with styling my hair.

You can save a little money by purchasing the 3 month supply, which comes with 3 vials and one eye-dropper.

column6: Aesthetica Cosmetics Contour and Highlighting Powder Foundation Palette / Contouring Makeup Kit; Easy-to-Follow, Step-by-Step Instructions Included
column14:
This contouring kit was highly rated and discounted by 50% which was why I purchased it. It came on time as expected.

The kit does come with diagrams of different face shapes to illustrate which parts of your face to add contour or highlights. I recommend that you watch the video provided on Aesthetica's Web site to learn about contouring techniques.

There are step by step instructions that are really generalized. You really learn the most information from watching the video.

Also, be sure to buy a large blush brush and an eyeshadow brush for use only with the kit. This isn't mentioned until you watch the instructional video. Obviously, they'd prefer it if you bought their 2 headed brush, but you can find good cheap brushes from Target or Walmart.

You'll want to practice a few times. What's not mentioned is that the top 3 colors are only for highlights and the bottom 3 are for contouring. I've practiced twice since I got my kit, but will be playing around with it some more.

column6: TRESemm√© Expert Selection Flexi Bounce Mousse, Youth Boost 8.1 oz
column14:
I like using mousse. My hair is very straight and using mousse easily adds volume and body to my hair. That said, this mousse works as it should on my hair. It lifts it and adds an extra boost. I find that even if I generously use this product, it doesn't add stickiness or weigh it down. It still leaves my hair soft and manageable while plumping it up. Some products leave a lot of residue and makes your hair look like it needs to be washed. This doesn't do that. It keeps your hair bouncy and light while adding body. I think my hair type is just right for this mouse. For the price, I think this works very well. You have to shake it up to get it foamy and then distribute it evenly through your hair. This works great when I use the blow dryer and flat iron and adds just enough body to make my hair fuller, shiny and it still retains a natural bounce. This Tresamme mousse doesn't make my scalp itch or cause build up on my hair. The product is easy to use and wash out.

I had to change my review to three stars because I developed an itchy rash on my neck after using this and had to give it a rest from this product. The rash went away with Benadryll cream but it took me a while to figure out what was giving me a rash and I think it was this mousse as it was the only new product I was using aside from a new pillow. I stopped using this and the rash went away and hasn't returned.

column14:
I started to review this on the seller feedback, oops.

Shipping: Very quick! Came at the beginning of the window estimated for delivery.
Packaging: Came in a cute little pink and blue box that was easy to open and was sturdy. Each bundle was labled with the length and in a hair net then inside a plastic bag. (Came with a cute little extra gift inside the box as well).

Hair: So far the hair seems awesome! It is definitely black even though there are VERY FEW single strands of a dark reddish brown throughout the bundles. Barely notice them, I just inspected them very closely. Also, when combing through the hair there were A FEW tiny pieces of what looks like dried glue. They slid out fairly easy though. Didn't notice really any shedding when combing through them. They are wavy as described, soft, and the same shade of black and texture throughout. I did test a strand with my straightener and it's real hair. It straightened really easily I might add and with little heat (I don't set my heat setting very high).

**I get these sewn in on 8.15.2015. I will post a few pictures afterwards of the finished product as well as the hair before installation. After a few weeks I'll try to remember to come back and update the status after wearing it for a bit. So far I feel like I will purchase from them again in the future.

The English name Shea comes from its Bambara name "sii", which means sacred. As a sacred tree, it is treated with particular respect.. Growing up to 60 feet tall, the Shea tree does not flower before it is 20 years old and can live up to 200 years. The Shea nuts are traditionally harvested by women, crushed and boiled to extract the Shea butter, which has its unconditional aficionados all over the world. In the hot Sahara or Savannah, Shea butter protects the skin from the sun and dehydration. For millenniums, people have used it to protect their skin from the drying winds and sun as well as to heal many skin problems, minor cuts and burns.

Just look for one that is:

Raw/Unrefined
Unbleached
Organic
Grade A

Different Types of Shea Butter, Different Qualities

Not all Shea butters are made equal when it comes to quality and efficiency. They come in different types depending on how they have been extracted from the nuts: refined or unrefined. You want to make sure that you get the unrefined organic Shea butter, here is why...

Refined Shea Butter

Refined Shea butter has been extracted with chemical process (with hexane mostly), which involves bleaching, deodorizing and overheating. All of these deeply altering chemical processes yield a white odorless Shea butter that has lost all of its deep moisturizing, anti-aging, protecting and healing properties. By the way, this is the type of Shea butter that goes into chocolate making. Do you taste the hexane in your chocolate bar?

Unrefined Shea butter

The raw Shea butter in its natural state has been extracted manually or mechanically. It has a mild nutty-smoky scent and a golden to light ivory color. The odor can be removed thanks to a mild steam treatment that doesn't degrade any constituent. The raw or deodorized Shea butter is what you want to use because it has retained all its precious skin moisturizing, anti-aging and healing properties. This is the only type of Shea butter we carry at Nature Purity, because for us quality is a must and we do not do "green-washing". Our Shea butter is organic and fair trade.

Shea butter is for external use only. Ask a doc or dermatologist before using, especially with underlying skin conditions. Those with nut allergies should avoid or check with an allergist.

Indulge dry skin

According to the American Shea Butter Institute, the moisturizers in Shea butter are the same ones that are produced by the skin‚Äôs sebaceous glands, making it one of the best matches for dry skin.

Make your hair happy

Shea butter is used in many a hair care product and with good reason. It is said to have a number of benefits, including sealing in moisture, defining curl, conditioning the scalp, alleviating dandruff and decreasing the dreaded frizz. Also, applied to just the roots when styling can add a bit of volume to fine hair.

Fight wrinkles

The American Shea Butter Institute claims that the application of high-quality Shea butter will diminish the appearance of wrinkles after four to six weeks of use. Other research suggests that the application of Shea butter to the skin results in a brighter complexion and visibly reduced wrinkles.

Enhance your kisser

Shea butter is said to protect and soothe the lips. Apply several times a day; smooch frequently to test its efficacy.

Calm inflamed skin

Shea butter has several anti-inflammatory agents, including derivatives of cinnamic acid. In a study on Shea butter and its anti-inflammatory and chemo-preventive effects published in the Journal of Oleo Science, researchers concluded that ‚ÄúShea nuts and Shea fat (Shea butter) constitute a significant source of anti-inflammatory and anti-tumor promoting compounds.‚Äù

Fade stretch marks

While authorities like the Mayo Clinic and Baby Center note that the only way to really diminish stretch marks is with Retin-A or laser treatments, there are many testimonies across the Web of people who swear by the power of Shea butter for helping in this endeavor.

Ease eczema and acne

Both eczema and acne require delicate treatments as not to exacerbate the problems; and in both cases, a pure and natural product is favorable to one with synthetic ingredients and fragrances. According to reviews, Shea butter's efficacy for eczema and acne is mixed. Some say that it doesn't work at all, but more seem to agree that Shea butter does indeed help. For eczema, users like to soak in a tub then apply Shea butter while still damp to lock in the moisture; for acne, suggestions include applying a thin film after cleaning the face and then rinsing it off after a few hours. We can't guarantee these uses, but with Shea's unique properties, it sure seems worth a try. (And if you have experience with either of these treatments, leave a comment and let us know how you fared.)

Repair cracked heels

Many who suffer from painful cracked heels and dry cuticles claim that Shea butter solves the problem. For heels that are particularly bad, apply Shea butter before bed and slip into cotton socks for the night.

Give skin an antioxidant boost

Shea butter is high in vitamins A and E, as well as catechins and other significant plant antioxidants, which may protect skin from damage. There is evidence that suggests that cinnamic acid esters in Shea fat also help to prevent damage from ultraviolet radiation.

Ditch the itch from insect bites

With its anti-inflammatory magic, it makes sense that Shea butter would quell the swelling of insect bites, but if crowds of people across the Web are correct, it also stops the irksome itch of insect bites pretty much on the spot.

Shave Aid

Some like a Shea shave because it‚Äôs so nice on the skin; others say that it doesn‚Äôt provide enough cushion for the razor since it doesn‚Äôt lather. If you like more of an ‚Äúoil shave‚Äù than a sudsy one, shave with Shea. And even if you use a lather to shave with, applying Shea post-shave can soothe irritation.

Clear nasal congestion

A study published in the British Journal of Clinical Pharmacology found that Shea butter was potentially more efficacious in treating nasal congestion than nasal drops. Subjects with congestion (mostly associated with seasonal allergy) were given 2-4 grams of Shea butter applied to the interior of the nostril ‚Äúby means of the subject‚Äôs right index finger.‚Äù (Which is to say, you can try this at home!) The airways of those using the Shea butter (opposed to those using nasal drops or petroleum jelly) became clear within 30 to 90 seconds of application, and remained so for 5 to 8 hours, besting the other treatment methods.

TIP: If you get unrefined Shea butter, that means it has not been filtered and may contain trace particles of the Shea nut. I often gently heat my Shea butter until it just melts and then pour through a cheesecloth or strainer to remove any particles, then pour the Shea butter into silicon molds in premeasured amounts so that it is ready to use for your natural beauty recipes.

We can't guarantee these uses, but with Shea's unique properties, it sure seems worth a try. (And if you have experience with either of these treatments, leave a comment and let us know how you fared.)

Repair cracked heels

Many who suffer from painful cracked heels and dry cuticles claim that Shea butter solves the problem. For heels that are particularly bad, apply Shea butter before bed and slip into cotton socks for the night.

Give skin an antioxidant boost

Shea butter is high in vitamins A and E, as well as catechins and other significant plant antioxidants, which may protect skin from damage. There is evidence that suggests that cinnamic acid esters in Shea fat also help to prevent damage from ultraviolet radiation.

Ditch the itch from insect bites

With its anti-inflammatory magic, it makes sense that Shea butter would quell the swelling of insect bites, but if crowds of people across the Web are correct, it also stops the irksome itch of insect bites pretty much on the spot.

Shave Aid

Some like a Shea shave because it‚Äôs so nice on the skin; others say that it doesn‚Äôt provide enough cushion for the razor since it doesn‚Äôt lather. If you like more of an ‚Äúoil shave‚Äù than a sudsy one, shave with Shea. And even if you use a lather to shave with, applying Shea post-shave can soothe irritation.

Clear nasal congestion

A study published in the British Journal of Clinical Pharmacology found that Shea butter was potentially more efficacious in treating nasal congestion than nasal drops. Subjects with congestion (mostly associated with seasonal allergy) were given 2-4 grams of Shea butter applied to the interior of the nostril ‚Äúby means of the subject‚Äôs right index finger.‚Äù (Which is to say, you can try this at home!) The airways of those using the Shea butter (opposed to those using nasal drops or petroleum jelly) became clear within 30 to 90 seconds of application, and remained so for 5 to 8 hours, besting the other treatment methods.

TIP: If you get unrefined Shea butter, that means it has not been filtered and may contain trace particles of the Shea nut. I often gently heat my Shea butter until it just melts and then pour through a cheesecloth or strainer to remove any particles, then pour the Shea butter into silicon molds in premeasured amounts so that it is ready to use for your natural beauty recipes.

column6: Project E Beauty D'arsonval High frequency direct for Home Use - skin tightening, Wrinkles, Fine lines, Puffy Eyes
column14:
I bought this device last summer.

After I received it and looked at the instructions, I was somewhat concerned about the quality of this device because the instructions are horrible! I wasn't sure how to use it and at the time, I couldn't find any good instructions online. So what I did was just move it in upward strokes over my face and held it in place over areas of bigger concern for several minutes. I did this morning and night for about 2 weeks. Doing just those things definitely helped. My husband noticed a difference after a couple of weeks. I know he would tell me the truth because he's told me when things didn't help at all.

How It Has Helped Me:

After about a month, I began to use it less and less frequently until I just didn't use it anymore. I went for several months without using it at all before I began to see an increase in wrinkles again. So I began using it again. I saw improvement more quickly this time.

I have quit using it and restarted using it several times over the last year and each time I have noticed a quicker improvement in my skin.

It has helped with:

- Vertical lines above my lips from years of smoking.( Quitting smoking helped a lot, but not enough)
- Puffy eyes
- The 'elevens' between my eyebrows
- Crows feet
- A general lift in the eye area
-Tightening of the skin under my jaw line. ( That has never returned even when I quit using this device)
- An all over healthy glow to my skin
*** The ONLY thing I can't say I've noticed an improvement in is pore size, BUT I haven't used this consistently over the last year. Therefor, I can't say for certain that it wouldn't. I also have never gotten rid of all wrinkles, but again, I haven't been consistent with use.

Information About Me

These are things I would like to know about people reviewing beauty products. I'm listing factors that may or may not have an effect on my success with this device.

- I am *yikes*, 44 years old
- I am very fair skinned
- I have spent YEARS in the sun without any sunscreen working outside as a landscape designer and avid gardener.
- I began using sunscreen religiously at the age 41
- I did a lot of damage to my skin by smoking for nearly 30 years, especially vertical lines above my lips
- I never did much to take care of my skin until I was 39 years old
- At 41, I began making my own skin care products from organic sources which helped A LOT before beginning to use this device
- I have done glycolic acid peels at home. Many before using this device
- I have been blessed with good genes, (This may have something to do with why I have had such good results?)

About This Device:

I have never had any problems with this device. The only one thing that has happened is that a screw came loose. This caused the wands to wobble. I tightened it up (with the device unplugged!) I have had no problems since then. ( see picture)

I have since learned that the frequency rating of this device is much lower than what is generally recommended. Even so, I have had wonderful results.

I am considering purchasing a new HF device with a higher Hz rating. When I do, I will purchase one by D'arsonval because it is obviously a well made product.

column6: Sally Hansen Instant Cuticle Remover, 1 Fluid Ounce
column14:
This stuff is great for removing cuticles (-NOT- the Eponychium, which is live skin, that people often try to trim) and removing thickened skin (callouses) on your feet. Yeah, gross... but effective! The directions say to squeeze onto cuticles, wait 15 seconds, wash with soapy water. I use it slightly differently: Squeeze onto cuticles, wait 15 seconds, gently push the surface of the nail bed to edge with a soft rubber cuticle pusher (Jamberry or BMC brands are great), then wash. Follow up with cuticle oil to prevent tearing and drying. For calluses, the directions say to do the same but for one minute. I rub with a washcloth before washing with soap and water. Repeat if necessary.
It doesn't remove the Eponychium, which is apparently what some people want- it just removes the actual dead cuticle and neatens up your nail beds. Even if your nails look fine now, they'll look even better after this cuticle remover and your polish will stick longer without the layer of invisible cuticle covering your nail.

I'd describe the consistency as being between dish soap and hand sanitizer. It's enough to sit on your nails for the few seconds required. It's not particularly drying but you'll need to use some cuticle oil afterwards. Overall, I love it - the bottle is larger than my CND Cuticle Eraser, cheaper, and works just as well.

column6: Henna Hair & Beard Dye - 100% Natural & Chemical Free - The Henna Guys
column14:
This review is for the Deep Red henna color.
I've treated my hair with henna several times before. My first time was with regular henna from The Henna Guys. The color came out extremely pigmented, but pretty orange, since it was pure henna. It wasn't ideal but I didn't care since the condition of my hair improved SO MUCH from just one use. I straighten it often so it was extremely damaged. I broke some comb teeth trying to get rid of the gnarly knots that would always form in the back and at the ends (even after conditioning and oiling it up it took me an hour to do a half assed job). I tried oil treatments and leave in conditioners, but they didn't do much and mostly just made my hair look oily and weighed it down. But after one henna treatment my hair felt amazing, and I knew right away that I'd be using it for a long time.

The second time I used henna, I decided to save some money by getting the Godrej mix with 9 herbs. I thought it would be a good deal since you get more of it and there are other plant powders in it that are supposed to be beneficial to hair. I was disappointed to find that it didn't make my hair as soft as the Henna Guys henna did. Also, my hair came out much brassier, less pigmented, and dryer, which was a pretty bad combination. I wasn't very happy, but I kept using it throughout the year. I really wanted to finish what I had left, but I eventually gave in and bought the Deep Red color from the Henna Guys. I had already had a great experience with one of their products, so I hoped I would be equally happy with this purchase. In fact, I was even happier than the first time. I was absolutely blown away by how much it repaired my damaged, dry hair (again), and how VIBRANT the color came out on my dark brown hair! Not only that, but due to the hibiscus powder, it started out looking almost black, but with strong, gorgeous purple and red highlights that bring me compliments even 2 months later. The best I can describe the color is a beautiful black cherry. Don't even get me started on how magnificent it looks when the sunlight is hitting it at the right angle! I honestly can't remember the last time someone had complimented my hair. I couldn't be happier with this henna powder. The only drawback of the Deep Red version is that it bleeds orange for a while, but for me it wasn't that big of a deal. I just use an old towel to dry my hair and it's all good. It's no different than what you have to deal with with a semi-permanent dye. I saw some people giving out low ratings because of this issue, but it's not as bad as they made it out to be. It's 100% worth it for me. After 2 months, there's very minimal orange bleed, and while the color is less deep and less purple, it STILL doesn't look brassy. The purple tones still come out, just not as strongly as before. The color is definitely more red now, and my hair is still looking great. Seriously, this stuff is amazing.

I'll try to add some photos soon!a beautiful black cherry. Don't even get me started on how magnificent it looks when the sunlight is hitting it at the right angle! I honestly can't remember the last time someone had complimented my hair. I couldn't be happier with this henna powder. It's 100% worth it for me. After 2 months, there's very minimal orange bleed, and while the color is less deep and less purple, it STILL doesn't look brassy. The purple tones still come out, just not as strongly as before. The color is definitely more red now, and my hair is still looking great. Seriously, this stuff is amazing.

I'll try to add some photos soon!

column6: Vidal Sassoon Hot Air Styler
column14: I've used a dryer and round brush when blow drying my hair for years, but getting the top really dry can be a challenge so I was hoping this tool would make it easier. After being so used to the weight of an ac dryer it felt really lightweight in my hand, and it took a bit to get used to having the other hand free. I suppose that since it's right up by your head with your hair wound around it it wouldn't be safe to have it as hot as a normal hair dryer. I didn't have problems with tangling, and it did dry my hair on top and put kind of a nice shape in it, but my hair looked sparse and frizzy. I think part of the problem was that I am used to a 3/4 inch round brush and this barrel was 1 inch. Due to my hair type, length and style I have always had problems styling my hair with a 1 inch round brush. For myself, I think I'd have better results with a 1/2 to 3/4 inch barrel, but I can't be certain it wouldn't leave my hair frizzy so I don't think I can turn in my hair dryer just yet.

column13: This is a MUST in anyones skincare routine!
column14: I LOVE this product! I am an avid mask user. Masks have always been a key product in my skincare routine. I've heard a lot about the Dead Sea Mud Mask lately and after seeing how many great reviews it has, I had to give it a try! All I can say is WOW! I've always gone between 2 or 3 masks at a time for different skin problems. Not anymore! The Dead Sea Mud Mask has completely replaced those. After just one use I felt a major difference in my skin and by the next morning most of my skin problems had vanished. I have combination skin (oily t-zone and dry everywhere else) and large open pores on my nose. I use this twice a week after cleansing my face before bed. This is the first mask that hydrates my skin AND clears any acne and uneven skin tone. My biggest skin problem is the pores on my nose. I've always found no matter what I use they just don't go away. This mask fixed that problem, too! I've had a lot less dirt and oil build up and my pores are starting to look smaller and less noticeable. It's not often you get a mask that does it all. A little goes a long way and I see this mask lasting quite a while. I will definitely be repurchasing when the time comes. I would highly recommend this mask to anyone! Dry, oily, acne, uneven skin... this mask will fix it.

column13: and honestly wasn't very happy with the results
column14: I've used this in silver, and honestly wasn't very happy with the results. My hair was pure cold white, but as my natural hair color is black I tried to do a bit of a gradient with the silver to make my roots less obnoxious. The first time I tried it just wasn't obvious at all, it appeared as if nothing happened. A while later I figured going full silver would be fun, and it'd probably just fade back to my white anyways. Boy was I wrong. I went from a cold white with zero brassiness or yellow at all to a muddy yellow grey. I really don't know how this silver color put SO much brassiness in my hair, but suffice to say I was left with a weird muddy blonde when it finally faded out. Clairol's Shimmer Lights Shampoo does a much better job of getting my hair silver than this dye does.

I think part of the problem when looking at low-cost cosmetic brushes we all worry they'll be scratchy and hard, or they'll shed terribly...or just be really, really poor applicators of makeup. This is certainly not the case with these brushes. I know. I looked at the price of this set and thought to myself how on Earth could they possibly be good if they are *so* inexpensive? I was half expecting those terrible, cheap brushes that come around during the holiday season, or worse, that come free with a product you buy. Not the case at all.

It's rather a feat to produce brushes like this so inexpensively. These are dense yet beyond soft. I have waited over a year to do a review of these. I HATE when I read reviews when someone has the product for like a day. Sure, they'll probably be amazing right after you get them. But how do they hold up? I'm not expecting too much for the low price, but I don't want to waste my money, either. So. They do not shed (I've washed them about 10 times now with baby shampoo). They remain as soft as the day they arrive. No discoloring, no scents, etc. They've remained just as nice as the day they arrived.

The application with these brushes is amazing. I like a full coverage look from my foundation. The best way I have found do to that is with a dense, kabuki- like brush. Yay! These fit the bill. I love applying foundation with these. I only use these for foundations. I tend to use the flat top and the rounded top most. The result is an airbrushed look. It's nice to have a set of four because if you have slacked on cleaning, you'll always have one you could use. The handles are solid and hefty, without being too heavy or awkward.

I am a fan of high end cosmetics (and brushes). I use a lot of Bobbi Brown brushes and my absolute FAVORITE foundation brush is from Kevyn Aucoin (read: not cheap). This brush set is an amazing option for someone just starting out withe cosmetics, someone who doesn't want to invest a lot of money in tools, etc. They're just...great. Cheaper than even Real Techniques (and similar to the Expert Face Brush, imo)!a lot of money in tools, etc. They're just...great. Cheaper than even Real Techniques (and similar to the Expert Face Brush, imo)!

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I received two full-sized tubes (one tube of "Step 1" and one tube of "Step 2" and they're color-coded!) in the mail for free from BzzAgent as a promotion from Crest brand. The first tube (cleansing toothpaste) is purple and the directions say to brush with this paste for one minute, spit, but DO NOT rinse. Then brush with the second tube (a white tube, the whitening gel) for one minute, spit, rinse with water. Those steps are easy-peasy compared to other whitening products on the market!
You're supposed to do these steps twice a day. If you're like me and brush at lunch time or additional times throughout the day, I've just been using the step one tube without the gel for those additional times.
Both the paste and the gel taste pretty good, which was a surprise to me! Most whitening products don't taste so pleasant. The toothpaste kind of reminds me of that "bubble mint" flavor of the blue toothpaste I used when I was a kid, and the gel has more of a cool mint flavor. My mouth feels fresh and clean when I'm finished brushing, and no weird after taste or filmy sensation is left behind. :)

There is one thing I should mention: the first time I used this product, I saw a white spot on my gum on one side Immediately after using. I was prepared for it because it is written on the packaging as something to be aware of but I know some people don't always see things like that so I want to let you know it's nothing dangerous (and not painful or anything either). I had used it at night that time, and it disappeared by morning. :)

As far as results go, I've been using the product for 4 weeks now and I have noticed a difference in the brightness of my smile. I wouldn't say it's a huge difference in whiteness per se, but I definitely think it's noticeably brighter. I think the best part isn't the whitening power but the squeaky clean feeling in my mouth after brushing.

column6: Ann Chery Caffeine Cream - Slimming And Toning Cream Reduces Cellulite Appearance
column14:
What should have been obvious before buying it, is this product doesn't work lol I applied it at least once a day for a month and saw no obvious change. I've found that to be the case with most of these creams.

After further research, it appears that no cream will really get rid of your stretch marks. The reason being, stretch marks are not on the surface of your skin. The only proven method of removing them is some sort of surgery like laser-removal or a tummy tuck (removing the skin entirely).

I have a paler complexion and the only way I've seen that my skin looks thicker, tighter, and my stretch marks less noticeable is when I use fake tanning lotions. Other than that, no stretch mark removal cream has really worked.

I don't recommend these rollers if you're looking for spiral curls. That's not what these are good for. These are good for giving volume to a straight hair look. I recommend wrapping small sections of dry hair around the rollers, while rolling them away from your face. Usually, unless your hair is really short, they stay put by themselves. Sometimes with shorter sections of hair I use clips or bobby pins to secure two rollers together so they don't fall. I also spritz with hairspray to add a little more volume to my roots. I usually leave them in for 10 to 20 minutes, or however long it takes me to finish getting ready in the morning. Then, I take them out and shake for natural looking body and volume.

column6: OPI Studio LED Light
column14: EDITED REVIEW: FEBRUARY 12, 2016 I decided just to keep this light after my second review. But I, now, fully regret that decision. It has been about seven months, and it was working okay. The burning scent went away but it was still pretty hot on my clients skin. The sensor is not accurate most of the time as well. So I always had to unplug and plug my lamp back in to get it to work.  Today, the machine finally broke on me. The middle section of the light bulbs are not turning on anymore. The touch sensitive timing also stopped working. When I received this light, I filled out and sent out the 1-year warranty. I called OPI's customer service and they stated that the warranty is not applicable when purchased from non-authorized dealers such as Amazon and eBay. They also do not have anyone at the moment that can fix this light.  I'm pretty annoyed. This shouldn't happen after only seven months. If the warranty is void, this company should make an effort to get their products off Amazon. I DON'T recommend this light at all. The black OPI LED light has been discontinued. I've used Gelish in my last salon for years and didn't have any issues. If you can't find the black OPI LED light, I recommend the Gelish brand but make sure you double-check the warranty policy.  EDITED REVIEW: AUGUST 12, 2015 The first time I used the white led studio light I was amazed and gave it 5 stars. But after using it on a few of my clients, I'm not so impressed anymore. There are several issues I'm experiencing with it so I'm reducing my rating and giving it 3 stars for the WHITE STUDIO LED LIGHT. For hands the size of it is great. But for pedicures, I feel there is not enough space for the foot to fit in without feeling comfortable. Because of this, I've had had a few complaints from clients stating that the lamp feels too hot on their skin. The next issue is that when using, I notice a slight burning smell. It smells as if plastic is burning.  I've never experienced any issues with the BLACK LED LIGHT. Even though it's a lot higher in price, I will most likely exchange my white one for the black one.  MY FIRST INTIAL REVIEW: AUGUST 10, 2015 Amazing LED light! Really happy with my purchase! I purchased the white OPI Studio LED Light and it works perfectly. I use the black LED light at work so I'm more familiar with it but for the price of the white light, you really can't beat it!  Some differences between the two.. The black led light is made of metal, making it heavier to handle but seems more durable in the long run. It's bottom less and is bigger, so you have more space. There are 4 pushable button settings for the timing. There is a handle on lamp making it easy to carry.  In comparison, the white led light is made of plastic, making it lightweight. The bottom tray is removable so you can cure the polish on your toes. The tray also has finger guides to help guide your fingers for placing. It's smaller (flatter and more narrow) than the black led light. The timer button is touch sensitive which is a really nice touch.

I also added the ACT dry mouth tooth paste and mouth wash to go with my regimen to treat medication -induced dry mouth- and the dryness has greatly improved!! A dry mouth causes cavities indirectly since lack of saliva in the mouth leads to increased bacteria, which can lead to tooth decay. LASTLY: I noticed a couple of reviewers stated they "SLEEP" with these in the mouth. column14:
I have had painful and unsightly hormonal breakouts on my back and shoulders since I was 24 (I just turned 29) and after trying a ton of different products, finally I thought "Hey, I use tea tree oil for everything else, maybe it'll work." So I searched all over the site and found several, but this sounded the best, so I got the body gel and the toner along with Phisoderm for blemished skin that balances your skin's PH levels (important for any troubled skin treatment) and after the first shower (this first on a body brushing tool, then this again on a loofah, then the Phisoderm with a terrycloth very thoroughly and then the toner on my shoulders and back right before my pores closed) I couldn't believe it...although I had to as there was tangible proof. The large, under the skin bumps weren't as inflamed and didn't really hurt, the medium ones were smaller, and the small bumps were in that state where you know it will be gone in a day or two. I love the scent, as it actually smalls like tea tree oil, which to me smells like cleanliness and being pathogen-free lol
This was just my experience, I don't think it would be the same for everyone, I think I just got exactly what my body needed, which was PH balance and anti-bacterial that wasn't harsh and was mostly natural, which is what I prefer anyway.

I will never use other domestic products for my face though; I have VERY sensitive skin. Most products contain harsh ingredients like benzoyl peroxide...I'd left my Porefinist Cleansing Oil and Foaming Cleanser in my other bathroom, didn't own this yet, and found an a tube of ********** cleanser so I used that...that stuff burned half of my face HORRIBLY and left it raw and almost bloody red and left the rest painfully sensitive. P.S- To anyone interested in alternative, non-drugstore brand natural products for facial skin: For facial breakouts which are mild and only for a few days a month like mine, this, I use a spot treatment; generally use a Bee Venom and Propolis with Mucin spot treatment over a fully dried and patted in tea tree and eucalyptus essence, pink clay with tea tree and a few other super effective natural ingredients when that dries, and if I get a really large blemish, I use the pink clay with tea tree oil clay pack and the next day the blemish has shrunk and lost so much redness that it isn't even visible. column13: This IS a permanent/Texturizers Only good on COILY Types!!
column14:
All I can say is that this (beep) ruined my hair!! Unless you have Coily hair, this is not going to do anything but STRAITEN your hair. I did some research on texturizers before purchasing and of course, all articles claim that though they are a mild straightener, texturizers will loosen your natural curls... But if you have kinky/(already) Curly hair.. you really just need to condition because it isn't your curls that are the problem, it's the dryness from it being kinky that needs to be solved.
Some people say that when you go natural, it isn't all that important to know your hair type, but they are Wrong!!! They put these little light skinned children on the boxes of these products which suggests that no matter your hair type, it'll look like hers. But the truth is, this IS a Relaxer and unless you have hair that is sooo tightly coiled and course (meaning, when you look at your roots, the hair is NOT Fine and/or Wavy), the child's hair on the box will Not be your end result. You, are going to end up with a half-assed perm! (excuse my language)
With my experience, if tou really want to go natural, just stay away from this stuff. I know how frustrating and time consuming it could be trying to figure out alk the things that your poor hair is yearning for but use the words from the great Prince Akeem from Zamunda.... Only but 'the Finest Nuts and Berries' will do!! (Lol) I don't recommend this product. Its not healthy and very damaging to your hair. I have an entire section of hair on my crown and back, left side that I basically have to cut out of my head because it's brittle and absolutely destroyed! I hate myself for putting this (beep) in my hair and if I had a daughter, I for damn sure wouldn't use this on her EVER!

column6: Improved Triple Mint Freshness - Polident Antibacterial 3 Minute Denture Cleanser 96 Tablets Per Box (Pack of 2)
column13: MUCH Better than Efferdent for Mouthguards and only marginally more expensive
column14:
We are a family of night grinders, so we have mouthguards that we use these denture washes to clean. We started with Efferdent since that was the most popular on Amazon at the time and it seemed much cheaper.

After we finished using Efferdent, I went back to Amazon and realized that a pack of Efferdent was $7.97 for 120 tablets for one of the better/most popular deals selling on Amazon, coming to about 6.6 cents each tablet. This deal for Polident is 96x2=192 tablets for $14.27, coming to about 7.4 cents each. This product page for Polident can make the casual browser/shopper mistake this for being almost twice as expensive than Efferdent, as I read the title really fast and pretty much thought it was $14.27 for 96 tablets...only after I read it more carefully did I realize it was really 192 tablets.

The reviews for Polident are glowing and much better than those I read for Efferdent....I must say that even though this Polident stuff is less than 1 cent extra, I find Polident MUCH better for these reasons:
- Faster and easier to use (Polident is done cleaning in as little as 3 minutes compared to the Efferdent that needs 15)
- Cleans just as well if not better. I notice all this weird blue residue on the cup I soak the mouthguard in when I use Efferdent--there is no residue on the cup after using Polident. If you think about it, there must be more residue left on the mouthguard itself after using Efferdent compared to Polident if the cup itself has all that residue. The mouthguard feels much cleaner after 3 minutes with Polident and a quick rinse in the sink afterwards compared to 15 minutes with Efferdent followed by the same quick rinse.
- Prefer Polident odor/scent over Efferdent

So for less than one cents extra per tablet, my family will gladly use Polident for years to come.

column13: Nice Mineral Powder, More Foundation Than Bronzer on Me
column14:
I was offered this item at a discount in exchange for a fair and honest review, so here it is:

First, I am reasonably fair complected. I do tan, but I also burn easily without proper coverage. I have natural dark blonde hair. I am explaining all of this because I chose the "light" bronzing powder anticipating that it would, indeed, give me a healthy glow. Perhaps it's just too light or the fact that it's late summer and I already have a base tan, but this powder very much goes on me like a basic foundation powder and I do not see any bronzing effects. I do like the matte finish and it feels light on my face, so I will happily use it for light powder coverage, but it is not what I was expecting.

Secondly, the price on this item is exceptionally high, even for what the item runs elsewhere. Even with my great discount, I don't quite get the hype, so to speak. It's a nice mineral powder, but maybe my lack of experience with this line makes me unable to appreciate the luxury of the item? As it was shipped wrapped only in a thin layer of bubble wrap and then dropped in a larger box with other items, I had quite a bit of mess just pulling off the tab. I tried to tap it back into the container, but there was still some loss of product and at this price point, that is frustrating. Also, I received just the powder in the container, there was no kabuki brush included as stated in the listing.

Quenched and Peppermint are great for just a shiny and glossy look while peach is a more natural light corally pink nude with shimmer and grape gives my lips the perfect amount of color that brings life into my no-makeup face. These may not be as moisturizing and healing as Bert's Bees and Carmex, but why not just put a little more effort into applying it often and conditioning your lips subtly.

column6: [2 Pack]Ipow 3D Super Smooth Mask with Earplugs- Breathable & Soft Contoured Sleep Eye Mask With Adjustable Velcro Strap Perfect for Travel, Insomnia or Quiet Night Sleep
column13: Nice Set Of Sleep Masks And Earplugs
column14:
I have tried out a few different sleep masks over the years and this is one of the ones that I have liked the most. I love how the mask is contoured and not just a flat piece of fabric. As you can see in the picture provided with the listing there is an area for your nose and also the areas for your eyes are raised so that the fabric is not touching your eyes.

The mask is nice and dark and fit both myself and my wife well so I would guess that it would fit more adults without a problem. The strap has a Velcro connection at the back and is easy to adjust.

The earplugs are a nice touch if you're buying this set to travel you never know what you'll have to endure from noisy neighbors in the room next door or partying in the streets below. They are a very basic foam type of earplug but they'll do the job.

Overall this is a really nice set of eye masks and earplugs that are perfect for traveling or just when you need to get some sleep during the daytime. Recommended.

The Therapeutic Lotion & Soap
Since the pore therapy worked. I looked it up online and saw that there were two more products to the package. I ordered the cleaning bottle and used it with the pore therapy. IT WORKED EVEN BETTER.
Then I tried this Therapeutic lotion along with the other two. I did not see any enhancements so I just stopped using it. I bought this lotion about a year ago.
A week ago, I saw the bottle and didn't want to throw it away because 1) it was hard to find - always out of stock 2) it was expensive. So I started using it again and now IT WORKS.
So, with the Pore Therapy and the Cleaning soap and another product I use (acne=scars so the other product is to lighten the scars) my skin was doing good but adding this lotion makes it look better - Skin is smoother, I believe it helps with everything : pores reductions, acne scars, even tone ....
If you have been battling any kind of acne, you know your skin. One other reason why I decide to use it too is because I thought my skin was "healthy" enough to accept the product now and it did.
Give it a shot - Pore therepy and this Lotion should work... The soap really cleans the oil from your skin if you have oily skin hence why I use it

column6: Dove Men+Care Body Wash, Aqua Impact 18 oz
column13: Body and face wash that stings my face and eyes but feels refreshing on the body
column14:
ABOUT ME:

I'm one of those women who use and love men's body wash. (I even wear Men's Infinity perfume on occasion.) I often choose these over others for my shower such as Old Spice, Irish Spring Gear Body Wash, and some AXE fragrances (although AXE is usually my last choice due to the strong fragrance in their products). My most favorite men's shower gels of all time were Glacier Bay, Woodland, Mountain Frost and Cool Spring from Bath and Body Works but the company discontinued them several years ago. Since I love men's shower products so much, I often hide them from my boyfriend.

ABOUT THE PRODUCT:

When this men's product came up for review, I just had to try it. Since this is both a face and body wash, I used it in the shower on my entire body. It has a mediocre lather and does feel refreshing as a body wash. I also like the fresh scent. My skin also felt clean, soft, and moisturized after showering.

This wash is also touted as a face wash. Therefore, I incorrectly assumed it was gentle and safe enough to use on my face. However, it stung my face and eyes even though my eyes were closed. The product instructions say to keep away from the eyes but I never understood how to do that when washing the rest of my face. Since the cooling affect is achieved via the menthol ingredient in the soap, this is also what causes the sting.

I've purchased mint body washes in the past that have the same effect. I prefer a wash that does not sting and which I can gently use on my face as well as my body, but this is not one of them. It is because, besides a body wash, they market this as a face wash that I rate this two stars for the results I experienced. However for the body, I consider this a 4-star wash.

column6: Travalo Excel
column13: Hasn't leaked for me. I love it!
column14:
I was worried I'd have trouble filling it up (I've never used a refillable atomizer before), but as many others have said, it was super easy. On the bottom of the atomizer, there's a little "hole." All you have to do is take the perfume/fragrance you want, take off the top sprayer (the nozzle part that just pulls right off), and set the atomizer hole on top of the spigot. Push it down, and the perfume bottle will "spray" the contents into the atomizer. Keep doing that until you can see it fill on the clear side, and wah-la!

I then wiped the bottom off, just to make sure there wasn't any residue left. The atomizer comes with a cute little case, so I put it back in that (to assure myself if it did leak, it wouldn't get all over the inside of my purse), and I went on my merry way. I've had it in there for a few weeks now, and not a drop of perfume to be wasted!

column6: Redken Shades EQ 09V Platinum Ice Color Gloss for Women, 2 Ounce
column14: I used 9V and 9NB in equal parts to tone down the ugly golden hues in my color treated blond hair.  A few weeks after I had balayage (with three different shades) my hair started turning really gold.  I tried using purple shampoo, which did work, but the effects are temporary and don't last through a regular shampoo.  I had never used Shades EQ before but this formula was recommended by the hair board on makeupalley.com.  I wanted to neutralize the gold but not take all the warmth out of my hair.  Simply put, I didn't want an ashy result.  So NB was added to 9V, which has a violet base and therefore cancels out yellow tones.  The NB is a neutral/brown and would mitigate the effects of the 9V.  I'm happy to say I got exactly the result I was hoping for.  I I first shampooed with a clarifying shampoo and lightly conditioned.  I then applied the color to damp hair. I left the color mixture on for about 8 minutes, just until I saw that the most obvious golden tones were neutralized.  I then rinsed and conditioned with a moisturizing formula.  The result is a warm neutral shade that is very close to the one I had when I left the salon.  It didn't darken my hair at all and left it shiny and soft and really healthy looking.  This is exactly the result I was hoping for.  I'm impressed with Shades EQ.  I only hope the color lasts several weeks.  I use a sulfate free shampoo and try to wash my hair as little as possible, which keeps the color fresh and bright longer.  If you want to neutralize some gold but don't want a really cool toned result, I suggest you use this formula.  I definitely recommend this brand of color and this formula.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I haven't used an electric razor for at least ten years. It was a $50 electric razor, and pretty much no frills. I've been shaving with a cartridge razor since then. I was given a Braun Series 9 shaver for free to review. Compared to that old electric razor, the Braun Series 9 shaver is like magic. I had about four days beard stubble, and fully expected it to hurt a little bit. Not only did it not hurt, but it shaved my face pretty much effortlessly.

The model I have comes with the Clean & Charge station. To give you an idea of how much stubble it cut, it gave me three water drops (out of three) to indicate the maximum amount of cleaning needed. After it cleans, it actually enters a drying cycle to dry the blades.

I'm going on a trip in a couple of days, and one other benefit of carrying an electric razor is that I don't have to worry about taking too much shaving cream and getting it confiscated by the TSA. I'll just throw the razor and the charging cable in the included hard shell carrying case, and that's all I'll need.

column6: Remington iLIGHT Pro Hair Removal System
column13: Thick black hair like a man
column14: As I progressed in to menopause I started growing a full out manstache! Thick black hair like a man!! Even though I shaved it off I had a literal 5 o'clock shadow by the end of the day. It was horrifying!! I decided to give this a try before signing up for professional treatments.  I DID NOT follow the manufacturers directions and instead used the device every other day. I DID NOT shave beforehand so that the laser could find the dark hair and get after it. The pain for me was minimal and I worked my way up to the highest setting after about a week. A little pain is a small price to pay for being hair free.  After 2 months I am 70% hair free on my upper lip and will continue to use the light pro for maintenance.  It is so nice to just do this at home whenever necessary. My advice is to give it a try. The cost is less than one professional treatment and hopefully it will work for you too.

column13: Very comfortable, I'm a Norelco fan
column14: I know beards are kind of fashionable nowadays, but I've never been able to go more than a day or two without shaving before it starts to drive me crazy.  (Actually, I've gone a whole week while backpacking, but I'm sure you can guess what the first order of business was when I got out of the back country.)  I'm a big fan of Norelco shavers, having previously used the Arcitec.  As Norelco says in the manual, it takes a little while for your face to adjust to a new shaver, and it took me about a week before this one stopped feeling like it was pulling at the hairs.  This one can be used wet or dry, but I preferred using it dry as I was accustomed.  One plus for this one over the Arcitec is that the trimmer is a separate attachment which works much better.  The downside of it being separate, of course, is the fear that I'll lose it in the drawer.  I also like the angle of the heads on the Arcitec over this one - slightly cup shaped instead of bulged outward from the center, but both flex and once my face got used to it, it wasn't really an issue anymore.  Cleaning the heads is very easy - the whole top pops off and can be rinsed easily.  The top can even be disassembled for better cleaning - another plus over the Arcitec, where I was constantly getting tiny bits of fuzz from the towel clogging up the little rotary blades.  For even better but less frequent cleaning there is the base.  This comes with a solution to put in, but I found just rinsing it keeps it clean enough for the most part, and using the base is something that doesn't need to be done as often.  This is fortunate because the base is huge, and even my 13 year old daughter didn't like seeing it on the bathroom counter.  Also note that the base is not required for charging - the cord can be plugged straight into the shaver.  (A small "travel/storage case" also comes with it, which is very nice.)  My overall assessment is that this is a comfortable shaver that does a really good job for me.

It does a medium hold without the overly stiff look, nor the sticky feel from some styling gels. At the end of the day, my hair still looks relatively fresh instead of an oily mess.

The spray does have a manly scent that I don't really care for. I would rather prefer a fragrance-free spray. Fortunately, the scent fades away after drying and remains unobtrusive to most people within normal social interactions. As a styling spray, this seems like a winner to me.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: Braun Series 9 9090cc, a close comfortable shave with good bang for the buck!
column14:
I received the Braun Series 9 9090cc Electric Shaver with Cleaning Center from BzzAgent as part of a Bzz campaign FOR FREE. Upon being selected for the campaign I began to do a significant amount of research into the Braun Series 9. What I found was an abysmal lack of information with respect to this series in particular. Obviously because it is Braun's latest and greatest and most people hadn't really gotten their hands on it State-side just yet. I had a ton of questions though and no one place really answered them. Now that I have the razor and have been using it for about a week, I'm excited to be able to share the answers to my questions with you.

Let me begin by saying I am a life-long cartridge razor user. I never made the jump to electric because I had always heard that the shave wasn't anywhere near as close, the cuts were worse (entirely false apparently), and it just wasn't as comfortable. That's what I heard.

My first shave with the Braun Series 9 9090cc was a little rough because of the above, the fact that I'd never used an electric before. I didn't know what spots would need more pressure, less pressure, a few passes, etc. I even watched a video on how to shave with an electric! I found myself doing a cursory pass, leaving the bathroom and having to go back several times to get those spots that I missed. I also started with a solid 3-4 day beard. On me, that growth is near entirely invisible because of my hair color, but it‚Äôs present, uncomfortable and even a little thick, so I figured it‚Äôd be a good test. I was right. Eventually I wound up with what I would consider a comfortable shave that was NEARLY as close as what I could get with a cartridge razor with shaving cream. Considering I thought I‚Äôd be walking around with a bit of a shadow, I was highly impressed, and no stubble unless I really pulled at my skin in spots that are generally a pain even with a cart razor.

My next few shaves improved in both accuracy and time to complete. I am now to the point where I can knock out a nice clean shave in about 3 minutes. I‚Äôm also shaving with much less fear of cutting myself. Essentially because I feel like it‚Äôs pretty much not even possible. I have been stretching, pulling and digging into my face to get a nice clean shave for a week or so now and I‚Äôm just fine.

The Braun Series 9 9090cc brings a good deal of value to the table on top of a nice clean shave that you can even take on the go. The shaver comes with a locking / unlocking tilt head that plays very nice with the curves of your face. It comes with a trimmer for tight spots, side burns, etc. So far I have had good success with the trimmer in keeping my lines straight. On top of that, you get a charging / cleaning base and a single cleaning cartridge, estimated to last approximately 1 month.

The charging base cradles and cleans the razor when not in use while using an alcohol based solution from the cleaning cartridge inserted in the bottom of the base. It should be noted that the charging base requires to be plugged in (when charging), and that it takes up a little bit of space. If you have a small bathroom with limited outlets, this could get tricky. There isn‚Äôt a law that says it needs to be in the bathroom, but common sense puts it there most times. Following the instructions, after a shave, you should remove the head of the razor, use the included brush to sweep out any easily accessible loose remaining hairs, re-connect the head and then place head down in the cleaning center. With the touch of a button, the cleaner goes to work and 3 minutes later, you get a near surgically fresh electric shaver clean as the day it was born.

Cleaner cartridges can be found for about $19.32 for 4. Braun Clean & Renew 2 Cartridges Consider that about $4.83 per month to maintain your razor. When held up against cartridges (about 4 per month at $16 per pack), the cost for shave per month is a heck of a value, if you discount the initial cost of entry. At $350, some may find the Series 9 9090cc a bitter pill to swallow, but the month-over-month savings are definitely a teaspoon of honey to help the medicine go down. Just a little math for you. If you use this vs. cartridges, the razor pays for itself in 55 months!

Being raised on cartridge razors, and now stunned by how well this works leaves me with a bit of planning and strategizing to do I think. A cartridge shave with shaving cream is baby‚Äôs butt smooth. Electric a little less so. I think my plan go forward is to continue using the electric during the week, and go with a wet cartridge shave over the weekend. That should keep cost down, time less, and shaves comfortably close week over week.

I mentioned at the start of this that I had questions. I have answers.

1. Can you shave wet with the series 9 9090cc? The short answer is no. The long answer is that Series 9 from Braun has two wet razors, the 9095 and the 9040. However, at the risk of voiding the warranty on my shiny new $350 razor, I tried a wet shave. I wasn‚Äôt electrocuted and the razor came nice and clean after a cleaning cycle. The shave was also comfortable and familiar to a cartridge shave. I make no testament to the long term wear that this may cause. I‚Äôm sure any defects resultant to this kind of use will void warranty.

2. Do electric razors shave as closely as cartridge or disposable razors? Almost!

3. If you slip with an electric razor, can you cut yourself terribly and need to go to the hospital? I‚Äôm pretty sure you won‚Äôt be able to do that. But if you do, the number is still 911.

4. Are the cleaning cartridges refillable vs. re-purchase-able? See my previous notes on warranty. There are countless recipes to hack your cleaning cartridge online. Using them will assuredly void your warranty.

5. Do you need to replace the razor blades for an electric shaver? Yep. ‚ÄúBraun recommends changing your shaver‚Äôs foil & cutter block every 18 months to maintain your shaver‚Äôs maximum performance.‚Äù A replacement foil and cutter block is about $60.

6. Is it easy to shave with an electric? It is something I can stand in front of a mirror and do. Missing spots drives me nuts, and if I‚Äôm not at a mirror, I miss spots. I can‚Äôt understand how I have seen men driving and using an electric razor, but it happens. These men are brave professionals and I commend them.

Conclusion
The Braun Series 9 9090cc is a great electric razor. I say with honesty that I don‚Äôt have any other electric shaver to compare it to, but when matched against my normal shaving regiment of shaving cream and cartridge razor, it holds up well and it will supplement my weekly shaving routine in a way that will save time and cost. I can‚Äôt ask for a lot more than that.

****
Update
I have now had the Braun Series 9 9090 long enough to feel like it's part of my routing. Now, it is part of my routing. I shave with the 9090 5 days a week, and do one close shave with a cartridge razor and shave gel for that super clean feeling once a week.

For 5 days, I'm comfortable, my shave is close, my skin is smooth to the touch. No in-grown hairs, no cuts, not even skin irritation. I feel great, confident and look presentable on a daily basis.

I have found that the shave time tends to take only a little bit less time than a wet cartridge shave, but the cost savings are already being felt. Saving on cream, saving on razors, saving on water! The razor has remained pretty much as clean as un-boxing day thanks to it's cleaning base. I am still using my first cartridge. I run the cleaning cycle every second or third shave and so far I'm very very happy with the results.

I haven't persisted my use in wet shaving, the dry shave is really very nice and close and leaves my skin happy. If you are on the fence about picking up a Braun Series 9 shaver,

I know the price is a little scary, and I come from a place where I got mine for free from BzzAgent, but if I didn't, now knowing about electric shaving, it's a small price to pay for a fantastic package of convenience and good shaving!rmance.‚Äù A replacement foil and cutter block is about $60. 6. Conclusion The Braun Series 9 9090cc is a great electric razor. I say with honesty that I don‚Äôt have any other electric shaver to compare it to, but when matched against my normal shaving regiment of shaving cream and cartridge razor, it holds up well and it will supplement my weekly shaving routine in a way that will save time and cost. I can‚Äôt ask for a lot more than that. **** Update I have now had the Braun Series 9 9090 long enough to feel like it's part of my routing. Now, it is part of my routing. I shave with the 9090 5 days a week, and do one close shave with a cartridge razor and shave gel for that super clean feeling once a week. For 5 days, I'm comfortable, my shave is close, my skin is smooth to the touch. No in-grown hairs, no cuts, not even skin irritation. I feel great, confident and look presentable on a daily basis. I have found that the shave time tends to take only a little bit less time than a wet cartridge shave, but the cost savings are already being felt. Saving on cream, saving on razors, saving on water! The razor has remained pretty much as clean as un-boxing day thanks to it's cleaning base. I am still using my first cartridge. I run the cleaning cycle every second or third shave and so far I'm very very happy with the results. I haven't persisted my use in wet shaving, the dry shave is really very nice and close and leaves my skin happy. If you are on the fence about picking up a Braun Series 9 shaver, I know the price is a little scary, and I come from a place where I got mine for free from BzzAgent, but if I didn't, now knowing about electric shaving, it's a small price to pay for a fantastic package of convenience and good shaving!

column14: If anyone would bother to research on how sunscreen actually works, you wouldn't buy this product.  This is what the honest writes on their website about the ingredients in the product.    Naturally derived, unscented, broad-spectrum (UVA and UVB) SPF mineral sunscreen - everything you need, nothing you don't   Easy to apply, non-greasy, non-whitening (non-nano!) zinc oxide sunscreen provides safe, effective sun protection for the entire family   Zinc oxide is the ONLY active sunscreen ingredient - NO synthetic chemical sunscreens   Water resistant - tested effective for up to 80 minutes   Shake well before use!   Hypoallergenic ‚Ä¢ Non-Nano ‚Ä¢ Mineral-Based ‚Ä¢ Biodegradable ‚Ä¢ Reef-Friendly ‚Ä¢ Water Resistant (80 minutes) ‚Ä¢ pH Balanced  Now did you see that the only Active ingredient is Zinc Oxide?  Zinc oxide protects against UVA. UVA is the longer wave light (ultraviolet light) that penetrates deeper into the skin. What about the UVB light?  the uvb light is whats giving you the burn!  now compare the product to the others with the chemicals in it that protect you from all and are a true broad spectrum sunscreen protecting you from UVB and UVA. what would you do?  id rather have the proper stuff on for a few hours than burn my skin. you're are essentially applying an assortment of oils to you skin with the Honest product Remember the day of applying baby oil?  just reading the Ingredients on the Honest product raises red flags period!

column6: Philips Sonicare for Kids Connected Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column14:
A couple of years ago, I bought a pair of Oral-B electric toothbrushes for my children. I had been using the same set for over ten years and have been pleased with the results. Unfortunately, they did not take to using the Oral-B toothbrushes and have mostly been manually brushing their teeth.

I was offered this Sonicare electric toothbrush and decided to let my younger daughter use it. She has crazy teeth (even worse than her sister who is now wearing braces) but many are still primary so the orthodontist is waiting for more permanent teeth to come in.

The standard size fits her mouth OK although we may try the compact size in the future. The Sonicare brush head design is superior to the Oral-B for keeping the brush clean. Both children have had some build-up around the brush area. I am in the habit of removing the brush head and rinsing it thoroughly, but they cannot remove the Oral-B brush too easily. The Oral-B brushes are less expensive.

My old set started having charging issues (understandable after 15 years) so I bought a new unit with Bluetooth capability. I tried the BT app a couple of times but did not really see the benefit and just use the toothbrush one a day, alternating with a regular toothbrush.

We have not tried the iOS app yet, but I do not really see the need. She knows how long to brush and since she is messy, it is better to avoid taking other electronics into the bathroom.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I was given a Crest 3D White Brilliance kit to try courtesy of Bzz Agent so I didn't have anything to lose or gain by trying it.

I have used several whitening toothpastes (Colgate, Rembrandt and other Crest pastes.). Compared to the other pastes I have used the pros:

The cleaning paste leaves your teeth feeling very clean. My teeth felt as though they had been flossed after each use.

The whitening paste is very effective in lifting moderate stains fairly quickly. After about 4 days of use I could really see a difference.

There is no harsh taste to either paste and didn't cause any tooth sensitivity with prolonged use.

Just a couple of cons:

The whitening paste is very thin and can come out of the tube very fast so be careful if you're brushing after showering or if you're in a room with high humidity.

In my opinion this is a paste that you could use to really prep your teeth for whitening strips but I feel like Crest's line of single system toothpastes clean and whiten as well (if maybe not as fast.)

column14: I was having severe eczema problems on the palms of my hands. Nothing was helping it, and I read somewhere that neem oil can help the symptoms of eczema, so I decided to give it a try. When the package arrived, and I opened it up and put a drop of the oil on my hand, the stench offended my nose immediately. This stuff SMELLS. I would describe it as a mixture of rubber and burnt peanuts blended together into smell. I decided to use the oil anyway, because I would rather have my skin problem treated. Even after one day of using the oil (very small amounts rubbed in well), I could see the change in my skin. The redness was going down, the itching was reduced, and my skin was hydrated. After about two weeks of continual use (twice a day, once in the morning, once at night) my eczema is GONE. Previously, my skin was so thick and callused, but now it is smooth, hydrated, and healthy. I cannot rave about this oil enough. If you have eczema, PLEASE use this, it will change your life. A bit of stink is worth the ultimate results.

column14:
I have loved Fusion Beauty Lip fusion for a long time. Fusion Beauty and one other high end company's are the two I always go back to when the other's don't work. I did knock this down to 4 stars only because I received it in a zip lock baggie not even closed. No retail box, no directions, but the tube did have a sticker seal on it. I know the retail one's always come in a box with a small pamplet of information and directions.

I have used it 3 days now and yes it plumps. No it isn't going to look like you had a professional dermatologist procedure done that cost over a grand, but it will work if you use it morning and night. I know the directions from using it before. it has ingredients in it to work instantly and give you a warming tingly feel, but the night formula also has more ingredients in it to work over night and pull on moisture and keep lips plumped up for up to 48 hours. Also has wonderful lip conditioners to help also fill in those lines. Reapply it during the day also, over lipstick it will still work. With this package you get both day and night formula in one package. It is a double ended product, with one on each end. It is a clear gloss and works over or under anything. I prefer it on bare lips nights, but over lipstick days.

column14: I officially used this today as I wanted to wear a dress to work without hose.  I have to say, it looks fantastic out in the natural light.  My legs look smooth and natural.  I put on three applications for each leg as I wanted to make sure I covered the entire area after moisturizing.  My legs look pretty good.  It doesn't cover every imperfection entirely, but it's nice enough to make a big difference in how I feel about my legs.  My legs are in good shape on their own but I typically wear nude fishnets during the summer to give my outfit an extra refinement.  This product does the same.  I see more dresses without hose in my summers.  I'm even considering trying a darker shade to see how it looks.  This shade matches my natural (Ivory with olive/yellow undertone) skin very well.  The key is prepping with moisturizer first.  I shaved after working out this morning, so I can assume that acts like exfoliating as some people have written about.  End of Day Update:  Okay, so it's now 4:29 and I can't believe how nice my legs look in the natural light that comes in my window at work.  I got so many "looks" at my legs today in a very nice way.  It literally looks like my skin!  This stuff is the bomb.  I'm going to wear dresses way more often this and every summer.  YEAH!  :-)

column6: Cellulite Defense Gel-Cream - Cellulite Cream w Caffeine + Retinol + Seaweed; Firming & Toning Gel - Use Solo or as the Perfect Companion w Massager, Brush, Scrub, Roller or other Remover Treatment‚Ä¶
column13: Improves appearance of skin! Retinol increases skin density to cover cellulite.  I have been using it for months.
column14:
This really worked for me! Before I tried this I was really skeptical that it would do anything to help reduce cellulite. I had been doing research to find something that would help with cellulite besides just exercise. I read several articles that described how retinol can reduce the appearance of cellulite. Retinol is converted into retinoic acid which stimulates collagen growth and makes skin appear smoother and denser. I looked at several retinol creams and Body Merry's cream had the recommended percent of retinol for the best price. I also noticed that other customers raved about their customer service and return policy, so I knew that if I didn't like it I wouldn't be stuck with it.

The cream smells like peppermint and spreads really well so a little bit goes a long way. After applying it my skin starts to feel really cold. Literally, the first time I tried it I felt like I was sitting on ice. Over time, the cooling sensation has become less intense (I'm assuming because my skin is more dense) but it is still prominent. I think this also depends on how sensitive your skin is (my skin is very sensitive). My boyfriend put some on just to see what it was like and he really enjoyed the cooling sensation. I usually wait for at least 5 minutes before I put on clothes to give it some time to absorb. I don't have a cellulite brush or anything like that so I just used my hands.

Overall, I have been really happy with the results. I must be since I have repurchased it two or three times now. lol It has left my skin looking smoother, tighter, and reduced the appearance of cellulite. Its not a miracle cream, but if you use it consistently you will see an improvement in your skins appearance. At first I used it daily, but now I use it two or three times a week for maintenance. Best of all, there is no animal testing and its made in the USA, which makes me feel better about my purchase. After all, true beauty is cruelty free. ;)

column6: Eye Cream for Dark Circles, Puffiness and Wrinkles. Reduces Fine Lines & Dark Spots with Vitamin C, Peptides & Alpha Hydroxy Acid. Minimizes Crows Feet, Puffy Eyes and Bags
column13: This tired mom appears more awake now!
column14: Lack of sleep is a huge reason I wanted to try this eye cream out. I am a mother of an infant (still nursing occasionally at night) and a toddler, so the "bags under the eyes" from limited sleep is almost a daily occurrence for me.  The seller contacted me shortly after purchasing this cream making sure any typical questions asked were answered.  I was informed that the product is paraben and papas free and has not been tested on animals.  It is 60% organic and 100% natural.  The moisture in this cream reduces dryness around the eye, which in return reduces swelling.  The aloe Vera helps improve blood circulation, also helping with puffiness and fine lines.  Although it is labeled as an eye cream, it can be used on the entire face.  I have tried this and it instantly makes my face look smooth and youthful. The cream is a nice consistency (not too thick and not too thin) and has a light natural fragrance.  As with many creams, a little goes a long way with this one.  You only need to dab a small amount around the eyes.  It absorbs within a few minutes.  It can be used morning and night and wears great under make-up.  I have found that after applying my tinted moisturizer or foundation after the cream has absorbed, my make-up looks more fresh.  And on the plus side, I don't feel like I need as much make-up under the eyes, since the skin does not appear as dark. This eye cream does make your skin feel incredibly soft and makes you look more "awake".  I definitely will continue using this as long as these ugly bags and fine lines stick around!  I was fortunate to have received this product at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.
