If you're going to be putting things on your skin, you should educate yourselves. There's so much information out there and the more you read, the better you'll get at wading through the BS claims. This stuff is the most expensive poison I've seen!

column14:

I've tried pouring a quarter sized amount into the palm of my hand and massaging into skin, but I've found that it truly does work best the way they describe (pouring on cotton, applying, and then rinsing). If you have issues with cotton pads due to the lint factor (my face becomes extremely itchy when I use those standard cotton pads designed for makeup removal) than you should try either the smooth lint free ones found at Ulta and the like, or the reusable cotton wipes. If you wear makeup you should remove it first, and their makeup remover/light moisturizer works quite well.

I also really like the finish on the outside. It's like piano gloss black. It wipes nicely, doesn't show fingerprints easily, and just reads 'high class'.

column13: An overall beautiful, solid body brush
column14: I purchased this brush to use as a wet brush in the shower. I needed the brush to be plastic with 100% natural bristles. The wooden brushes that I had been using were less sanitary because they absorbed moisture and weren't as easily cleaned. This brush fit the bill perfectly.  The first thing I noticed about this brush was the craftsmanship. The construction is very solid and the bristles are firmly rooted in the brush; if a bristle has ever fallen out, I haven't seen it. From handle-to-head, the brush is just shy of eleven inches long.  My first impression upon actually using the brush was that it was way too harsh. I had to be extremely gentle during the first use. With the bristles being so solidly rooted in the brush, there is not much give and the bristles don't move very much as they are being rubbed against the skin. However, I found that after the about three uses, the bristles gained more flexibility and I'm now able to use the brush with more force. After each use, my skin is left feeling soft and brand new. I do not buy scrubs or use any other type of exfoliation method. This brush is all I need.  My only actual complaint is the design of the handle, which explains my four-star rating. Because the handle is curved, has a groove going up the center, and is made of hard plastic, the brush can be tricky to keep hold of when using it in the shower. I have never dropped it, but it constantly slips out of position when in use and I have to adjust my grip on the handle so that it is tighter and the brush is in the correct position again. I can imagine that people with gripping issues or very small hands would struggle if used when wet. If the handle of this brush were more ergonomic, it would be absolutely perfect.

column13: Aawesome! Strongest I have ever used.
column14:
Wow! I received this package and opened the box, instantly I smelled it. I though "oh no, it must have came unsealed and spilled everywhere". I continued through the packing and the bottle was perfect. Wrapped in bubble wrap, then inside a small ziplock type bag, in a box with air bubble packs and a couple other things. The oil is just that strong I could smell it. The bottle was still sealed well and the plastic band around the top was not broken.

Rosemary oil has several uses, I use it for sleep, rest, anxiety, hair care, pet shampoo and conditioner. I instantly started a diffuser going with 3 drops lavender and 2 drops rosemary in the tank. It was wonderful, the entire house had a very light calming aroma. I add 3-5 drops per bottle of shampoo. It helps with dandruff, smells amazing, is very refreshing and feels clean. Helps with hair growth also and strengthens hair. I have very coarse curly hair and it needs all the help it can get for strength and moisture. I also use it in hair gel, I make my own out of flax seed, I have to make it every 3-5 days as it has no preservatives in it and I only make about a cup at the most in a batch and 2 drops works perfect in it. I add it to pet shampoo, it seems to help with dry itchy dog skin and the smell keeps fleas away I think, even though I have never read that anywhere. When this ad stated it was 3X stronger than other brands out there I would believe it after the smell. It is packaged in a 10 ML, (1/3 ounce) brown glass bottle with a dropper for ease of use. I have used lots of different brands of rosemary oil and by far this is the strongest I have ever had the pleasure if using. I will be adding it to lotions and other things shortly I am sure.

This label doesn't state how it is processed, all it states is manufactured by: Aviano Botanicals, LLC, Dallas Texas.

column14:
I have a very very tricky 3C/4A blend that is very very soft (won't hold curls) but also, has NEVER actually "absorbed" a product in my entire 36yr life! meaning products are usually just sitting on the outer layer of my hair and not doing a damn thing. I have had my hair in braids for about 3 years hoping that it would get a little stronger, longer, and grow in the places where years of weave wearing and over processing had made it fall out; when I finally took the braids out, my hair was SO Dry, brittle, frizzy, and dull that I almost just gave up and cut it ALL off!! But after a little research I heard about co-wash as a great way to condition hair and after all other great hair online hair suggestions I decided that the best kind for my hair "may be" a milk based shampoo formula. So one day at my local hair store (while getting SOoooOoo overwhelmed with all the different products that all claim to do pretty much the same things...but different, lol) I hastily settled on the Renpure Coconut Co-wash and after the very FIRST USE...there was a TREMENDOUS IMPROVEMENT!!!
One day I'd purchased one of those magic barber sponges with the hope that it could help give me tighter curls that would actually last; with this product you need to use a moisturizer on the sponge and I decided to go with a Motions brand product that, UGH!! Was SO disgusting and just made my hair super oily and sticky on the outside, I had thankfully bout this Renpure Coconut Milk Shampoo (simply because I was so impressed by the co-wash) and when I tell you that my hair has NEVER FELT SO CLEAN...Hun-tee!!! I can't even describe in words how well such a little amount of this product lathered up and cleaned my hair. I swear that as I ran my hands down the strands, my hair and scalp began to sinnnnnggg to the Heavens like little baby angels!!!! I followed with the co-wash AND... I had also purchased the Renpure Argan Oil Deep condition (I mix a few drops inside a spray bottle with water and while my hair is in bantu knots which I usually leave in for a few days, I periodically spray the mixture on the knots and line my scalp with Jamaican Black Castor Oil)... I took a knot down fora girl yyesterday to explain how hard it is for me to hold curls... that girl touched my hair and was in aww!!! She was like OMG!!! Its sooooo silky and soft! column13: I bought this product because of the great reviews. I bought it to use on my ...
column14:
I bought this product because of the great reviews. I bought it to use on my breast to counteract the side effects from radiation therapy for breast cancer. I actually looked at the very tiny label tonight and saw a whole bunch of chemicals!!! The kicker for me was "triethanolamine." This is what I found out with some research:

Triethanolamine is considered a moderate hazard ingredient by the Cosmetics Database, which notes as concerns. According to Cosmetic Ingredient Review, Association of Occupational and Environmental Clinics, and the U.S. National Library of Medicine, there is strong evidence that Triethanolamine is a human skin, immune system and respiratory toxicant. One or more animal studies show sense organ effects at very low doses, especially when used around the mouth, eyes and lips, and one or more in vitro tests on mammalian cells show positive mutation results. It has been shown to cause bladder and liver cancer, as well as changes in testicles. According to OrganicConsumers.org, Triethanolamine can cause allergic reactions including eye problems, dryness of hair and skin, and could be toxic if absorbed into the body over a long period of time. It can cause itching, burning, scaling, hives, and blistering of skin, all symptoms which may increase with higher concentrations (The Green Beauty Guide).Triethanolamine "should not be used in products containing N-nitrosating agents to prevent the formation of possibly carcinogenic nitosamines."

Needless to say, I stopped researching when I got this product, threw this product in the trash and I will be buying an aloe vera plant tomorrow. This chemical is not for skin!

column13: Great Eye Cream for Fine Lines
column14: I love this eye cream. My undereye area is a bit high maintenance. I have dry under eyes with fine lines that are genetic. Im in my late twenties and have always had issues with my fine lines. Most eye creams I have used will hydrate that area but it doesn't plump or soften the lines. I had fallen in love with Clinique's anti-gravity eye cream but they changed the formula. I've done research and used everything from Fresh, Clinique, Kiehl's, Burt Bee's, etc. I love Korean brands because you get a large amount of product for a good price. Most U.S eye creams are around 15 ml and range from $35 and up. Etude Super Moistfull is 25 ml and its around $20 dollars. So you get twice the amount compared to U.S brands. The product is very creamy and moisturizing and helps to plump up the fine lines. It smells great and is in cute packaging. I would definitely repurchase.

column6: Aveeno Ultra-Calming Daily Moisturizer For Sensitive Skin With Broad Spectrum Spf 15
column14: Been using it since I got it in the mail (few weeks now) so far it has cleared up almost my entire face from redness! I especially use it when am going out and need the sunblock. It leaves my skin smelling nice and smoother. I am sensitive to smell and if my lotion smells strong I begin to sneeze but not with this. It is nice to see my face finally clearing up without any dryness! It has definitely come a long way and this product is good for its price here on amazon. I might increase the rating if it finishes clearing up my face a bit more, I still have some redness around my nose but no longer elsewhere like my cheeks. When you apply it it does have a tan looking color but it is absorbed and leaves no residue if you apply it evenly. I might be a bit more sensitive then I thought because the first 2 times or so I didn't respond as well until continuous use I saw my skin clear up. Like I felt a tingly sensation not sure if it was because its new on my skin or something or if that is how it works. I recommend it but if your skin does not seem to take well with it after some use stop applying it.

column6: Highest Quality Peppermint Essential Oil - With No Fillers, Bases, Additives And Carrier Oils. Best Choice For Aromatherapy, Massages And Relaxation. Elrique Naturals Peppermini Essential Oil BIG 2 OZ SIZE 100% Gold-Standard!
column14:
I've been using a variety of essential oils for quite some time now, and I'm always eager to try new ones and learn about the various benefits of each and everyone one. I was especially anxious to try Peppermint Oil, because I read some time ago that it is great as a bug repellent. I initially bought a cheap version at a local store, and proceeded to put it around my house to "repel" ants, spiders, etc. I was so disappointed that it actually seemed to ATTRACT bugs!

Luckily I was able to try Elrique Naturals Peppermint Oil and let me tell you, it made ALL the difference! I put it on cotton balls around my house (especially in the garage and by the doors and windows), and it definitely works to repel bugs that are a major issue this time of year.

I was having a terrible problem with ants, but since using this I no longer have issues. I also use it in my DIY bug spray because my son and I couldn't play outside without getting eaten alive by mosquitos. This stuff is pure, natural, nontoxic, safe and extremely effective.

I also love using it in my diffuser for the relaxing benefits.

It is all-around a great essential oil by a great brand, and has a multitude of benefits. This will he THE brand of peppermint oil that I purchase from now on. It has been a lifesaver!

I received this product in exchange for my honest, unbiased review, and all thoughts expressed are completely my own.

column13: I was disappointed. I do have a clarisonic
column14:
After reading all of the reviews here for this product, and just hearing so much hype about Konjac sponges in general, I was disappointed. I do have a clarisonic, which I love, and I feel that does a much better job (and if you are constantly buying these, it's not really so expensive in the long run... ). I have had this for about two months now. I use it probably 2-3x a week in the morning, when I'd usually just splash my face with water. So it IS nice and easy, to quickly do a once over with the sponge, rather than washing it or getting out the clarisonic for a whole minute, etc. This should last 2-3 months, and I have only used it a few times a week (versus 10-14) and the sponge is starting to fall apart. So that is my biggest disappointment. The string is really handy and nice, but the holes where it goes through the sponge seem to be the starting point for sponge break down. Overall, I would use these for traveling when I don't want to bring my clarisonic.

Edit 1/26/16: After my original 2 star review, the company reached out to me to refund me, then never followed up. So I'm knocking it down another star due to bad customer service.

I did NOT receive this product for free, like many of the other reviewers.

column6: Beauty By Shea Raw Unrefined African Shea Butter
column13: The real deal, you can't beat this shea butter!
column14:
Shea butter has many properties and it is known to help reduce the appearance of wrinkles and fine lines. It quickly penetrates the skin to immediately protect and infuse with rich lasting moisture and it deeply nourishes and hydrates dry scalp or damaged hair which helps to reduce dryness and flakiness. I am very critical of products that claim to be 100% organic or natural, especially shea butter because there are so many companies out here that supply it.
Real, unrefined shea butter is off white/ivory to light yellow in color and will be a bit grainy due to its natural texture. This product fits that criteria and I am glad to have bought it! I even had my dad smell it (we're Nigerian) and he said it smells just like the shea butter back home! The shea butter came with a little tin to keep some in and I thought that was really nice! The product is very thick and is an off-white/ivory color with a nutty smell. Just how shea butter should be!

For my hair and skin regimen, I also use shea butter to protect and seal my ends to prevent split ends and I apply it on my skin to prevent stretch marks and fade scars and to moisturize my skin in general. I have an ample supply of shea butter and essential oils, so I made a few jars of shea butter creme and they turned out really well!

This product was provided to me at a low cost. All thoughts are unbiased and of my own opinion.

column6: Colgate 360 Sensitive Pro-Relief Slim Toothbrush, Extra Soft (Colors Vary)
column14:
I agree with "C. Borchert" - there is just way too much going on with the brush. The handle is too thick, it has an odd curve it it, and the rubber parts in the middle of the brush head are strange. I would have liked the cheek and tongue scraper, if the brush head wasn't so large that it made it difficult to use. Maybe I have a small mouth, but I found it difficult to brush comfortably with how large the brush head is. This resulted in the bristles pressing on my to hard teeth and gums, which defeats the purpose of a toothbrush meant for sensitive teeth and gums.

Also, I didn't even find the bristles particularly soft. Honestly, they weren't that much softer than those of the "soft" bristles on Target brand toothbrushes.

I have a Sonicare toothbrush that I use regularly (sensitive brush head on sensitive setting), but like to use a manual toothbrush sometimes. I think I used the Colgate brush about a dozen times before getting rid of it. I also tossed a second brush without even using it. I replaced it with a Sensodyne Extra Soft toothbrush that I found in my local Rite Aid (unfortunately, it is difficult to find online). It is perfect for me - a basic toothbrush with super soft bristles.

column6: Prima Cholesterol Test Strips (Pack of 25 pcs)
column14: You need the test instrument to use these. I bought the instrument but it took a couple of tries to get correct readings. Follow the directions, also the test seems more consistent if you fast overnight and then do it in the morning before breakfast.  The other important fact to remember is that you must use enough blood. Wipe off the first small drop then really push a good amount of blood out for the test. I find it also helps to tap the side of the instrument immediately after the blood droplet is on the strip. I now get consistent reading and the system works well. I gave it four stars because it's costly and the company doesn't offer different amounts, 5, 10 strips for example.  Before this I bought the strips you 'read' the color line on after a period of time. I found them inconsistent, hard to get accurate readings on, and basically a waste of time, blood and money.  I bought the Triglycerides 25 pack also so I could test my friends.  Rob

column6: Organic Tamanu Seed Oil and Treatment Roller, Pure Cold Pressed & Unrefined For Skin, Nails, Face, Hair & Scars by Pursito Foraha Nut Seed Oil, Certified Organic by ECO Cert ICO
column13: It's a different scent, but it moisturizes well and keeps mosquitoes and flies off of me
column14:
What interesting oil. It comes out greenish-grey and smells of a pungent herb, the smell which I can't pinpoint. Cardamon-basil-oregano? Patchouli?! It's a scent that takes some getting used to. The oil's color does resemble the olive oil served with Bruschetta at high-end Italian restaurants. It's not the scent typically associated with beauty oils, and not a scent I want in my hair. It's advertised as unrefined, so this is a more natural oil than a processed oil. Processed oils only create more allergies to the skin.

But it's quite different on my skin. Despite the unappetizing color of this oil, it absorbs quickly into the skin and it doesn't leave the skin oily or greasy,nor leave a greenish-grey hue, either. I really like how it works on my skin! My face feels soft. I'm also noticing that the mosquitoes are staying away, and these pesky flies as well, who just a few minutes ago were using my arms as a landing pad. Could it be they can't stand the smell of this oil, either? Have I just discovered a more natural mosquito-fly repellant?!

So, in short, this oil has a very unappealing scent but it moisturizes very well and it keeps insects off of me. I'm wavering between 4-5 stars.

I received a free sample in exchange for a review

column13: A Lifesaver for nail polish wearers.
column14:
There are so many reasons why I love the twist and scrub sponge nail polish remover by Cutex.
1. It's a lot less mess because it contains it all inside the container and you simply replace the container when you notice it isn't quite doing the job you want it to anymore.
2. It requires a lot less effort on my part, which I'm all about, because I do tend to be lazy at times. Simply stick your finger or thumb in the middle of the sponge and work it back and forth a few times. Once you remove it, it should be clean. I almost always put two coats on and this has been the case for me unless it was time for a new container.
3. No more cotton ball pieces stuck to your fingers.. or everywhere else for that matter. I despise cotton balls and look forward to the day that my toes will be able to have something like this so they became nearly obsolete.
I can't think of any other reasons, but in my opinion, the above mentioned reasons are plenty enough! Happy nail polish removing! Not as much of a chore anymore!

column6: Organic Self Tanner. Sunless Tanning Lotion In a Spray for Face and Body. All Natural Ingredients. Fast Drying. Odorless. No Fake Bake Look. Tan overnight. Get Light, Medium or Dark Tan. No bronzers.
column13: Natural color on fair skin.  Not orange!
column14:
I'm a beginner when it comes to sunleess tanning. I love to be tan but I can't tan naturally due to health reasons. I have never tried a sunless tanner before except Jergens Natural Glow. I read something about My Skin's Friend and after reading reviews and the 100%
satisfaction guaranteed policy, I decided to give it try.

I was very nervous to try this because I was afraid of turning orange so I started out on just my legs. I couldn't wait to try it so the first application I did in the morning. It goes on clear and it didn't stain my clothes, but I found that it didn't provide an even tan because it rubbed off in spots, like my feet where my sandal straps were and on my thighs. When I woke up the next morning, 24 hrs later, the color was excellent. I was much darker. It provided a nice natural tan look. My feet were a little splotchy, but otherwise it wasn't bad. That night I applied again but this time I did my whole body. I did rub it in around my neck after spraying it on and I only did 2 coats instead of three and I jave found this is the most natural even looking area on my body.

I have found the application fairly easy to do on my own. I am fair skinned and I found that after two applications I had reached the perfect shade which is probably the darkest I've ever been. I followed the suggestions in the other reviews to put lotion on my knees, ankles, elbows and feet before. My feet and ankles still looked a little orange. I tried wiping some off with a tissue after as another suggested, which I think worked on my knees , elbows and wrists. The next time I am going to cover my feet with bags. It's actually a better color as it's fading so in the futur I'm going to do less coats per application.

I does have a slight odor but I don't think it's a bad odor or strong. It smells a little like spices.

Overall I like this product and I will purchase again.

column6: Salicylic Acid 20% Gel Peel Including After Peel Neutralizer Facial Peel Contains Retinol Enhanced With Botanical Extracts Bearberry Tea Kojic Acid Vitamin C Mulberry Licorice. Perfect For Acne Scars
column14:
If I can give this a 10 I would. I always had hormonal acne around the chin line. it is controllable during winter - I keep it in check using lavender and tea tree oil. But come spring, when it gets really hot here in TX, pimples start out as little pustules then get cystic. The oils have no effect around this time. I woke up one morning in tears when I saw how scabbed and blackened my chin has become. I tried using the 88% lactic acid which is great during winter but during summer I get a skin burn but won't kill the acne. I was resigned to the eventuality of spending hundreds if not thousands going to the dermatologist because my chin is getting me so insecure. Then I read the great reviews about this product. I try stay away from salicylic acid as the commercial ones that I have bought that has 1 or 2% salicylic acid caused my skin to dry out and breakout more.

Since my chin area has been toughened enough by the 88% acid that I used to apply on, using a 20% acid stung me just a tiny tiny bit. I can bear it without having to wash it off. On top of it, I apply hydrocortisone cream and 3% Nadinola bleaching cream overnight. The first week, it was like the acne was getting worse, I was getting cystic bumps. But I kept on applying it nightly. The next week, I saw my chin start to peel and then I noticed no new pimples coming out the next morning. After the peeling has finished its course, I see a younger skin underneath and a lightening of my blemishes and acne scars. I am now on my third week, the acne has all but disappeared. Of course I get one big one here and there - this 109 degree Texas heat will force them out. But once I apply this overnight with the bleaching cream and hydrocortisone, when I wake up, the pimples have all but dried up. Then my skin will start tightening and start peeling.

I cannot thank you enough for giving me back my confidence. I had been piling up my chin with body makeup to cover up the blemishes prior to this justso I can show my face at the office. Now, I don't have to use as much foundation, I just need a little more lightening on the dark spots. This saved me thousands hence I ordered another one.

To those first time users of skin peeling products, please follow the instructions to only apply for no more than 8 minutes then rinse with water. I have been using skin peelers for more than a year now so I have tougher skin and can handle the acid sting. Those doing acid peeling the first time may get a bad burn so follow the instructions with the package to the letter.

column6: ToLB Vitamin C Serum for Face with Hyaluronic Acid - Anti Aging Anti Wrinkle Facial Serum with Natural Ingredients - Paraben Free, Vegan - Best Vitamin C with Hyaluronic Acid Serum for Skin - 1 fl oz
column14:
Packaged in a 1 ounce, brown glass bottle with a dropper. Ingredient list is as follows: Organic Herbal Infusion, Aloe, Vit C, MSM, Botanical Hyaluronic Acid, Witch Hazel, Vit E, Carbomer, 2-Amino-5-Guanidinopentanoic Acid, Ferulic Acid, Kosher Vegetable Glycerin, Jojoba Oil, Phenoxyethanol, Ethyl Hexyl Glycerin. I can not find anywhere it states the percentage of Vit C, but thinking it is higher than the HA since it is higher on the list than the HA. The Vit C is Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate since it is a more stable form of Vit C than L-Ascorbic Acid. Serums with Ascorbic Acid in them have a very short shelf life it starts oxidizing immediately and become completely ineffective in a few short weeks, if that long.

I used this one for 4 nights now and 3 mornings. It is a cloudy yellow in color, very watery, (normal for some serums), but the dropper makes it very easy to use a drop on cheeks, forehead and chin, massage in then use an extra drop or two in places that need more attention, around eyes or lips. If you use the dropper properly you never waste a drop. It left skin very soft, smooth, and glowing. I cannot say it has lightened anything such as sun spots. I do think it has evened out the skin tone where it was not even in places. It has helped with the firmness in my eye area and pores are less noticeable and appear smaller. I had no irritation at all, and have moderate sensitive skin.

After using tons of different Vit C serums over the years, (yes I am over 50), this one is at the top of my list. I have seen a visual difference in a short time. It takes at least a month to see any difference over time with any product, but some that do have any effect in just a few days for the better are few and far between and this one does just that.

column14: I received this 3D Fiber Lash mascara today in the mail, and I am in LOVE! column6: PurO3 Fully Ozonated Olive Oil - 4 Oz
column13: Helped Cure Demodex Mange on Puppy
column14: A homeopathic vet told me to use this on my 6 month old weim puppy.  She had demodex mange and it worked great.  My regular vet prescribed 6 weeks of daily treatment with ivermectin.  I did not want to use ivermectin and went searching for a new vet.  The homeopath veterinarian recommend ozonatied olive oil.  I was skeptical, but it helped clear up 4 or 5 spots about 2 inches around.  The spots were not looking good.  They were very red, flacky, and becoming almost raw.  Within 2 weeks of starting this treatment all the large spots are gone.  I also bathed the dog with DermaPet Benzoyl Peroxide Plus Shampoo which I also purchased from amazon. column6: Nature's Cure Two-Part Acne Treatment System for Females 60 Tablets and 1 Oz Cream
column14:
Regarding the pills: if you are prone to getting headaches/migraines DO NOT GET THIS PRODUCT! I suffer from hormonal acne around the chin and was hoping that this could clear it up for me. The first couple days I started taking it I saw my acne get worse, but that's often what happens when you start new treatments. I also had bad headaches every night, but because I get them frequently, I figured it was because I wasn't eating right or drinking enough water. However, I was getting headaches every single day since starting the pills. Apparently they have diluted amounts of arsenic in it, which is known to cause headaches. I saw all the good reviews on this product, and while I'm glad it worked for some people, it definitely doesn't for everyone.

Regarding the cream: benzoyl peroxide is known to treat acne, and it does work. It will kill bacteria and dry up a pimple that you put it on. There will be flaking and maybe some burning, but it does work. I think it would be better to just buy benzoyl peroxide cream from somewhere else separately instead of the whole system.

column6: SleepRight Dura-Comfort Dental Guard
column13: This was the first dental guard I had ever tried ...
column14:
This was the first dental guard I had ever tried and my first one lasted at least 6 months. When I realized it was time to get a new one, I figured I'd try another type of night guard since I had no basis for comparison. I tried two other guards by different brands, both of which required molding. I quickly realized that the fit of those tooth-encapsulating mouth guards drove me absolutely nuts. So, I went back to this one and when I have eventually gnawed it to death, I will be purchasing it again.

If you've never used a night guard before, you should expect some mild discomfort for about a week- by which I mean an annoyance, not pain. After that period, you most likely won't even notice it. Also, it has never come out of my mouth on its own.

column6: Significant Beauty Anti Aging Clear Skin Facial Serum with 20% Vitamin C - 1 Oz. BEST NATURAL serum ‚Äì Better than face, neck & eye creams or moisturizers for your blemishes, dark spots & wrinkles. For day, night, men & women - With Retinol, B3, MSM.
column13: Packed with all sorts of good for the skin ingredients!
column14:
I am trying out different serums and creams because my skin is changing as I reach age 50. I use Retin A which, for me, is an absolute MUST. But that isn't enough to keep skin looking and feeling youthful. I know Vitamin C is necessary and I absolutely love hyaluranic acid for its plumping properties. This serum has those two but so much more. They are one of the few I have seen with Squalene which is an amazing skin enhancer. There's retinol in here too but not enough to make it retinol overload with my use of the strong stuff. Salicylic acid is another really good ingredient for the skin that wards off blemishes and makes skin glow. Tea Tree is an antibacterial and also helps with breakouts and there is so much more in one little bottle!

I tend to use a Vitamin C serum, then a hyaluranic one, and then a good anti aging cream and eye cream when I am not using Retin A. (I use it every other night.) A lot of steps but it pays off. I tried this serum alone before using my cream and my skin felt firmer and also looked brighter. Most serums take a while to work and instant results, if any, are not astounding. But over time, the skin drinks in all the good stuff and your face will look smoother, younger, softer and more hydrated. I haven't been using this one long enough to tell you the long term results but so far I really like it. It is thin and absorbs fast. Not sticky or gummy. Doesn't stink. Doesn't burn or sting and I have sensitive skin. No drying of my skin so that it feels uncomfortably tight. Fine around my eye area which is ultra sensitive. And I see brighter skin and feel smoother skin on contact.

I really think,with all these great ingredients, my skin will look and feel better than it has after about a month's use. Maybe less. At this point though, I like that I immediately feel hydrated and soothed and my skin brightens. I am going with 4 stars ONLY because I haven't yet seen long term results. I will update in a month to let you know if this serum has changed my skin in a positive way or at all. I believe I will see even more improvement in my skin. With the ingredients in this serum, it's almost impossible not to. It has almost everything I could want in one bottle.

I received this product at a reduced price in exchange for my evaluation and honest review. I was not obligated to leave a positive review, just my honest opinions and the above are just that. I hope I help you in some way to make a choice because, if you are like me, you're muddling through the many, many options out there and just don't know what to try. column14:
I am not one to typically leave reviews for products, but this is amazing. I have been fighting my 7 year old, who has hair down to her rear end, each time we have to brush out her hair. There are always tears and yelling and it was never pretty. I finally decided to give this a try after seeing the commercials for it several times. While it was $15 dollars, I figured if I could eliminate half the fighting, it would be worth it.

I just brushed her hair with this thing (and it was a tangled mess after soccer practice) and she didn't flinch. I thought she was making it up, so I called her sister in who has regular hair. This brush is meant for fine hair, but I thought I would try it even though she has more normal hair than her sister (whose is baby fine). The other daughter didn't flinch. So, I tried it on mine. I have very thick hair. This brush worked with no problems and I didn't flinch. It is amazing.

Now, It did break hair still. There was a lot of hair in the brush when I finished, but honestly, I don't really care. I brushed my 7 year olds hair in 5 minutes with no tears or fighting. Well worth it for me.

This spray on nail dry is really the solution to this problem. I don't have to worry about running into things because my polish will be dry by the time I walk out of the bathroom! I didn't even notice when I bought it that it was scented, but that's also nice because it doesn't smell like chemicals.
It really doesn't require more than one quick spray over your hand/foot to dry the polish so this giant bottle will likely last me a year or more.
I can have cute nails and be productive all at the same time! Hallelujah!

column6: VLV Natural Skin Care Products - Best Vitamin C Serum with Hyaluronic Acid, Organic, Anti Wrinkle, Anti Aging, Brightening Cream for Face, Eyes, Neck and For Men and Women
column14:
How do you compare the hundreds of skin care products? As a regular tester, I've arrived at a list of key considerations. I hope these are helpful to you!

* Fragrance: Grapefruit scented, from natural grapefruit essential oil
* Feel during application: This is a medium weight, light yellow lotion. It feels wet and smooth going on.
* Feel after absorption: Moist, soft, very slightly oily. It produced a slightly irritated heat on my face; I have very sensitive skin.
* Is it best for a certain skin type?: Dry and normal skin. On my arm (normal skin) it felt pleasant. On my face (oily, sensitive) it made my face feel hot, was slightly oily and sticky, and made me break out.
* Is it tested on animals?: No.
* Packaging: 1oz plastic pump bottle; possibly an airless pump but I can't see inside it to tell. Pump is easily controlled and dispenses a small amount.
* Immediate cosmetic effects: Plumpens, reduces fine lines, makes skin look fresher and brighter. The cosmetic results are excellent and if this hadn't made me break out, it'd be a five-star product.
* Potential long-term effectiveness:* Vitamin C, hyaluronic acid, vitamin E, and the various herbal oils and extracts are all going to be excellent for your skin. I feel that while it would absolutely be better than nothing long-term, this be viewed as a vitamin C serum - not your entire facial care regimen - and supplemented with a product containing more active ingredients.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

I received this free or virtually so for product testing and review. I am under no obligation to provide a positive review and receive no incentives or rewards for doing so. My aim is to highlight features and drawbacks that I would want to know about as a buyer, not hype the product for the manufacturer. My remarks are sincere and my own.eview. column14:
I received these yesterday. Two of the ten rings were considerably flawed. One looked like it was factory damaged, and the other was missing a stone. I don't feel it's reasonable to complain too badly about minor flaws when I know the quality is going to be at least fair considering what I paid for them.
They arrived in a bubble pouch, but the mail handlers were hard on it and there was a hole in it large enough for the rings to fall out. I was lucky that didn't happen. I do think that the ring missing a stone may have been due to the handlers because there was crushed golden glass in the inner bag. I still think I got a good enough deal. column13: Loving my brighter, whiter teeth! Just wished it tasted better!
column14:
I got to try this product for free, thanks to Crest & BzzAgent!!
I have really enjoyed the Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing & Whitening System and am loving my new whiter, brighter smile!! This power couple totally works and is easy to use! The instructions are easy to follow, brush with step 1, spit, brush with step 2, spit and rinse and done. I like this way better than any of the strip systems I've used in the past, as I feel this seems less irritating to my sensitive teeth as the strips used to be. I'm a coffee/tea drinker and I noticed almost immediate results using this system. My teeth are so much whiter and brighter and that makes me happy! The only reason I gave it 4 stars is because I wish it had a better taste. Step 1 has some mint flavor, but step 2 straight up tastes like peroxide. The first few times I used it, the taste was awful, but I guess I've built up to it now and doesn't bother me quite as much as it did when I started using it a few weeks ago. The results make it worth it, and I've just tried to avoid getting step 2 on my tongue to alleviate the taste. Overall I'm loving this system and plan to keep using it!! I'm thrilled with my cleaner smile, and highly recommend it!!

column14:

I then tried the vinegar mixture before I applied the deodorant and that has greatly helped. However, I still have to use the vinegar solution daily, even after several months of use, or I still get the painful rash. I feel like the price is too expensive for the ingredients that are used. But since I don't want aluminum going under my arms, I am still using the product.
Frustration: Customers can only get a discount when ordering this product if they rate it 5 Stars in their reviews!!! Now I have to evaluate the motives of the company. Do they want honest opinions from the clients who purchase their products? Or, are they really interested in getting rave reviews to sell more We are involved in business and we would much rather folks tell us the truth rather than flatter us with words. So with that being said...the search continues for a less harsh product that can be purchased at a more reasonable price.

column13: Softer, less frizzy and more manageable hair
column14:
I swear when U had my daughter 9 years ago she took my thick beautiful hair from within the womb. Now she has the thick BEAUTIFUL hair that I once possessed. Uve tried hot oil treatments and vitamins and every treatment you can buy at the pharmacy, with no luck in helping rejuvenate my hair.
A friend of mine told me about howher mother always added rosehip oil to their shampoo growing up, which she now does as an adult. She has gorgous healthy hair, so I absolutely had to follow suite!
I've been using it about two weeks now. I add one dropper to my actual shampoo bottle, but I have also been doung weekly hot oil treatments (U just heat up two droppers full till luke warm and massage into my head andleave on about 30 minutes). So far i've noticed my hair is softer, less frizzy more mangeable. Im definatly goung to continue this regimen and hope the change continues.
The bottle size is great, compared to other smaller more expensive bottles ive seen. Its probably going to last a long time. The smell is soft and not nasy like other essential oils i have used. They even package it appropriately for long shelf life, so if you dont plan on using quickly it wont lose its qualities.

*I recieved this rosehip oil at discount for an HONEST review

column13: My dermatologist recommended that I apply this product under my eyes in ...
column14: My dermatologist recommended that I apply this product under my eyes in the morning and before I go to bed. After using this product, however, I have mixed feelings about it. On the one hand, this product did soften my fine lines slightly, it seems to include more natural ingredients than other products I have used, and it is one of the most gentle products I have ever used. If I ever get it in my eye by accident, for instance, it never stings, unlike Neutrogena Healthy Skin Eye Cream or Olay Regenerist Serum. On the other hand, it was only partially effecting at reversing my skin damage, like all non-prescription anti-aging creams, and I did not feel that the minimal results merited the extremely high price. I will not be buying this product again, but I would recommend it to someone who really wants to use a non-prescription, fairly natural, gentle product for very sensitive skin.

The Radha is still infinitely better than any other non-rosehip lotion I've used, but I'm suspicious that the effects are so much different than a competing 100% pure cold-pressed rosehip oil.

column6: Taylor of Old Bond Street Sandalwood Shaving Soap in a Wooden Bowl, 3.5 oz.
column13: Great shaving product which also brings back great memories
column14: Great refill for my Taylor wooden bowl. I originally started shaving, years ago, using the old Yardley of London wooden bowl (Gifted to me by my Dad.), but those haven't been available since the late 60s/early 70s. The Taylor bowls must be turned on the same lathe pattern though, because they are a dead ringer for the old Yardley bowls, except that they have a nicer sealing finish to the wood. I'd missed the Yardley bowls, and the resemblance is what first got me to try the Taylor's. I was very pleasantly surprised, and I am sold. The Taylor soap lathers richly even in our hard water, and I get a good, clean shave. The soap rinses cleanly, doesn't irritate my skin, and leaves a nice, mild, clean scent, which can either stand alone, or is subtle enough not to conflict with my aftershave. I saw one submitter complain about the rising price, but at one year's life per bowl, the current $15 price yields a cost of only a little over $0.04 (4 cents!) per shave. I'm pretty sure that the hot water that I use per shave costs more than that, so I'm fine with it.

column6: MelodySusie Long Curly Wig
column13: Great Deal for the Money But Could Be Better
column14: This is one of the few wigs I have purchased for everyday use. First things first, if you have never worn a wig before it can be tricky to get on. You NEED to use a wig cap and then you need to apply the wig over the wig cap and the wig latches with two clips at the nape of the neck. With that being said, this is a very cute wig but it doesn't look very natural. If you are looking for something that is going to look completely natural and for everyday use, this probably isn't going to meet your expectations. If you want a spare wig to use as a back-up for your everyday wig, this is a good choice. It is designed in a way that it will fit a variety of head sizes. With that being said, it is not a very "full" wig (meaning if you look closely you can see the weave of it against your scalp when wearing it). Is this a perfect wig that no one will be able to tell isn't real? No. Is it great for cos-play or for a quick stand-in or for emergencies? Yes. For the price you can't beat it. I can't see spending $400 or more on a back-up wig. This will do just fine. I just wish it were a bit fuller

column6: Axe Detailer 2-Sided Shower Tool, Colors May Vary 1 ea
column14: Welp, the title says it all. I'm puzzled as to why this review section is riddled with posts of people complaining about this scrubber being "too complex". For Christ's sake, you put soap on it and wash your body! Stop complaining about there being a rough side on the darn thing! It's there so you have a choice. If you don't want to use the rough, exfoliating side then don't use it!  Additionally, I see some poor reviews being given as a result of the product being too difficult to hold - another puzzling complaint. This thing is only about three inches wide so unless you're an oompa loompa or have the grip strength of a 98 year old woman with arthritis who bathes in WD40, I can't see how anyone could not grip this thing.  The detailer is a simple product with a simple purpose: a sponge for washing yourself with two different scrubbing surfaces for you to choose from. Stop over thinking things, people. Oh, and this thing lasts a damn long time and I love the rough scrubbing surface which is why I'm giving it five stars.

column13: I've had two of these quiet inexpensive dryers. The thing is....
column14: I've had two of these.  I like quiet hair dryers and I've tried three different brands. This is the best deal I think. The thing with the two that I've had of this brand is that they get a bit of a rattle/whirring after a while.  Like a bearing isn't rolling right or something. The fans and heat are working still.  The second one was used for about 150 hours before the loudness made it not "quiet" anymore.  The first one came with the noise right out of the box but it was low enough to be equivalent to my previous dryer, which was three times as expensive.  The second one was perfect right out of the box.  For the first time I heard how quiet these can be and it is pretty darn quiet. Especially at the low setting of course.  Real nice.  So, I figure from now on I'll make sure I get one that doesn't have the noise when it arrives (which truthfully me to me is a defect that slipped by the quality checkers) and it will be worth it to keep buying them.

column13: I've tried just about every toner out there to find the best, and this is by far my favorite
column14: My hair is naturally straight black (I'm half Japanese), but I've had my hair pure snow white multiple times now. I've tried just about every toner out there to find the best, and this is by far my favorite. While I wish the less damaging toners would work, the use of developer and chemical process of this one is what makes the toner really WORK. Personally, I prefer leaving the toner on until my hair is lavender and within a wash or two my hair is white. It seems that going to lavender first and letting it fade out gets your hair to a better white, while going straight to the color you want will simply cause it to fade a bit more yellow when it settles.

column6: Labeled Makeup Brushes Set And Travel Case - Professional Quality Compared to MAC Brand - Powder, Blush, Foundation, Liner, Eyeshadow, Blending, All Over Shadow And Concealer Brushes
column13: Give these a chance! You may be pleasantly surprised, I was!
column14:
When I *very very first* opened this package I was hit with uncertainty. After all, I have an extremely sensitive nose and I was hit by a plasticy smell. But, I reminded myself that these were synthetic brushes, still in their wrapping, and unwrapped the package and set them aside to air out for a day or so.

When I picked them back up this morning to test them with my makeup, I was impressed, The scent was gone, the brushes are soft, ferrules secure, and bristles lovely. The case is exactly perfect to roll up the brushes in and snaps securely. It has a light pearly sheen of a finish to it, and is absolutely lovely. These brushes pick up product perfectly, and don't shed, which is a huge plus. I have a TON of makeup brushes and am very picky, I have brushes in my collection from crown to MAC and these fit right in. They are inexpensive, so I don't feel bad taking them to a show or lending them out, and they work great.

There are four eye brushes and 3 face brushes in this set, and the face brushes come with protectors, which is wonderful, so that the bristles don't get bent in any way with cleansing. Each brush has its own pocket, and if there is one thing I wished about this case, it is that it had larger or extra pockets so that I could fit some of my other brushes in it. I like these brushes and they will go in my normal rotation.
I got this set at a promotional discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Eye Cream for Dark Circles, Puffiness and Wrinkles. Reduces Fine Lines & Dark Spots with Vitamin C, Peptides & Alpha Hydroxy Acid. Minimizes Crows Feet, Puffy Eyes and Bags
column14:
I have horrible horrible bags under my eyes, that often become dark and puffier with stress and lack of sleep. I've never had much luck when it came to eye creams as far as helping minimize the puffiness, but I was pleasantly surprised when I started seeing results after about 5 days. My once puffy dark eyes have now lightened, the puffiness has decreased, my lines are diminishing and my under eye looks smoother. I didn't expect to see results so quickly when so many products failed to help anything. This is a great product I don't think I could say enough good things about this eye cream, but I absolutely love it. The texture is very similar to lotion, the smell reminds of some of the lotions with light fragrances. It absorbs very quickly, it doesn't leave a tacky feeling after, and it gives a slight cooling sensation. I still can't believe the results I've already seen, I'm so happy that I finally find a product that actually does what it claims. I recommend this for anyone who suffers from dark circles and/ or puffiness. You won't be disappointed!

I received this product in exchange for my honest review.

column13: Great Product, Watch Out for Bottle Breakage
column14: I really enjoyed this cleanser while I had it, I'll explain the "but" a little bit later. So for $27.00 I think this cleanser is really worth it. You don't have to use that much to get a good bubbly consistency, so you'll have this for a long time. The scent is very light but pleasant, and from what I can tell it improved my skin over time with use. BUT-- please be careful with the handling of the bottle. Put it in a place where it won't fall. I made the mistake of putting it on my shower caddy and a few weeks ago it fell. I didn't notice any damage at first but the next night when I went to go take a shower I noticed that the bottle was leaking from a little hole cut through the plastic at the bottom. It looked like a hole that had already been in the bottle, and there was nothing on my shower floor that would've caused such a puncture. So I taped it up and all was well until the next week. The round, plastic circle that pushes the cleanser up had completely dislodged, and there was no way of moving it back. I was still able to use it, but each time I had to tilt the bottle upside down and shake it to get more of the product out. Then, yesterday I found that the tape stopped holding up and the rest of the cleanser in the bottle (about halfway) had leaked out into the shower. I'm pretty bummed, especially since I know I would've gotten a ton of use from what was left, but I guess it was probably my fault for not putting it in a better place. You would think that with the sturdiness and quality of the packaging, it would prevent those mishaps from occurring, but I was mistaken. Otherwise, it was a wonderful cleanser and I may buy it in the future.

column14: I want to start off by saying I am an avid Amazon buyer and I have never wrote a review until now. And I wish I could have gave 0 stars. Most recently was my 4th or 5th time ordering this serum. While the serum was en route I received an email from the company explaining an added ingredient that may change the color. But assured that it was a good change, in terms of additional benefits of the serum. Well, I went to put on the serum as I do in the morning, before moisturizer, as directed, and it is a terrible, confusing, disappointing change. The serum used to go on smooth and light. I noticed it was thicker but didn't think that was a big deal until 2 minute after I applied the serum and my face felt like there was a clay mask on it, extremely dry & uncomfortable. Then, I looked in the mirror and there was a VERY noticeable thick film on my face that looked like I had a chemical peel on my face. My face legitimately looked like I had put scotch tape over it. I can't believe that such a well-reviewed company, a company I gave my money to for a product that was by no means outstanding but wasn't bad until now. Truthfully, I've looked at othe serums on Amazon and this whole "review for free product" trend has really changed the integrity and ease of ordering products like this on Amazon. I just want a simple vitamin c serum that does what it says. Oz naturals - you just lost a customer.

column6: Razorock Mudder Focker Shave Soap
column13: Why this Mudder Focker stands out
column14:
If you're new to wet shaving or shaving soaps, please believe all of the reviews regarding Razorock soaps. The prices are incredibly low and they are very usable for beginners picking up a shaving brush for the first time. Don't concern yourself with performance or "lather-ability" at all, because every soap they make will lather very easily. Mudder Focker is certainly included in that recommendation.

However, even veteran wet shavers should take note that Mudder Focker (full disclosure: I ALMOST made a dangerous typo right there) punches way above it's price, and the point that I want to emphasize is that it does this more so than perhaps any other Razorock soap (not just soaps in general). Many of us shaving geeks have at least used some of the more popular Razorock soaps -- I've personally used XXX, Zi' Peppino, Don Marco, and recently Santa Maria del Fiore -- and I can confidently tell you that Mudder Focker stands out in a different way from any of the ones I've used.

I'm typically a fan of lanolin soaps for their enhanced post shave feel, but many of them make me a bit itchy in the summer time when my skin doesn't need that extra layer of protection. Mudder Focker (and what I can only assume is the Fuller's Earth ingredient) gives you something different. The post shave is notably more conditioning and softening than many other soaps I've used (vegan, tallow, or anywhere in between), but it doesn't have that feel of an "extra layer" on your skin that lanolin gives you. Your skin simply feels "improved" rather than over-protected or, dare I say, "gunked up" the way lanolin sometimes does. I've found this to be both unique, and quite preferable in the summer heat. In the category of post shave, Mudder Focker is 1 of 1; difficult to compare, and almost in a category of its own.

I think the reason that this soap has gone a bit under-appreciated is because the name and description can leave you scratching your head over what it actually smells like. Does it smell like mud? Dirt? Earth? Fock? A lot of people say "cologne type" scent, but you know that it was meant to remind you of a spa... so... cologne-type-spa scent??? The truth is that the scent is well-blended, so it's tough to just pick out distinctive notes. It veers slightly to the sweet side, with perhaps the easiest thing I can point to being a gentle vanilla or cacao. Very comforting and relaxing, but also blended to sit somewhat evenly with a slightly Earthy undertone (so slight that I only really detect it out of the tub), and sort of a citrusy aromatic vibe that comes out on top (which is where I think people are getting the cologne description). The scent manages to be a bit fresh and somewhat classic, while striking that vibe of relaxing and natural, probably much like the spa which inspired it. Think about how tricky it must have been to combine such elements: spa + nature + shaving... it's great how a bit of inspiration can lead you to some unique results.

I'm a budding fragrance geek w/ about 40 EDTs in my collection right now, and Mudder Focker had a scent unique enough where I didn't quite know what to pair with it. The closest thing in my collection turned out to be Dior Homme Intense due it's distinct powdery cacao vibe... although it didn't quite match up because Mudder Focker is slightly more fresh and masculine vs Dior Homme Intense being a bit feminine (iris) and intimate. So what was the solution??? I GOT THE MUDDER FOCKING AFTERSHAVE SPLASH!! So dispel any weird conclusions your subconscious may have drawn from the name, description, or the green cartoon barber who is now the mascot for this soap (Mr. Focker himself? THE Focker?). This scent is probably more agreeable than you'd expect, and was unique enough for me to get the matching aftershave to help carry the scent for several hours. There's not too many soaps that I'm willing to do that for, due to my EDT habit, but uniqueness is perhaps the greatest prerequisite.

Even if you already have 10 Razorock soaps in your den, there's a surprisingly strong case to be made for adding Mudder Focker to your stash. For me, it's going to be my protective summer time soap when I want to avoid lanolin, as well as one of the more relaxing scents in my den., but uniqueness is perhaps the greatest prerequisite.

Even if you already have 10 Razorock soaps in your den, there's a surprisingly strong case to be made for adding Mudder Focker to your stash. For me, it's going to be my protective summer time soap when I want to avoid lanolin, as well as one of the more relaxing scents in my den.

Initially I thought this set was too expensive, especially when compared to other clippers I have owned. Then, I realized that I must have bought, tried, and abandoned, enough clippers over the years, that I easily exceeded the price for this set. More about the price in a minute.

This Klipit set includes two clippers; one for your fingernails and a larger one for your toenails. Both are very well made (construction is stainless steel), and they are identical, except for the size. Many of the features seem specifically designed to address the minor annoyances that come with using such tools:

- Very strong, heavy, and solid feeling; this helps to control them during use;
- The hole for attaching to a keyring is not covered when the tool is folded closed;
- There is a small -- but very useful -- "emery board" built into the underside of the folding lever...great for smoothing rough edges after clipping;
- They come with a small, re-sealable, "zip-loc" plastic pouch for travel and storage.

I have always had difficulty with clippers slipping out of my hand during use. I put a 1" split-ring through the hole on each clipper, and slip my finger through it when grasping the clipper...making it much easier to control. The weight, smooth operation, and ergonomic styling of the clippers make it much easier, as well. I really appreciate that the lever does not cover ‚Äì and thus interfere with ‚Äì adding the split-ring.

By the way, both clippers fit nicely into the zip-loc case, even with a 1" split-ring installed on each.

column13: Sweet Perfume - Everything Here Re-Usable.  Love Love Love This Company!
column14:
There's nothing about this product I don't love. First, its a neat little unisex scent that is hand blended with organic essential and carrier oils that comes in a great little fantastic tin. Instead of alcohol base, its jojoba based. And then from there they've mixed bergamont and cedarwood oil to give you an earthy citrous scent.

The oil goes on non-greasy, soaks in fast, and leaves you with a fresh almost just out of the shower scent. The tin, while great for a gift, is even more fantastic to reuse as anything at all. Once the perfume went in my purse, the stickers got carefully peeled off the tin and I filled it full of bandaids to also go into my purse. Win win. I love a company that packages stuff that you can reuse and NEVER need to throw away.

The cute little perfume bottle? Re-usable. Just gently pry the roller ball off and refill with whatever you want once you get done with the LIVETART ESSENTIALS PEACE blend. However, just because I can reuse the bottle doesn't mean I won't reorder. I will. Small companies like this SHOULD be supported when they have such kickass items.

column13: Might work for you, but it didn't work for me
column14:
My skin, usually perfect, started suffering from blackheads and acne (no pus, just painless raised bumps) as of May 2015. Since nothing else in my lifestyle had really changed, I decided to turn to products. The rave reviews for this one convinced me to buy. It smells nice (kind of like oranges, albeit a little chemical-y), absorbs easily, is lightweight and leaves no residue. I've used it religiously for 2.5 months but it has done nothing for my skin.

The sheer abundance of active ingredients, especially for a "reasonable" price, strikes me as odd -- you don't see these combinations very often. Are these ingredients of sufficiently high concentrations and quality? Do they offset each other? If the mix is beneficial, why don't other companies use them?

column6: Dr. Christophers Herbal Tooth & Gum Powder 2 Oz
column13: 21 days of using this and is seeing little results
column14:
I purchased the two pack because they cost lest than if you would buy two for $13.49.

This arrived to my home July 22nd and I've been using it daily ever since.

Right now it gets 3 stars because of the slow results and the bleeding gum problem that I still have.

Ever since I was a kid I've always had a problem with one of my lower teeth. It becomes severely loose if I clinch my mouth shut. I'm 40 now and this tooth is still doing the same thing.
Back in 2001 when I had dental insurance a dentist told me I had periodontitis. So I got a root scaling done. Apparently that was only a temporary fix because I still have that tooth where my gums still bleed. I hate waking up in the morning with a metallic taste. I know it's gross but I will do a spit test and my saliva would be pink.

It's been a minute and I no longer have dental insurance so I've been looking for herbal remedies and I came across this b/c of the reviews.

First off, this does not have teeth cleaning properties so I don't know why it's suggested that this powder can be replaced with toothpaste.
I have a rechargeable toothbrush and this turned my toothbrush brown within 3 days. Who knows if damage has been done because loose powder have fallen into the crevices of the toothbrush.
I've tried to sleep with a gum pack on only to find the next morning there wasn't a trace of powder in my mouth. I swallowed this stuff sometime in the night.
A lot of these ingredients do the same thing such as: stopping bleeding, repairing broken bones, arthritic remedies, ulcer remedies. The prickly bark ash is the only thing that is used for teeth such as a tooth ache. Bayberry bark is not for internal use. Slippery Elm is for gastrointestinal issues, sore throats, and other things.

I brushed with this for three minutes and I saw no improvement. I then brushed my teeth and didn't rinse for 15 minutes and saw no change. I then left this on for 20 minutes and again saw no change. I then started rubbing this on my gums and tried to keep my mouth closed without trying to let saliva build for 2-3 hours and noticed some tightness in the gums where I'm having problems with my tooth. I'm guessing the longer this is left on the better the results.

The small gum area where my tooth is loose is still soft. I still have an occasional blood filled saliva in the morning.

This isn't a quick fix. It's a slow process. I still do oil pulling in the morning with coconut oil and comfrey root powder which has tremendously helped my on coming cavity. With this it's too soon to tell if this is worth the buy or not.

column13: First time I've ever used a product like this, and after the first time I wondered ...
column14:
First time I've ever used a product like this, and after the first time I wondered why it took me so long to get started. I've never been a daily floss orf always seem to get a little correction from the dental assistant when I go in for check up for work. After using the WaterPik for several weeks now I found that I floss with it every day and sometimes twice.

What is so amazing to me is how easily the WaterPik gets the small, sometimes larger than you might want to admit, pieces from between your teeth. Pieces of grizzle, celery string, and many other foodstuffs are easily removed by the pressure of the water coming from the system. The overall quality of my teeth has improved just from using this product. Of course, this is no substitute for use of a brush quality toothpaste. It is a great way to supplement those tools and I found an easy substitute for regular floss.

One thing that I didn't think I would use it and found it very satisfying is the massage option for the WaterPik. I use it a couple times a week on gums and tongue and find it oddly satisfying. I would strongly recommend this product for anyone that is a part-time flosser, and even those dedicated to the stringer tape would likely find this product of great benefit.

column13: Cruelty free with results similar to high-end products.
column14:
So far I am really liking this product. I especially appreciate that it is organic. Serums can be a really powerful tool if used correctly. I always make sure to wash my face really well before use and to finish with a moisturizer. I had an opportunity to try this for review purposes and it has a few advantages over other serums I've tried. The first thing I noticed is that the bottle seems more high-end. Every other serum I've tried has came in the exact same glass bottle with a label slapped on. This has a pleasant cooling sensation and makes the skin feel tighter (this is thanks to the witch hazel, I believe.) It's been FDA certified, so I felt safe using it. But the absolute most important thing is that it is not tested on animals. If you Google cosmetic testing on animals you would see immediately why cruelty-free is the way to be. Even the hyaluronic acid is vegan. An added bonus I've noticed is that it's starting to lighten some of my acne spots.

Really the only thing I'm unsure about is the smell. It seems a little strange, slightly medicinal. Others have posted that they love the smell, so this could just be my personal interpretation.

Overall, really impressive.

column13: Helps treat and improve skin texture issues!
column14:
I'm a woman in my mid-thirties with combo/oily skin and some hyperpigmentation. I have been trying several topical products recently to rectify some damage that came from adult hormonal acne (scarring, discoloration, etc.). This product has worked very well as a mid-step moisturizer, but I haven't noticed much difference in the way of correcting hyperpigmentation. However, it's been fantastic for treating skin texture issues (pores, icepick scarring, etc.), so I'd have to give it a big thumbs up! If you have maturing skin, I'd recommend trying this out to help treat fine lines and wrinkles as well. I use it after washing and applying a toner, and I finish with a moisturizer (if you're trying to aggressively treat hyperpigmentation, I'd recommend supplementing this with a high-powered spot treatment). It's also- just FYI- packaged beautifully. :) I always prefer that my products be dispensed with a pump versus a dropper. They're both a good way to precisely dispense product, but a pump doesn't constantly expose the product within to oxygen. Also, this is packaged in a silver-colored plastic tube (photos attached), which is my only concern. It looks awesome, but I'm not sure how the plastic interacts with the ingredients within (dark-colored glass is the ideal). The serum has a light, botanical smell that disappears after the product dries, and it is pumps into your hand without running off, while still easily spreading all over your face, even when your skin is dry. The consistency is PERFECT.

INGREDIENTS: Deionized Water, Sodium Hyaluronate, Aloe Barbadensis Juice, Phenoxyethanol, Witch Hazel Extract, Acrylates/C 10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, MSM, Potassium Sorbate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Sodium Hydroxide,Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Lavender Oil, L-Arginine, Retinyl Palmitate, Cholecalciferol

I gave it a shot anyways. I dabbed a little under my eyes and fanned it per other reviewers advice. It seemed fairly decent but in no way had the effect that I saw in the videos posted online. I was looking for that miraculous "de-puffing" of the under eye and ended up being underwhelmed.
I tried again the next day and used a little less makeup under my eyes and tried some on my forehead. Again, very underwhelming. I am in no way impressed with this product. It dried the skin under my eyes to the point I looked like I had wrinkles. I'm pretty disappointed. I'm afraid to try the other product for fear of similar results. Save your money. The only reason I gave this 2 stars was because the product was shipped in a very timely manner.

column6: Premium Sheets - Metallic Flash Temporary Tattoos - Gold and Silver Bling
column13: A Large Variety of Temporary Flash Tattoos to Add Some Accent!
column14:
I've been really enjoying these Metallic Flash Temporary Tattoos by Spaworks. I see more and more people with these on now, and I kind of understand the hype. These temporary tattoos are extremely easy to apply and they add some fun and shininess to your get-up. Just lay the tattoo over where you want it, and wet the back of the paper until the tattoo gets transferred to your skin. It literally takes 30 seconds. They also last at least 2 full days before starting to fall off (that is, if you shower everyday.)

I've been using these to add individuality and some uniqueness to my apparel. Sometimes I go to work with several of these tattoos around my arms, wrists, and a even a couple on my ankles and neck. I like using these when I go to parties or just go out in general. They can be used for casual and more formal settings, which is pretty awesome.

I like how this product comes in sheets of 12 (or more) with a large variety of designs, wording, objects, etc. There are definitely more than a few of the tattoo designs that I really like and wish there were more of and there are some I'll probably never use, but overall, I'm content with the variety. A sample of these tattoos were provided for testing and review. I am never obligated to give positive reviews, and all opinions are solely my own.

Well, as I opened the package yesterday the metal pieces started falling off their plastic hinges. I thought "It's probably because it's just out of the package". So, I reassembled it and closed it. Then today I wanted to put it outside for clothes to dry and as I opened it the small pieces from the bottom all came out from the hinges of one side. So, again, I put it back together, trying to balance it. And I closed it. And when I closed it those piece came off the hinges of one side again. And in all of this I hadn't even put one sock to dry on it.
Moral: I am not happy and I will send it back. It was pricy and not at all stable.

column6: Remington D3190A Damage Control Ceramic Hair Dryer, Ionic Dryer, Hair Dryer, Purple
column13: great price for a well made hairdryer
column14:
This is a nice basic hairdryer. We have a big family and own several Remington hairdryers. This one is in the kids bathroom. With its smaller grip it's a good size for older kids and teens to use. It dries hair fairly quickly, on par with most other dryers we've owned. We keep it on a command adhesive hook above the outlet to the side of the sinks. The cord has a good sized built in loop for hanging.

I was really happy to find that it comes with both a wide, flat nozzle for straightening as well as a diffuser for curly styles. My fancy high end dryer didn't come with a diffuser and it took forever to find one that fit. I also like that it has a cool button, no need to slide a button up and down to set a style with cool air.

My one complaint is that this dryer is a bit noisier than the other Remington dryers we have. It's not so noisy that it consider it loud for a hairdryer but if you're searching for a quiet model know this one is average to slightly above average as far as noise goes.

All in all I'm impressed with this hairdryer. It's a fantastic value at this price point. All our other Remington's have lasted years.

So I have been sharing my favorite Watts serums with all my friends.  I also take a lot of vitamins, amino acids & enzymes internaly as well. I am sure this makes a big difference too. column14:
[[VIDEOID:6caf69fe563ece4f1987f6623032f464]] As a rule, I don't usually review facial serums, despite receiving two or three requests a month from manufacturers.

After taking a closer look at the ingredients*, I agreed, and Petunia Skincare sent a sample.

It is hygienically packaged, remove the cap and twist the dropper on. As the video shows, the dropper allows you total control over the amount of product you use. It's also easier to recycle or reuse than a pump.
The serum itself has a slight herbal-medicinal scent. After application, it is not noticeable.
Smooth it on, going outward and upward in order to facilitate lymphatic drainage.

After a few seconds skin will feel dry and ready for the next steps...moisturizer, sunscreen, foundation.

This is a serum that is perfect for even sensitive skin, thanks to the aloe and witch hazel, and a host of botanicals.

*Ingredients:Deionized Aqua (Water), Organic Aloe Barbadensis Leaf (Aloe), Sodium Ascorbyl Phosphate (20% Vitamin C), MSM, Plant Based Hyaluronic Acid (Cassia Angustifolia Seed Polysaccharide), Witch Hazel (Hamamelis Virginiana), Vitamin E (d-Alpha Tocopheryl Acetate), Carbomer, Arginine, Ferulic Acid, Kosher Vegetable Glycerin, Jojoba Oil (Organic Simmondsia Chinensis), Phenoxyethanol, Ethyl Hexyl Glycerin, Gotu Kola Extract (Organic Centella Asiatica), Horsetail Plant Extract (Organic Equisetum Arvense), Geranium Extract (Organic Pelagonium Gravoleons), Dandelion Extract (Organic Taraxacum Officinale)

column6: Remington PR1285A R8 Wet & Dry Rotary Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Blue
column14:
This razor will do the job for the price, but don't expect anything fancy or extremely high quality. It's right where it should be for it's price point. It shave in both wet and dry condition, although wet shaving has always been a bit more difficult with electric razors and this one is no exception. The razor is light weight, contours to the hand well, and is easy to hold even when wet. While being pretty light is a bonus, it also doesn't feel extremely sturdy so not how long this will hold up in the long run.

The power button is easy to press for one-handed shaving and the attached trimmer is easy to open and use as well. Charging is simple and quick with the charging dock, and the battery life is supposed to last pretty long on this. The flex head definitely helps when shaving around the chin and jaw as it swivels to match the pressure/angle of where you're shaving.

Electric razors I've used never get as close of a trim as standard razors do, and this one is pretty much the same. It still gets a pretty good trim, but, as with most electric razors, it has a more difficult time shaving if you have several days of growth and also hurts a bit as it catches hairs at angles when they're too long.

All in all, this is a good shaver for the price point, and I'm sure it will last me for several years to come.

column6: Conair Anti-Static Boar Round Brush
column13: Don't buy! Contains harmful and unnecessary Triclosan
column14: This comb is coated with an anti-bacterial film called Microban, more commonly known as Triclosan. Triclosan contributes to antibiotic resistance and disrupts hormones, among other issues. This is why many companies are phasing Triclosan out of their products.  I think the warning sticker on the outside of the comb package is telling of the dangers of Triclosan: "Keep away from children. The thin film may cling to nose and mouth and prevent breathing." This is a big plastic comb, with no sharp edges! There is absolutely no reason it should be required to be kept away from children. And since when does hair need to be treated with anti-bacterials? How ridiculous.
