column6: InstaNatural Organic Argan Oil - For Hair, Face, Skin & Body - 100% Pure & Certified Organic Cold Pressed Argan Oil of Morocco - For Nails, Dry Scalp, Split Ends, Stretch Marks & More - 4 Oz
column14:
Now, many people say this stuff is amazing/clears acne/heals scars/raises your grandmother back from the dead.This is the REAL stuff...now whether it works 'wonders' for you, or just suffices as a moisturizer, may be up to your individually. Argan oil is supposed to be non-comedogenic (not supposed to clog your pores), so supposedly is unlikely to cause a breakout or clog pores. From my own experience, it has not caused any breakouts (I've had quite a while of use--by a different brand at first, bought at Whole Foods for quite a bit more money). I believe this is also the real stuff as the consistency, color, and slight odor are the same as the type sold in the aforementioned store. It has a slight odor--not 'fishy', not unless you've had some strange experiences with cod liver oil, though.
As for its supposed miracles... one can often read that this is practically magic, like 'women of Morocco use it'. Careful with statements like that--are the women of Morocco the most beautiful in the world with perfect skin? That has about as much meaning as saying 'women of the U.S. use it', and telling you to buy foot cream. FYI, not hating on Moroccan women--just giving an example. Just because supposedly another nation may traditionally use a specific product doesn't mean that product is the very best of the best.
For me, it's been decent...nothing too special. It does moisturize my face, but leaves it looking OILY, so I put it on at night after a face wash, and in the morning first thing out of the shower (quite a bit before putting on make-up). And I do NOT have oily skin--it is sensitive, but normal (neither dry, nor oily, nor with a t-spot). Great at night after washing the face...great as a make-up remover that can get that eye makeup off without hurting those with sensitive skin. Removes super long-lasting lipsticks easily. Leaves lips moisturized. However, you know what else can do that? More than a few other oils. Sweet almond oil has a slightly higher possibility of clogged pores than Argan oil, however I've used that as well (for about ten bucks for eight ounces). Then there's more expensive stuff, etc, etc. About using it on nails/hair/etc... you get the result of a good oil; you do not get access to the fountain of life and your choice of princess crown.
BOTTOM LINE: Buy the stuff if the Amazon price is within your price point and you want to try it; at this price, the 4oz makes as much sense as a small portion (especially since you can also use it as a body oil, etc). If you don't like it on your face, and it doesn't perform magic tricks for your nails or hair, at least it's a good body oil that you can use up.

column6: Crest Pro-Health Complete Clean Mint Flavor Fluoride Mouthwash 1 L (Pack of 6)
column14:
I would give this line of mouthwash negative stars if possible. I have always had a beautiful smile and very white teeth. I get complimented and asked what products I use all the time.
I never used mouthwash, but recently started couponing and the crest pro-health products were practically free. I began using the toothpaste and moutwash, thinking I was doing something good for myself. Within 3 weeks I was checking my teeth in the car mirror and noticed I had a brown halo on one of my eye teeth, right at the gumline. I also had a lower molar that looked as though it had been soaked in tobacco and coffee for years. I've never had stains like this. My tongue was sore, always felt burnt. My gums were bleeding for the first time ever and my teeth were sensitive. I didn't put 2 and 2 together until I googled "stains at gumline". Aside from finding lots of horrific articles about decaying teeth I stumbled upon all horror stories of crest pro health. I stopped using it immediately and made an appointment to clean the affected teeth. The hygienist noted the stannous fluoride and acknowledged it can indeed stain. After the most aggressive cleaning I've ever had, the stain is 95 percent removed. I can not believe a product meant to
Improve oral health caused such a potentially damaging side effect.
On a side note, I used a crest toothpaste with the plastic grains and one became imbedded in my gums. It looked like a blue spot. Fun times.

column13: Probably only best used on Coily hair
column14:
They claim that this works on ALL hair types but this is NOT true. I have a really soft (thick in volume but thin in texture), kinky/curky 3C/4A natural hair that is too soft to usually hold curls (my hair may actually be closer to wavy than curly at the the roots but I can comb or finger roll the ends at the 3C sections; the crown is a very frizzy 4A that does not curl as easily and puffs at the sign of even the most minute amount of moisture) I bought this sponge to hopefully give a better twist or curl to the section on 4C hair, however, this sponge literally took OUT my natural curls and made the hair strait! Lol
Because my hair is SOooOo soft, it was basically impossible for the holes to even capture the hair in order to twist it because the hair moves to easily (if in afro form I usually describe my hair to people as something similar to a dandelion; it's thick but blows so freely in the wind that you would think it's gonna fly off like when you blow the fuzz off a dandelion) I can only assume that this sponge works primarily and most effectively on on kinky/COILY hair. Kinky/Curly hair is simply too fine per strand to adhere to the holes in order to twist. I am not saying that this product does not work 'in general' but because it claims to work on ALL hair types, but doesn't... my 1 star is a result of false advertising

column6: Premium Blackhead & Blemish Remover Kit by Ch√©rir - Acne Treatment - 7 Professional Surgical Extractor Instruments - Extra Mirror - Cure Pimples, Blackheads, Comedones, & Facial Impurities
column14:
When I first got this kit, I was a bit intimidated by all of the tools, however once I got to reading about how to use them I became impressed. There are six dual ended blemish removers and a mirror. The tools are stainless steel and are safe to use when removing blackheads or pimples as they are designed specifically for this and approved by estheticians. If you have ever popped a pimple, you know it can not only get pretty gross, you also risk the chance of causing a scar. With this set you can safely remove those unwanted blackheads with no risk and are basically getting 13 tools for the price of one.

I really like the case as it is a pretty royal blue and zips up so the tools not only stay clean, but it is discrete as well. Each tool is securely held in place by elastic bands so you do not have to worry about them falling out when you open the zipper.

I never thought that at almost 35 years old I would be dealing with any type of acne, but with my hormones constantly changing I am grateful I can now safely deal with these issues without causing harm or scars to my body. I am thankful I was given the opportunity to test and review this item for free.

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column14: This is a very effective product, but with some major drawbacks.   This is a very soft stick - I don't understand how other people apply this - it is a bit firmer than peanut butter.  If it sticks out of the applicator more than 1/8" it comes off in clumps or the whole stick breaks off.  I always end up rubbing it in by hand and that is definitely not what I want to be doing.  It is hard to wash off your hands after that.  If you have it sticking out a just a tiny bit (so it doesn't break or clump off) you are rubbing the sharp edges of the applicator tube against your underarm.  My house has central AC so it is not too hot here... The other issue is I tried this product along with two other natural deodorants - and used it up 2-3 times as fast. It is very hard to use just a little bit - even though that might be all you need.  maybe this is easier for those with shaved underarms where the hair doesn't grab it and make it so difficult to apply.  For me the cost of using this would be unacceptable. It did seem to work well - if you can figure out how to apply it in a thin film that would maybe resolve both issues.

column6: Biotene Sensitive Toothpaste, 3.5-Ounce Tubes (Pack of 6)
column13: The Best Sensitive Toothpaste No Longer Available
column14:
Biotene Sensitive Toothpaste was by far the best toothpaste on the market for sensitive teeth. It doesn't have the cool mint in it which burns the lips and mouth, whiteners, and all the things that people with sensitive teeth do not need. And the taste was wonderful. Even a child would love it. I have tried what is probably the leading toothpaste for sensitive teeth, and it is much too harsh for me. I have had the same experience with another toothpaste which has come on the market for sensitive teeth. I would have used Biotene's Sensitive Toothpaste for the remainder of my life. I suppose the dentists did not tell the public much about it, so the company, to my sorrow, discontinued the toothpaste.

I don't know if it's okay to mention a brand name, but my dermatologist has placed me on Tom's of Maine toothpaste because other toothpastes contain so many ingredients that burn my mouth and lips. I use Tom's of Main Sensitive Toothpaste.

column6: Allay Aromatherapy Essential Oil Diffuser
column13: Great diffuser! One of the best I've gotten!
column14:
Great diffuser! One of the best I've gotten!

I was actually surprised at how large this diffuser was when I got it and opened the box. I've gotten a few products from ZAQ and they are all of great quality. They offer this Allay diffuser in three colors which are blue, orange, and pink. Some diffusers change colors, but this one one is lit with an interior LED light, which only lights up the top of the diffuser whichever color you purchase.

The water reservoir holds about a small dixie cup full of water. There's a water line inside the reservoir so you don't over-fill it. Filling to the fill line will allow the diffuser to run for several hours. Once you have added water, you then put in your essential oil of choice. You then have to put the first water-cover on, then the top cover. Press the button on the front of the diffuser and it will start diffusing! If you press it a second time, the light will turn off, but it will continue to diffuse. Press a third time, and the diffuser will turn completely off.

column6: Perfekt Matte Body Perfection Gel Tan 3 fl. oz
column13: Phenomenal product, nothing else like it!
column14: Wow, I was pleasantly surprised by this product!  I am extremely fair-skinned and do not tan.  In the summer I usually use self tanners but really don't like how they smell.  Also, you have to wait several hours for them to "develop" and you never know what color you're going to get or if it will be blotchy until it is too late.  This is a WONDERFUL alternative to self-tanners.  When it comes out of the tube it is super dark and it looks like it will be a disaster, but once on your skin it gives you just the right amount of gorgeous color!  A little goes a long way.  Very important not to moisturize before using this or it will slide right off.  Believe it or not, the gel consistency makes your skin silky and soft and this is all you need for moisture.  I use it mainly on my legs to give them color when I am wearing shorts or a dress, although I have used it on my arms and decollete as well.  I do have some spider veins and freckles on my skin and it does not cover them up, but does go a long way to even out the tone and they are not nearly as noticeable.  Color is very natural, not orange or reddish, just a nice, neutral brownish tan.  Does not rub off easily, however I would not wear anything white - I wouldn't wear white with a self-tanner either so no difference there.  This will be my go-to instead of self-tanner from now on!

column13: Wish it had a dropper, but otherwise..love it!
column14:
This is a large bottle, much larger than what most essential oils are sold. This one however, does not include a dropper so using it can be a challenge. It is easy to spill if you are not careful.

Peppermint is definitely a flavor that I find in items from all over the world. From baked sweets and candy to medicine, potpourri, and soaps, it is found all over the store and inside our homes. Needless to say, I have a bottle of 100% pure Peppermint Oil on hand at all times, because of it being so versatile and handy!

I think that when people are starting to learn and try essential oils that peppermint oil is one of the first ones most people try. The first time it was suggested to me was when I was feeling sick to my stomach at a conference and I didn‚Äôt want to leave and miss the speaker. A friend of mine put a few drops in my water and within a few minutes of drinking it, my stomach felt better.

I‚Äôve also had some success with it treating my headaches, making my own natural toothpaste, sore muscles and of course in my kitchen!

Now, it is definitely a strong oil and a little goes a long way! Plus, if you have sensitive skin, you should definitely put it in a carrier oil (like coconut or almond oil) first so you avoid any skin discomfort. Plus by adding it to the carrier oil, it helps prevent evaporation.

Whether you are brand new to essential oils, use them for your cooking and baking, or are looking for ways to replace harmful products with all natural homemade ones, then I‚Äôd definitely recommend you try the Peppermint Oil.

I'm a natural redhead (as in, I've never colored my hair, ever) and I'm now just a little closer to strawberry blonde than I would like, so I bought this color and the Warm Spice. It definitely adds red to the point that I see why people are saying it's pink. It's not a very natural orange-red, definitely more artificial looking. column6: Sulfate Free Argan Oil Shampoo and Conditioner: Sodium-Chloride-Free, Alcohol-Free, Paraben-Free, Natural Sun Protection and Highest Salon Quality Pure Ingredients with 12 Plant Extracts.
column13: I just don't understand all the 5-star ratings.
column14: I'm not sure what has prompted all of the rave reviews except that the company contacts you and asks for reviews and feedback. Seems that customer service on these products would be very good--the company is eager to please. As for the products, I'm not wowed. My hair isn't remarkably softer, more manageable or less frizzy than usual. Maybe a little bit, but I'm not sure, so it's not better enough that I would put up with the sickly sweet perfume of this shampoo again by re-purchasing. I know we were warned about the smell...that it smells like creamsicles...but it's even sweeter than that. Like creamsicles dipped in orange-blossom honey. It just can't be natural--other argan-oil hair products at my local natural foods store don't smell like this. Luckily, the odor doesn't cling too strongly on your hair after the fact.  Also, my head has been itchy, which happens when I use conventional shampoos but not when I use more natural ones. All in all, I much prefer the natural ingredients and scents of products such as Shikai, Avalon, and Acure's argan oil shampoo/conditioner (though that left my dry hair a bit heavy/greasy), and the rich but sulfate-free lather of Shikai.

column6: Redken Shades EQ Equalizing Conditioning Color Gloss 09NB Irish Creme,2 fl oz
column14: I mixed this shade with 9V in equal parts in an attempt to tone down the ugly golden tones in my color treated blond hair.  I wanted a warm neutral outcome not an ashy one and adding in 9NB was the perfect call.  I used a clarifying shampoo and a light conditioner and then applied the color mixture to damp hair.  I left it on for about 8 minutes the first time, checking in the mirror every two minutes, until I saw that the overly golden tones had disappeared.  I then rinsed well and used a moisturizing conditioner.  I'm happy to report that my hair came out exactly how I wanted.  The ugly golden tones were neutralized and I had a nice warm neutral blond shade.  If I had used 9V alone, the outcome would have been far too ashy and cool.  The addition of 9NB was the perfect call.  And my hair was really soft and shiny, with no damage whatsoever.  This is the first time I used Shades EQ so I was understandably nervous.  But it was easy to apply and comb through and I watched the effects very closely.  I'm hoping it will last a few weeks.  I use a sulfate free shampoo and try to wash my hair as little as possible, which keeps my color fresh and bright longer.  If you want to get rid of ugly golden tones but don't want an ashy outcome, then I suggest you try 9NB + 9V.  I got this recommendation from the hair board on makeupalley.com.  Those girls really know their stuff!  It was the perfect remedy for me.  I highly recommend this shade and this formula.  I also recommend Shades EQ in general.  My hair is in super great condition too.  I will definitely keep using this product.

column14: A very interesting face wash to say the least. It does not exactly lather, which I prefer going into my 30's. There is an overall tightening sensation while the wash is on, but you're left with a comfortable cushiness that's very agreeable with my skin after you rinse. While I usually enjoy a good double cleansing, waiting around for 5 minutes may not always be efficient. Also, the product while natural, is very strong so daily use for some may be too much. I've opted to use this as a pick me up facial 2-3 times a week rather than a daily wash. I've seen improvements on texture and clarity, but beware, you may experience an initial "purging" phase in the beginning because it's digging deep to get all the gunk out.

column14:
I'm not the type to wear makeup everyday, but when I have a nice event to go to or an important meeting at work, I like to be able to look my best, and this Geoge concealer set is a great addition to my makeup set to help with this goal. I love the huge range of shades included, so there is something not only for any skin tone, but also darker and lighter shades so that during the summer when I get a bit of a tan, there is still a shade that can perfectly match my skin. I also can blend together multiple colors, since any person's skin in reality is not a single color, so this gives a much more realistic look. I also really like that there are the light green and pink shades, which are great for evening out blemishes and dark spots. I've used the green one already for some reddish spots on my face and wow it does a great job of neutralizing it to a more natural skintone. The texture on this is really nice - very creamy and easy to blend into my skin. I know that I'll be getting a lot of use from it for a long time to come!

column13: It is working well for me. UPDATED!
column14: all I hate going to the dentist. I have had very few good experiences and haven't been in years because of intense anxiety. I have been looking for something to help remineralize my semi-translucent teeth. After much research and some convincing reviews I decided to try Uncle Harry's. I purchased the remineralization kit and have only used it a week, and already I see positive results. My teeth are much whiter and are less translucent. I experienced some sensitivity in the first few days, it did pass and I have no issues with pain or discomfort. The flavors are intense and "herby" but not unpleasant. My mouth and teeth feel noticeably cleaner, and my breath stays fresh all day long no matter what i eat. I will never go back to traditional toothpatste. I will update this review after I finish the kit.  UPDATE I have finished the majority of the kit. I still have lots of the tooth powder left, it will probably take me a couple months to finish. The mouthwash ran out first and there is a noticeable difference without it. My breath just didn't feel quite as fresh as when I was using it. I will be repurchasing the large bottle ASAP. My teeth and mouth still feel very clean, I also noticed that some hard plaque I had behind a tooth has shrunk in size. If I do purchase a mineralization product I am leaning towards the powder instead of liquid, I believe the powder form will last longer. These products have EXCEEDED my expectations.

column6: Philips Norelco HQ8 Dual Precision Replacement Heads
column14: I ordered these replacement blades for my 4 year old Norelco and they came in a ridiculously short amount of time. The blades are great, I think, but with the new blades I've been getting a lot of razor rash especially in the area under my chin. Apparently it takes a while for your skin to get used to the new blades, but the rash was really bothering me, so I went to the internet looking for a solution.    I found online that the rash was really avoidable if I exfoliated my skin a couple of times a week to get rid of dead skin and bacteria, and exfoliating also gives you a much better shave. I figured it was worth a try, so I ordered this[[ASIN:B00U1J83SQ TreeActiv Anti Acne & Rosacea Treatment Sulfur Mask Plus Rhassoul, Bentonite Clay Mask with Witch Hazel & Aloe Vera - Refreshing Lemon Scent (1 Jar) (4 Oz)]] online, and whoa--it worked really well. It felt a little funny at first to use such a thick cream on my face, but it really helped make my shave so much smoother and I also was able to get rid of some of the painful razor bumps that I get every so often on my face.    I definitely recommend changing your blades more often than 4 years in between, and just in general it helps to exfoliate your face a few times a week for super smooth shaves that you will have to do less of. Also, I use [[ASIN:B00LFT0CEO TreeActiv+ Tea Tree Oil Acne Solution for Advanced Acne Treatment - All Natural Acne Spot Treatment - Blemishes Gone or Your Money Back! (60ml)]]to clean my razor, apparently it works better than anything else in preventing dullness of the razor, and its good for keeping your razor in good shape.

column6: pureSOL Konjac Sponge - Original - Body Sponge, 100% Natural Sponge, Eco-friendly - Gentle Exfoliating Sponge, Deep Cleansing, Good for Sensitive Skin
column14:
This wonderful exfoliating sponge is made from the root of a Japanese plant: %100 pure, vegan, and cruelty-free (BIG PLUS!).
It feels hard and rough when you first touch it, but allow it to soak up water and it becomes soft, pliable, and nearly doubles in size.
It gently exfoliates the skin without causing scratching or redness. While soft enough for face and neck, it also works well on elbows, heels, and feet. Excellent for those, like me, that have sensitive skin.
The pureSOL Konjac sponge comes with a small suction cup so can hang it up and allow it to dry. Rinse any soap out of it first to keep it clean.
This sponge is eco-friendly and may be safely disposed of when it has served it's purpose.
For myself, I prefer the sponge to a loofah (which may be too rough) or a washcloth.
I received this sponge for the purpose of review. All opinions are my own and based on my own use of and experience with the item.

column6: GRAVE BEFORE SHAVE Gentlemen's Blend Beard Balm (Bourbon Scent)
column14: Love this beard balm!  Contrary to what another reviewer (jokingly I think) writes, it does not smell like alcohol, nor will you smell like an alcoholic using it.  The scent is more like others have described it being more of a manly cologne scent with hints of sandalwood. Just manly, musky, and cool.  The scent also subtlety sticks with you throughout the day, especially if you are in the habit of contemplatively stroking your beard every once in while like all cool bearded gentleman do.  And although I like the scent, what I love most about this balm is how it works!  It's fabulous.  It goes on smooth and is quickly soaked up by my beard.  Other balms I have tried leave my hands and beard greasy; not this one.  It makes my beard soft and smooth.  I also like the hold it gives as it tames and helps me to style my beard the way I wish, especially my mustache. I also have to say I am impressed with the company: from the branding, the products I have tried so far (Original and Gentleman's beard balm), their customer service, their employees, and the overall edgy, cool vibe that Fisticuffs/Grave Before Shave has,  I'm a huge fan!

column14:
I've used glass nail files before. These are by far my favorite. They're thinner than other files, but still incredibly durable. I love that they're double-sided! Allows me to file down all of my nails before needing to clean the glass.
(Note: cleaning just means running water over the file. Definitely not a hassle)

The etching is deep enough that it gets the job done efficiently, without ripping or damaging my nails (as far as I can tell) to the point where I don't even bother clipping my fingernails anymore. I just file them to a satisfactory length.

I haven't really figured out what to do with the "manicure" file with the edged point, but that's fine. Mostly it just sits unused.

The carrying cases are plastic, but are sturdy enough to protect the files from damage as long as you don't drop anything heavy on them. My boyfriend has claimed the small one and carries it in his pockets without issue.

All in all, highly recommend.

column13: Fantastic product, heals fast and minimizes peeling!
column14:
Very pleased! This is my first tattoo and I knew only what I read online about tattoo care (plus some recommendations from friends on using Aquaphor. My tattoo artist recommended Hustle Butter and after reading the reviews here, I was sold. I used the product 3-4 times a day for the first three weeks of my tattoo. As far as peeling, around the third day I started peeling but it only lasted 1-2 days and just in small bits. I also never had a second peal which I had read was normal, but not having the second peel is apparently normal with Hustle Butter! Also, I have sensitive skin and eczema, but had no negative reaction to Hustle Butter (which was a concern).
I admit, I'm new to tattooing and have nothing to compare to, but I would definitely use Hustle Butter again if I ever get some more work done!

column6: Waterpik Complete Care Water Flosser and Sonic Toothbrush
column14:
Came in nice packaging; items were well protected.

Includes a carrying case for two brush heads and the main brush itself. The main machine has the floss attached and a little brush/tip container that allows air flow to enhance drying. The two clear glass parts are detachable for washing.

The long power cord can be crammed into the bottom of the base to hide and then run through a small cut out at the bottom so it stays in place at any customized length you want.

The floss pressure gets pretty high actually and the pressure works pretty well. The one problem I had was that the machine itself is loud. Really loud. On the level of my phone on vibrate while sitting on a tin surface. This is only while using the floss stick. I'll probably only use it in the mornings.

With that said, I have awful dental habits. The main issue being I'm crazy CRAZY LAZY. The best part of this set is that the toothbrush feels wonderful on my gums. It's almost like a massage and the bristles really clearing out between my teeth. The floss water does get in-between my teeth really well and it feels refreshing. Surprisingly, it really does give you the feeling of going to your dentist... without the gross gloves smell and sharp objects.

The many heads of the floss really motivates me to try each one. I'm genuinely excited to brush and floss... like a weirdo...

Used only one day. Will update if anything goes wrong. If you see this review years from now, it's because it still works like a charm.

column14:
Considering that I am a man and that my ears are not pierced, I had to ask my wife for assistance. So, here is my review as filtered through her:

They are really beautiful, and she got compliments on the first day she wore them. They are two toned, which fits the style of the other jewelry she owns. She likes everything about them, except for one thing: the stud is not set in the center of the earring, which means when it is in ear, they rotate around the non-centered axis. This means that they angle down a bit more than she would like. When we examined the earring, there seems to be no reason as to why the stud was welded in any place other than the center. I do not want to label it as poor craftsmanship, but it would solve the problem of the earring rotating on its own.

She said that she got used to this and she still likes wearing them. They have made a nice addition to her collection.

column14: The picture doesn't do these earrings justice, they are gorgeous !  I recently discovered this brand and have been crazy about it ever since, they are not huge or heavy, very well made, and the fact that they are lever back instead of hooks, that are easily lost, is another plus. The crystal at the very top is the color of London blue topaz, the next crystal is a red bugle bead, under that are two gold colored beads, the largest stone is not purple as it looks in  the picture its a garnet color with a sort of borealis affect that can reflect a variety of colors including orange. The tiny crystals in the "V" formation are the color of rich peridot. If you love vintage jewelry you most definitely won't be disappointed purchasing these earrings, they are wonderful. They were also packed very well and arrived as expected. Thank you Amazon and please bring in more styles and the necklaces to match !

column13: This charm is so beautiful to me!
column14:
This charm is absolutely beautiful to me! It is made of Opals and Swarovski Crystals. It has a 4.5 cm core and is 10mm x 8mm.

This charm is meant to fit Pandora and other 3mm bracelets. I wore it on a necklace chain though and I really loved to use it that way! It matched really well with a shirt I wore when I spent time with coworkers during a recent work trip. During my trip, I would look in the mirror sometimes and see the charm. I had thoughts like "That is beautiful!" and "That looks really nice with my shirt". In my opinion, the pink, white, and blue colors really blend well together. I think it will match well with most (maybe all) pink, white, and blue wardrobe (top) colors. When I took off my necklace chain with this charm on it, I tucked it away in a jewelry bag to make sure I didn't lose it because I love it so much!

column13: Great design, poor execution. Otherwise I would love this shelf.
column14:
I really like this shelf, but the quality of construction is lacking. At least on the one I received. The welds aren't made very well, and on one side the front corner of the shelf is missing the weld completely so it's just floating there not connected. It still works, but it's very obvious that it's got a missing weld right in the front there. And I would never expect it to be able to support handbags or anything heavier than jewelry and hair accessories. The shelf on top seems sturdy enough, I've got nail polish and some perfumes up there, so I don't have a lot of weight up there either.
The quality is, of course, disappointing, as the shelf is awesome in design, and fits my space perfectly, I just wish it had been made better.

column6: Aiyaya 1carat Cut Cz Solitaire Bridal Ring
column13: it stands alone beautiful, or is the perfect addition to a band
column14:
this type of ring fits my style perfectly. simple, yet bold, without being ostentatious. it stands alone beautiful, or is the perfect addition to a band. four prongs gracefully spring up and cradle the square cut, securing it in place. it sparkles like the real thing.
i'm not one to go gaga over diamonds. in fact, i wanted a pearl. when my husband and i got married, we grabbed $15 bands from walmart and called it a night. he still teases me over the disaster that was ring shopping. but something simple yet elegant like this goes over very well. it's perfect for anyone that needs a replacement, but doesn't want to fork over thousands of dollars for one. or if one is going somewhere and wants to wear a stone, but doesn't want to risk losing or damaging their real stone. no one will know at all that it's not the real one!
i received this ring for free for my honest and unbiased review of it. i was not compensated in any way.

column6: 14k Rose Gold Diamond \Stackable\" Band"
column14:
I was looking for something delicate that I could stack with a 4mm simple wedding band, and this ring is perfect. I love the contemporary, clean look that it creates when I wear it with a plain rose gold band. The embedded diamonds show from the top & wrap nicely around the sides, but not so far that it causes irritation between my fingers. The diamonds are sparkly & the metal is very pretty and shiny. The color is a nice, subtle rose gold. Definitely a pink tone, but not too overpowering. It is true to the product photo, maybe a tiny bit less coppery.

It is thin, but not flimsy. The diamonds are mounted a little higher than I'd like, but the ring is only 1.8 mm wide, and the shared prong setting adds height to the ring. These are not channel set diamonds, they are prong set, so the ring sits a little higher than my wedding band. If you want a ring that will sit flush right next to a plain wedding band, then look for a channel setting.

Okay, that's it! I love it! I'm thrilled with the quality and the color. It's not chunky, but it looks like it will hold up. I looked at rose gold jewelry at quality jewelers before I made this purchase to compare color, design choices, and quality. Imho, this is a comparable ring at an affordable price.

column13: If you're a half size, go larger.
column14:
Ring is pretty true to size. I'm a 9.5 and got a 9 since I didn't want it to be loose. I'm now wishing I had gone with the 10. It's rubber so there is a little give however not enough to go up a half size. If you're on the fence about getting this, I'd recommend moving forward. If you're a half size, I'd recommend sizing up.

UPDATE:

I put a little brake cleaner on the ring and worked it around twice. This caused the ring two swell just enough that it's a much better fit. If you'r rings too tight and you can't or don't want to return it, try the brake cleaner, it worked for me. NOTE: Exposing it to harsh chemicals such as brake cleaner may reduce the integrity of the ring causing damage.

column6: Olen Cubic Zirconia Wedding Band Ring
column13: ... ring is just a tad bigger than i usually like, as i feel silly in anything large
column14:
the stone on this ring is just a tad bigger than i usually like, as i feel silly in anything large. that might be my own preference, though, because it's a very pretty ring that i think most women would love. the large middle stone is cut into a square, surrounded by smaller stones. these stones also extend to the band, giving the entire look a sparkly, beautiful appearance.
i am by no means high maintenance. when we got married, we grabbed $15 rings at walmart and eloped. i did have a pearl ring that i wore for a long time until i lost it. so something simple like this would be perfect for me. it makes a great replacement, if someone does not want to shell out the same amount they would spend on a small car to buy a new diamond. there are any number of reasons to purchase costume jewelry, but this one at least looks like the real thing, and not something your grandmother would wear.
i received this ring for free for my honest and unbiased review of it. i was not compensated in any way.

I'm usually very cautious about china-based products that are being shipped. One reason being because of the long shipping times, and another reason being the quality. So here is my honest review of this product (picture included):

It came MUCH sooner than I expected. In fact, it came pretty darn fast for an overseas shipment. The pearl is a little bigger than the picture shows & the chain is thinner. It doesn't look as elegant as the picture. At first I didn't like it, but when I tried it on it looked okay. Overall I enjoyed the purchase and I actually wear the necklace. At the end of the day you are getting what you pay for.

UPDATE: I don't ever wear this anymore. It lasted for a while, but the chain got rusty. The pearl itself got discolored too. As I had said in my initial review, you are getting what you pay for. I would not give this as a gift, however I would still say it is okay to buy for yourself. As long as you are okay with it being a temporary item in your jewelry box. Personally, I am fine with that because of the low cost.

column6: AUCHENTOSHAN SINGLE MALT SCOTCH PIN BADGE / LAPEL PIN
column14:
Show your love of the classic lowland malt with this lapel pin!

A few words are in order about this great single. Auchentoshan is considered the archetypal Lowland, along with Rosebank. It was always the first lowland I introduced new whisky buffs to at tastings because of it's very balanced and integrated character. Lowland whiskies are typically triple distilled comoared to the highlands but there are exceptions as the highland single Glenmorangie is also.

My other two fave lowlands were Littlemill, which was notable for it's cocoanut and vanilla flavors and overall very sweet and fruity character. I've seen bottles of Littlemill that you could literally pour over ice cream (I've done it, fun stuff :-)) like you could one of the sweeter bourbons. Littlemill could have quite an expressive range, though; check out the tasting notes on various bottlings by this reviewer who seems to have a pretty perceptive palate:

http://www.maltmadness.com/whisky/littlemill.html

Then there was Bladnoch, which has a very lemony, lemon-grass, citrus-like taste. As I considered those more "specialist" type lowland malts I would often follow the Auchentoshan with those. The point was to demonstrate that the lowlands could be almost as individualistic and eccentric as the weirder Islays such as Caol Ila since the lowlands usually don't get as much attention as the other regions.

Note I said "almost" because in general the lowlands are traditionally considered softer and more approachable than the other regions. But they're an important part of a good tasting. You progress from the lowlands to the highlands and other regions and finally to the Islays. The lowlands are more well behaved; you start there and then end up with the Islays where you're in psycho-freakshow territory. :-) Usually the Caol Ila or one of the "liquid peat" Ardbegs was the last malt on the list. For a while I used a Cadenhead barrel strength Ardbeg at around 120 proof that was ridiculous; it tasted like heavily peated shoe or nail polish, until it ran out. I've seen died in the wool Islay drinkers almost spit it out and not be able to finish a shot. A tasting can be a lot of fun if set up right. :-)

Now of course there are always the exceptions and limitations to the geographic approach. The classic examples of that are Bruichladdich and Bunnahabhain which are not typical Islays and are more like southern highland or even lowland malts. Most of the Islay lovers I've given those to who had never tried them before were disappointed. On the other hand, they liked the Springbank and Highland Park which although Campbelltown and Orkney malts respectively are basically second cousin to the Islays. They even liked a Clynelish which I mixed 50-50 with a Longmorn better (the favorite concoction of the late, great Victorian connoisseur, Professor Saintsbury--who am I to disagree with the professor?) LOL; it tasted like heavily peated shoe or nail polish, until it ran out. I've seen died in the wool Islay drinkers almost spit it out and not be able to finish a shot. A tasting can be a lot of fun if set up right. :-) Now of course there are always the exceptions and limitations to the geographic approach. Cheap quality. 2015-08-11 US 13269510 R3IPRXTW9GSZAE B00IWON18O 95978904 King Will 8mm Mens Tungsten Carbide High Polished Celtic Laser Etched Ring Jewelry 5 0 0 N N I love gunmetal When I received this ring, I opened the very nice box, pulled it out, and initially thought that it was quite heavy. Now that it's been on for a while, it somehow managed to be comfortable enough that I'm now forgetting that I'm wearing it. It feels sturdy, which is wonderful for me, as I tend to demolish my jewelry. I'm also enjoying the fact that the color is actually more of a gun metal color, and not a chrome type of sheen. It looks less flashy, and that's just the way I like it. I've never actually had a tungsten ring, so it hasn't occurred to me until I was wearing it, that even when I scrape it or run into things, it's not scratching out marring the metal in any way. column6: Parma77 Fashion Light Green Jade Queen Bangle Bracelet Christmas Gift
column14:
This is a very beautiful real jade bangle, smoothly polished and a light to medium green. Burmese jade is one of the most desirable (and expensive types), because it comes from Myanmar/Burma and is mined in limited quantities. Jade is supposed to bring luck, health and energy to the wearer.

It came in a perfectly gorgeous pillowed gift box and was nestled inside a yellow brocade gift bag - perfect for gift giving. I have large hands for a woman, and I couldn't get the large size over my hand despite squishing and soaping my hand. It did fit over my adult daughter's medium sized hand, though. Keep in mind that women with larger hands might not be able to wear this bangle (I was sad because I love Jade).

Because jade can be simulated with dyed quartz, marble and green garnet, I did a couple of tests and feel certain that this is authentic grade-A jade:

- real jade has a very high density and feels heavier than it looks, and this bracelet certainly does.
- Using a magnifying glass and bright light, I could see small fiber-y bits in the stone, which indicates real jade
- It feels cool to the touch, and takes a while to warm up to body temperature - another indicator of genuine jade
- I tried to make a tiny scratch on the inside of bangle using a knife but was unable to scratch it - jade is harder than glass or metal

Overall, this is an object of beauty and a bangle any woman would love to wear. I received a complimentary Parma77 jade bangle for review purposes. I wasn't asked to leave a positive review, nor was I paid or otherwise compensated for reviewing this item. Look at the hundreds of reviews I've written over ten years and you'll see that I work hard to give an honest opinion of the products I review.

column14:
This pink camo ring is absolutely beautiful. I normally wear a size 5 but with certain materials, my finger can swell up during the summer especially if it's hot outside. So I went with a 6.5. It was PERFECT! Even though my finger swelled up, I was still able to pull it off right away without any fuss.

I wear this ring out now more than any other ring. I have gotten several compliments on it and that makes me very happy. All I say to those who ask where it came from is "AntlerRings.com!". As a woman, I prefer wearing something more feminine over something neutral or masculine. Don't get me wrong! I love everything camo. The design itself fits perfectly for a woman. It's camo but with a floral like essence.

This would make a great wedding ring for that future camo wedding you may have OR it's a great ring to purchase just because. I have dinged it against a couple things and it still looks like it did the day I first received it. I am happy with it and I know anyone who buys it will be too!

column6: Aiyaya Jewelry 0.5 Ct Round Cut 4 Prong Sona Wedding Ring
column13: and sparkles like the real thing
column14:
what a gorgeous piece! it's one big rock surrounded by several smaller ones in a circle, and then the smaller ones go down the band. there are hearts cut out of the band below the four pronged large stone. it has a stunning smooth finish, and sparkles like the real thing.
it comes in a little red pouch, with the tag attached stating the size. the pouch makes a great presentation by itself, or you can choose a different method.
when i got married, we eloped, and we just got simple bands from walmart for $15 each. obviously i'm not the kind of girl that likes showing flashy stones. in fact, i wanted a pearl. but it's a nice ring for someone that wants a cheaper replacement, or for someone that wants to wear a rock but is going to a place where they are risking loss or damage. or someone that has watched blood diamond, and cannot stomach the thought of having something like that on their finger. either way, it's perfect!
i received this ring at a discount for my honest and unbiased review of it. i was not compensated in any way.

column6: Dainty Rose Gold Plated Heart Pendant Necklace - Jewelry for Young Girls, Kids, Children, Teens
column13: This Rose Gold Heart Necklace with Crystals by SmitCo LLC is a very Beautiful and Unique Necklace!
column14:
This Rose Gold Heart Necklace with Crystals by SmitCo LLC is a very Beautiful and Unique Necklace!
The Dainty Pendant is made up of Two Separate Portions.
The Left Side is a Solid Rose Gold Plated Alloy Metal Piece which is Curved in the Shape of the Outside of the Heart.
The Right Side contains 28 Multi-Faceted 1/16" Rhinestone Crystals which have been Pin Set to Secure them into the Rose Gold Plated Alloy Metal Base. The Reverse side of this portion shows the Tiny Pin Holes where the Crystals have been lovingly set into place.
When the Two Portions Nest Together, they form a Stunning and Sparkling 1/2" Pendant.
Each Separate Piece is Strung by an Opening onto a Delicate, but Sturdy 15" Rose Gold Plated Link Chain.
The Chain offers a Lobster Claw Clasp on one end and a 19 Link Extender on the other.
Gifting this Exquisite Rose Gold Plated Heart Necklace is a wonderful way to show the woman or young lady you hold close to your heart how grateful you are that they are in your life.
I received mine in exchange for my unbiased review and I will be gifting it to my sister who was there for me when I was going through some difficult times and needed her support the most.
As SmitCo LLC shipped it in a Very Pretty Gift Box, complete with Satin Ribbon and Bow attached to the box top, all I need to do is write the card which will accompany the gift.
A+++ Recommendation!

column13: Great kit for people just starting their ear stretching.
column14: I've just started stretching my ears and was using my friend's acrylic tappers and needed a kit of my own. (PS I have nothing against using acrylic tappers or plugs, I just suggested you clean your lobes regularly and soak the tapper in hydrogen peroxide). I was on size 6g when I received my kit in the mail. I mainly chose this kit for the tunnels because my friend's tappers were so long in the back they got caught on everything! The tunnels are so much nicer to wear. Since then I've gone up to size 4g and the tappers worked wonderful. There was a little bit of soreness but in a couple of hours it had subsided. Personally I prefer the steel kit over acrylic, but to each its own. This is an affordable kit with the option of tunnels or plugs. I would recommend this kit to anyone starting out. It came right on time and all pieces were there.

column14:
This Platinum-Plated Copper AAA Cubic Zirconia Ring is absolutely beautiful! If you are a fan of bling then you will definitely love this ring because it's got tons of sparkly bling. I would say that this ring is definitely true to size as my fingers are bigger then the average women so I got the size 7 for my pinkie which I think it looks pretty great on that finger; for me anyways. The center piece isn't overly big but it's also not small either which I really like because again my hands/fingers aren't small. The only down side to this ring is that it is platinum-plated however if you start to notice the band tarnishing you can put a layer of clear finger nail polish on it which will and can help keep it from tarnishing. Overall this ring is a great piece and would be great as a gift. I would definitely recommend this Platinum-Plated Copper AAA Cubic Zirconia Ring!

column6: Pink SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS Crystal Teddy Bear Charm Pendant Necklace Women Fashion Animal Jewelry
column14:
This Crystal Teddy Bear Pendant by Swarovski is so adorable. I got it for my niece for her birthday. She absolutely loves anything shiny and teddy bears.
I thought it was a tiny bear but it is pretty big at 3.26 inches. She really loved how the teddy bears head, arms and legs would move around. She said it looked like the bear was dancing.

It is made of white gold plated alloy that is eco-friendly, so it shouldn't rust or turn your skin green and will stay shiny a long time.
The teddy bear has a beautiful pink crystal on it's tummy with a bow on it. And it's whole body has shiny colorful crystals all over it. The back of the bear has an open design to it which allows light to shine through the pink crystal and makes it look so gorgeous.
It's really a beautiful piece with great craftsmanship.

My niece wore it to Disney World this weekend and she received so many compliments on it.
She was one happy little girl.
I do plan on getting her a smaller chain for it because this chain is a tab bit to long for her. The chains length is 31 1/2 inches.

column6:
Sterling Silver, Amethyst, Rose de France, and Diamond-Accent Heart Pendant Necklace, 18\" Jewelry 5 4 5 Y N Hearts and Flowers [[VIDEOID:48f392c7fd1f105c020c7bf7bdd39d00]] To be clear, this is an Amethyst pendant with a single SMALL diamond. And 'Rose de France' is simply a fancy name for an amethyst that is light in color.
The diamond is a 0.005 carat stone. Most people outside of the jewelry business would call it a diamond chip, jewelers would call it a melee diamond.
No matter what name you use, it is barely visible, smaller than a speck of glitter. If you can't see the video on your device, feel free to leave a comment and I'll help as best I can.

At this price point, you can't expect all of the amethyst to be rich and dark, or have a high quality diamond. Even so, this is not costume jewelry, you are getting a precious metal and authentic stones.
It comes with a fine gauge box link chain.
At this point in time, it appears that the pendant DOES include a gift box, as stated in the description, although mine did not.

I got this because a model in GQ wore a similar bracelet in 18kt white gold that cost $8,300. Anyway, I needed a birthday present to give to my housemate - so it fit him, so I gave it to him. I will keep looking for one that is actually more like 9", that when worse fits a 8.25" wrist.

5 stars for quick deliver, 5 star for craftsmanship, 5 star for stunning look, 3 star for misleading size.

column13: Nice quality, fun cufflinks for Trekkies
column14:
These are the most adorable cufflinks - not exactly Star Trek but 100% retro vibe of the Star Trek time period. What you can't see very clearly in the prduct pic is that the center is a bright white enamel surface making these even prettier in person than in the picture. The quality is very good and the price is very low for what you are actually getting. I honestly think they could sell these for more and actually get it.

The silver tone metal these are made of is supposed to resist fading and shine loss. They look a bit stainless steel to me but I'm not sure and I couldn't find the exact metal these are made out of. Only time will tell about durability.

I really really like these. Other than that, they come packged well and include a lovely little gift box.

Recommend.

I purchased these at a discount in exchange for my honest opinion.

column14:
These earrings are absolutely adorable. I bought these for my daughter since she seems to have a sensitivity to the majority of earrings out there, and so far they haven't irritated her ears at all. Some of the earrings that I've had in the past were advertised as sterling sliver and actually ended up being only silver plated and tarnishing over time, but these haven't shown any signs of tarnishing. The earring backs fit on snug and take a little extra effort to get off, which helps prevent accidental falling out. These earrings are very cute and petite for a little girl or anyone who likes less complex and lightweight earrings. I am a sucker for packaging (I have no idea why) but I loved the packaging these came in. They came in a zipper plastic case and a tie string bag inside of that. These are great quality for an incredible price, I am very very happy with these.

I received these in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.
